acm:AddTagsToCertificate.Description: Adds one or more tags to an ACM Certificate. Tags are labels that you can use to identify and organize your AWS resources. Each tag consists of a key and an optional value. You specify the certificate on input by its Amazon Resource Name (ARN). You specify the tag by using a key-value pair.
acm:AddTagsToCertificate.Title: AddTagsToCertificate

acm:DeleteCertificate.Description: Deletes an ACM Certificate and its associated private key. If this action succeeds, the certificate no longer appears in the list of ACM Certificates that can be displayed by calling the ListCertificates action or be retrieved by calling the GetCertificate action. The certificate will not be available for use by other AWS services.
acm:DeleteCertificate.Title: DeleteCertificate

acm:DescribeCertificate.Description: Returns detailed metadata about the specified ACM Certificate.
acm:DescribeCertificate.Title: DescribeCertificate

acm:GetCertificate.Description: Retrieves an ACM Certificate and certificate chain for the certificate specified by an ARN. The chain is an ordered list of certificates that contains the ACM Certificate, intermediate certificates of subordinate CAs, and the root certificate in that order. The certificate and certificate chain are base64 encoded. If you want to decode the certificate chain to see the individual certificate fields, you can use OpenSSL.
acm:GetCertificate.Title: GetCertificate

acm:ImportCertificate.Description: Imports an SSL/TLS certificate into AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) to use with ACM's integrated AWS services.
acm:ImportCertificate.Title: ImportCertificate

acm:ListCertificates.Description: Retrieves a list of ACM Certificates and the domain name for each. You can optionally filter the list to return only the certificates that match the specified status.
acm:ListCertificates.Title: ListCertificates

acm:ListTagsForCertificate.Description: Lists the tags that have been applied to the ACM Certificate. Use the certificate's Amazon Resource Name (ARN) to specify the certificate. To add a tag to an ACM Certificate, use the AddTagsToCertificate action. To delete a tag, use the RemoveTagsFromCertificate action.
acm:ListTagsForCertificate.Title: ListTagsForCertificate

acm:RemoveTagsFromCertificate.Description: Remove one or more tags from an ACM Certificate. A tag consists of a key-value pair. If you do not specify the value portion of the tag when calling this function, the tag will be removed regardless of value. If you specify a value, the tag is removed only if it is associated with the specified value.
acm:RemoveTagsFromCertificate.Title: RemoveTagsFromCertificate

acm:RequestCertificate.Description: Requests an ACM Certificate for use with other AWS services. To request an ACM Certificate, you must specify the fully qualified domain name (FQDN) for your site in the DomainName parameter. You can also specify additional FQDNs in the SubjectAlternativeNames parameter if users can reach your site by using other names.
acm:RequestCertificate.Title: RequestCertificate

acm:ResendValidationEmail.Description: Resends the email that requests domain ownership validation. The domain owner or an authorized representative must approve the ACM Certificate before it can be issued. The certificate can be approved by clicking a link in the mail to navigate to the Amazon certificate approval website and then clicking I Approve. However, the validation email can be blocked by spam filters. Therefore, if you do not receive the original mail, you can request that the mail be resent within 72 hours of requesting the ACM Certificate. If more than 72 hours have elapsed since your original request or since your last attempt to resend validation mail, you must request a new certificate. For more information about setting up your contact email addresses, see Configure Email for your Domain.
acm:ResendValidationEmail.Title: ResendValidationEmail

application-autoscaling:DeleteScalingPol.Description: Deletes the specified Application Auto Scaling scaling policy.
application-autoscaling:DeleteScalingPol.Title: DeleteScalingPolicy

application-autoscaling:DescribeScalable.Description: Provides descriptive information about the scalable targets in the specified namespace.
application-autoscaling:DescribeScalable.Title: DescribeScalableTargets

application-autoscaling:DescribeScalingA.Description: Provides descriptive information about the scaling activities in the specified namespace from the previous six weeks.
application-autoscaling:DescribeScalingA.Title: DescribeScalingActivities

application-autoscaling:DescribeScalingP.Description: Describes the scaling policies for the specified service namespace.
application-autoscaling:DescribeScalingP.Title: DescribeScalingPolicies

application-autoscaling:PutScalingPolicy.Description: Creates or updates a policy for an Application Auto Scaling scalable target.
application-autoscaling:PutScalingPolicy.Title: PutScalingPolicy

application-autoscaling:RegisterScalable.Description: Registers or updates a scalable target. A scalable target is a resource that Application Auto Scaling can scale out or scale in. After you have registered a scalable target, you can use this operation to update the minimum and maximum values for your scalable dimension.
application-autoscaling:RegisterScalable.Title: RegisterScalableTarget

athena:BatchGetNamedQuery.Description: Returns the details of a single named query or a list of up to 50 queries, which you provide as an array of query ID strings. Use ListNamedQueries to get the list of named query IDs. If information could not be retrieved for a submitted query ID, information about the query ID submitted is listed under UnprocessedNamedQueryId. Named queries are different from executed queries. Use BatchGetQueryExecution to get details about each unique query execution, and ListQueryExecutions to get a list of query execution IDs.
athena:BatchGetNamedQuery.Title: BatchGetNamedQuery

athena:BatchGetQueryExecution.Description: Returns the details of a single query execution or a list of up to 50 query executions, which you provide as an array of query execution ID strings. To get a list of query execution IDs, use ListQueryExecutions. Query executions are different from named (saved) queries. Use BatchGetNamedQuery to get details about named queries.
athena:BatchGetQueryExecution.Title: BatchGetQueryExecution

athena:GetNamedQuery.Description: Returns information about a single query.
athena:GetNamedQuery.Title: GetNamedQuery

athena:GetQueryExecution.Description: Returns information about a single execution of a query. Each time a query executes, information about the query execution is saved with a unique ID.
athena:GetQueryExecution.Title: GetQueryExecution

athena:GetQueryResults.Description: Returns the results of a single query execution specified by QueryExecutionId. This request does not execute the query but returns results. Use StartQueryExecution to run a query.
athena:GetQueryResults.Title: GetQueryResults

athena:ListNamedQueries.Description: Provides a list of all available query IDs.
athena:ListNamedQueries.Title: ListNamedQueries

athena:ListQueryExecutions.Description: Provides a list of all available query execution IDs.
athena:ListQueryExecutions.Title: ListQueryExecutions

athena:StartQueryExecution.Description: Runs (executes) the SQL query statements contained in the Query string.
athena:StartQueryExecution.Title: StartQueryExecution

autoscaling:AttachInstances.Description: Attaches one or more EC2 instances to the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:AttachInstances.Title: AttachInstances

autoscaling:AttachLoadBalancers.Description: Attaches one or more Classic Load Balancers to the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:AttachLoadBalancers.Title: AttachLoadBalancers

autoscaling:CompleteLifecycleAction.Description: Completes the lifecycle action for the specified token or instance with the specified result.
autoscaling:CompleteLifecycleAction.Title: CompleteLifecycleAction

autoscaling:CreateAutoScalingGroup.Description: Creates an Auto Scaling group with the specified name and attributes.
autoscaling:CreateAutoScalingGroup.Title: CreateAutoScalingGroup

autoscaling:CreateOrUpdateTags.Description: Creates or updates tags for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:CreateOrUpdateTags.Title: CreateOrUpdateTags

autoscaling:DeleteAutoScalingGroup.Description: Deletes the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DeleteAutoScalingGroup.Title: DeleteAutoScalingGroup

autoscaling:DeletePolicy.Description: Deletes the specified Auto Scaling policy.
autoscaling:DeletePolicy.Title: DeletePolicy

autoscaling:DescribeAccountLimits.Description: Describes the current Auto Scaling resource limits for your AWS account.
autoscaling:DescribeAccountLimits.Title: DescribeAccountLimits

autoscaling:DescribeAdjustmentTypes.Description: Describes the policy adjustment types for use with PutScalingPolicy.
autoscaling:DescribeAdjustmentTypes.Title: DescribeAdjustmentTypes

autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingGroups.Description: Describes one or more Auto Scaling groups.
autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingGroups.Title: DescribeAutoScalingGroups

autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingInstances.Description: Describes one or more Auto Scaling instances.
autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingInstances.Title: DescribeAutoScalingInstances

autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingNotificat.Description: Describes the notification types that are supported by Auto Scaling.
autoscaling:DescribeAutoScalingNotificat.Title: DescribeAutoScalingNotificationTypes

autoscaling:DescribeLaunchConfigurations.Description: Describes one or more launch configurations.
autoscaling:DescribeLaunchConfigurations.Title: DescribeLaunchConfigurations

autoscaling:DescribeLifecycleHookTypes.Description: Describes the available types of lifecycle hooks.
autoscaling:DescribeLifecycleHookTypes.Title: DescribeLifecycleHookTypes

autoscaling:DescribeLifecycleHooks.Description: Describes the lifecycle hooks for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DescribeLifecycleHooks.Title: DescribeLifecycleHooks

autoscaling:DescribeLoadBalancers.Description: Describes the load balancers for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DescribeLoadBalancers.Title: DescribeLoadBalancers

autoscaling:DescribeMetricCollectionType.Description: Describes the available CloudWatch metrics for Auto Scaling.
autoscaling:DescribeMetricCollectionType.Title: DescribeMetricCollectionTypes

autoscaling:DescribeNotificationConfigur.Description: Describes the notification actions associated with the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DescribeNotificationConfigur.Title: DescribeNotificationConfigurations

autoscaling:DescribePolicies.Description: Describes the policies for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DescribePolicies.Title: DescribePolicies

autoscaling:DescribeScalingActivities.Description: Describes one or more scaling activities for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DescribeScalingActivities.Title: DescribeScalingActivities

autoscaling:DescribeScalingProcessTypes.Description: Describes the scaling process types for use with ResumeProcesses and SuspendProcesses.
autoscaling:DescribeScalingProcessTypes.Title: DescribeScalingProcessTypes

autoscaling:DescribeScheduledActions.Description: Describes the actions scheduled for your Auto Scaling group that haven't run. To describe the actions that have already run, use DescribeScalingActivities.
autoscaling:DescribeScheduledActions.Title: DescribeScheduledActions

autoscaling:DescribeTerminationPolicyTyp.Description: Describes the termination policies supported by Auto Scaling.
autoscaling:DescribeTerminationPolicyTyp.Title: DescribeTerminationPolicyTypes

autoscaling:DetachInstances.Description: Removes one or more instances from the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DetachInstances.Title: DetachInstances

autoscaling:DetachLoadBalancers.Description: Detaches one or more Classic Load Balancers from the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DetachLoadBalancers.Title: DetachLoadBalancers

autoscaling:DisableMetricsCollection.Description: Disables group metrics for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:DisableMetricsCollection.Title: DisableMetricsCollection

autoscaling:EnableMetricsCollection.Description: Enables group metrics for the specified Auto Scaling group. For more information, see Monitoring Your Auto Scaling Groups and Instances in the Auto Scaling User Guide.
autoscaling:EnableMetricsCollection.Title: EnableMetricsCollection

autoscaling:EnterStandby.Description: Moves the specified instances into the standby state.
autoscaling:EnterStandby.Title: EnterStandby

autoscaling:ExitStandby.Description: Moves the specified instances out of the standby state.
autoscaling:ExitStandby.Title: ExitStandby

autoscaling:PutLifecycleHook.Description: Creates or updates a lifecycle hook for the specified Auto Scaling Group.
autoscaling:PutLifecycleHook.Title: PutLifecycleHook

autoscaling:PutNotificationConfiguration.Description: Configures an Auto Scaling group to send notifications when specified events take place. Subscribers to the specified topic can have messages delivered to an endpoint such as a web server or an email address.
autoscaling:PutNotificationConfiguration.Title: PutNotificationConfiguration

autoscaling:PutScalingPolicy.Description: Creates or updates a policy for an Auto Scaling group. To update an existing policy, use the existing policy name and set the parameters you want to change. Any existing parameter not changed in an update to an existing policy is not changed in this update request.
autoscaling:PutScalingPolicy.Title: PutScalingPolicy

autoscaling:PutScheduledUpdateGroupActio.Description: Creates or updates a scheduled scaling action for an Auto Scaling group. When updating a scheduled scaling action, if you leave a parameter unspecified, the corresponding value remains unchanged.
autoscaling:PutScheduledUpdateGroupActio.Title: PutScheduledUpdateGroupAction

autoscaling:RecordLifecycleActionHeartbe.Description: Records a heartbeat for the lifecycle action associated with the specified token or instance. This extends the timeout by the length of time defined using PutLifecycleHook.
autoscaling:RecordLifecycleActionHeartbe.Title: RecordLifecycleActionHeartbeat

autoscaling:ResumeProcesses.Description: Resumes the specified suspended Auto Scaling processes, or all suspended process, for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:ResumeProcesses.Title: ResumeProcesses

autoscaling:SetDesiredCapacity.Description: Sets the size of the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:SetDesiredCapacity.Title: SetDesiredCapacity

autoscaling:SetInstanceHealth.Description: Sets the health status of the specified instance.
autoscaling:SetInstanceHealth.Title: SetInstanceHealth

autoscaling:SetInstanceProtection.Description: Updates the instance protection settings of the specified instances.
autoscaling:SetInstanceProtection.Title: SetInstanceProtection

autoscaling:SuspendProcesses.Description: Suspends the specified Auto Scaling processes, or all processes, for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:SuspendProcesses.Title: SuspendProcesses

autoscaling:TerminateInstanceInAutoScali.Description: Terminates the specified instance and optionally adjusts the desired group size.
autoscaling:TerminateInstanceInAutoScali.Title: TerminateInstanceInAutoScalingGroup

autoscaling:UpdateAutoScalingGroup.Description: Updates the configuration for the specified Auto Scaling group.
autoscaling:UpdateAutoScalingGroup.Title: UpdateAutoScalingGroup

batch:CancelJob.Description: Cancels a job in an AWS Batch job queue. Jobs that are in the SUBMITTED, PENDING, or RUNNABLE state are cancelled. Jobs that have progressed to STARTING or RUNNING are not cancelled (but the API operation still succeeds, even if no job is cancelled); these jobs must be terminated with the TerminateJob operation.
batch:CancelJob.Title: CancelJob

batch:CreateComputeEnvironment.Description: Creates an AWS Batch compute environment. You can create MANAGED or UNMANAGED compute environments.
batch:CreateComputeEnvironment.Title: CreateComputeEnvironment

batch:CreateJobQueue.Description: Creates an AWS Batch job queue. When you create a job queue, you associate one or more compute environments to the queue and assign an order of preference for the compute environments.
batch:CreateJobQueue.Title: CreateJobQueue

batch:DeleteComputeEnvironment.Description: Deletes an AWS Batch compute environment.
batch:DeleteComputeEnvironment.Title: DeleteComputeEnvironment

batch:DeleteJobQueue.Description: Deletes the specified job queue. You must first disable submissions for a queue with the UpdateJobQueue operation. All jobs in the queue are terminated when you delete a job queue.
batch:DeleteJobQueue.Title: DeleteJobQueue

batch:DeregisterJobDefinition.Description: Deregisters an AWS Batch job definition.
batch:DeregisterJobDefinition.Title: DeregisterJobDefinition

batch:DescribeComputeEnvironments.Description: Describes one or more of your compute environments.
batch:DescribeComputeEnvironments.Title: DescribeComputeEnvironments

batch:DescribeJobDefinitions.Description: Describes a list of job definitions. You can specify a status (such as ACTIVE) to only return job definitions that match that status.
batch:DescribeJobDefinitions.Title: DescribeJobDefinitions

batch:DescribeJobQueues.Description: Describes one or more of your job queues.
batch:DescribeJobQueues.Title: DescribeJobQueues

batch:DescribeJobs.Description: Describes a list of AWS Batch jobs.
batch:DescribeJobs.Title: DescribeJobs

batch:ListJobs.Description: Returns a list of task jobs for a specified job queue. You can filter the results by job status with the jobStatus parameter. If you do not specify a status, only RUNNING jobs are returned.
batch:ListJobs.Title: ListJobs

batch:RegisterJobDefinition.Description: Registers an AWS Batch job definition.
batch:RegisterJobDefinition.Title: RegisterJobDefinition

batch:SubmitJob.Description: Submits an AWS Batch job from a job definition. Parameters specified during SubmitJob override parameters defined in the job definition.
batch:SubmitJob.Title: SubmitJob

batch:TerminateJob.Description: Terminates a job in a job queue. Jobs that are in the STARTING or RUNNING state are terminated, which causes them to transition to FAILED. Jobs that have not progressed to the STARTING state are cancelled.
batch:TerminateJob.Title: TerminateJob

batch:UpdateComputeEnvironment.Description: Updates an AWS Batch compute environment.
batch:UpdateComputeEnvironment.Title: UpdateComputeEnvironment

budgets:ModifyBudget.Description: This reference summarizes the default actions that are permitted in Billing and Cost Management for each type of billing user and the billing permissions that you can apply to your IAM users. The reference also provides examples of policies that you can use to allow or deny an IAM user access to your billing information and tools.
budgets:ModifyBudget.Title: Billing and Cost Management Permissions Reference

budgets:ViewBudget.Description: This reference summarizes the default actions that are permitted in Billing and Cost Management for each type of billing user and the billing permissions that you can apply to your IAM users. The reference also provides examples of policies that you can use to allow or deny an IAM user access to your billing information and tools.
budgets:ViewBudget.Title: Billing and Cost Management Permissions Reference

clouddirectory:AddFacetToObject.Description: Adds a new Facet to an object. An object can have more than one facet applied on it.
clouddirectory:AddFacetToObject.Title: AddFacetToObject

clouddirectory:ApplySchema.Description: Copies the input published schema into the Directory with the same name and version as that of the published schema.
clouddirectory:ApplySchema.Title: ApplySchema

clouddirectory:AttachObject.Description: Attaches an existing object to another object. An object can be accessed in two ways:
clouddirectory:AttachObject.Title: AttachObject

clouddirectory:AttachPolicy.Description: Attaches a policy object to a regular object. An object can have a limited number of attached policies.
clouddirectory:AttachPolicy.Title: AttachPolicy

clouddirectory:AttachToIndex.Description: Attaches the specified object to the specified index.
clouddirectory:AttachToIndex.Title: AttachToIndex

clouddirectory:BatchRead.Description: Performs all the read operations in a batch.
clouddirectory:BatchRead.Title: BatchRead

clouddirectory:BatchWrite.Description: Performs all the write operations in a batch. Either all the operations succeed or none.
clouddirectory:BatchWrite.Title: BatchWrite

clouddirectory:CreateDirectory.Description: Creates a Directory by copying the published schema into the directory. A directory cannot be created without a schema.
clouddirectory:CreateDirectory.Title: CreateDirectory

clouddirectory:CreateFacet.Description: Creates a new Facet in a schema. Facet creation is allowed only in development or applied schemas.
clouddirectory:CreateFacet.Title: CreateFacet

clouddirectory:CreateIndex.Description: Creates an index object. See Indexing for more information.
clouddirectory:CreateIndex.Title: CreateIndex

clouddirectory:CreateObject.Description: Creates an object in a Directory. Additionally attaches the object to a parent, if a parent reference and LinkName is specified. An object is simply a collection of Facet attributes. You can also use this API call to create a policy object, if the facet from which you create the object is a policy facet.
clouddirectory:CreateObject.Title: CreateObject

clouddirectory:CreateSchema.Description: Creates a new schema in a development state. A schema can exist in three phases:
clouddirectory:CreateSchema.Title: CreateSchema

clouddirectory:DeleteDirectory.Description: Deletes a directory. Only disabled directories can be deleted. A deleted directory cannot be undone. Exercise extreme caution when deleting directories.
clouddirectory:DeleteDirectory.Title: DeleteDirectory

clouddirectory:DeleteFacet.Description: Deletes a given Facet. All attributes and Rules that are associated with the facet will be deleted. Only development schema facets are allowed deletion.
clouddirectory:DeleteFacet.Title: DeleteFacet

clouddirectory:DeleteObject.Description: Deletes an object and its associated attributes. Only objects with no children and no parents can be deleted.
clouddirectory:DeleteObject.Title: DeleteObject

clouddirectory:DeleteSchema.Description: Deletes a given schema. Schemas in a development and published state can only be deleted.
clouddirectory:DeleteSchema.Title: DeleteSchema

clouddirectory:DetachFromIndex.Description: Detaches the specified object from the specified index.
clouddirectory:DetachFromIndex.Title: DetachFromIndex

clouddirectory:DetachObject.Description: Detaches a given object from the parent object. The object that is to be detached from the parent is specified by the link name.
clouddirectory:DetachObject.Title: DetachObject

clouddirectory:DetachPolicy.Description: Detaches a policy from an object.
clouddirectory:DetachPolicy.Title: DetachPolicy

clouddirectory:DisableDirectory.Description: Disables the specified directory. Disabled directories cannot be read or written to. Only enabled directories can be disabled. Disabled directories may be reenabled.
clouddirectory:DisableDirectory.Title: DisableDirectory

clouddirectory:EnableDirectory.Description: Enables the specified directory. Only disabled directories can be enabled. Once enabled, the directory can then be read and written to.
clouddirectory:EnableDirectory.Title: EnableDirectory

clouddirectory:GetFacet.Description: Gets details of the Facet, such as facet name, attributes, Rules, or ObjectType. You can call this on all kinds of schema facets -- published, development, or applied.
clouddirectory:GetFacet.Title: GetFacet

clouddirectory:GetSchemaAsJson.Description: Retrieves a JSON representation of the schema. See JSON Schema Format for more information.
clouddirectory:GetSchemaAsJson.Title: GetSchemaAsJson

clouddirectory:ListAppliedSchemaArns.Description: Lists schemas applied to a directory.
clouddirectory:ListAppliedSchemaArns.Title: ListAppliedSchemaArns

clouddirectory:ListAttachedIndices.Description: Lists indices attached to the specified object.
clouddirectory:ListAttachedIndices.Title: ListAttachedIndices

clouddirectory:ListDevelopmentSchemaArns.Description: Retrieves each Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of schemas in the development state.
clouddirectory:ListDevelopmentSchemaArns.Title: ListDevelopmentSchemaArns

clouddirectory:ListDirectories.Description: Lists directories created within an account.
clouddirectory:ListDirectories.Title: ListDirectories

clouddirectory:ListFacetAttributes.Description: Retrieves attributes attached to the facet.
clouddirectory:ListFacetAttributes.Title: ListFacetAttributes

clouddirectory:ListFacetNames.Description: Retrieves the names of facets that exist in a schema.
clouddirectory:ListFacetNames.Title: ListFacetNames

clouddirectory:ListIndex.Description: Lists objects attached to the specified index.
clouddirectory:ListIndex.Title: ListIndex

clouddirectory:ListObjectAttributes.Description: Lists all attributes that are associated with an object.
clouddirectory:ListObjectAttributes.Title: ListObjectAttributes

clouddirectory:ListObjectChildren.Description: Returns a paginated list of child objects that are associated with a given object.
clouddirectory:ListObjectChildren.Title: ListObjectChildren

clouddirectory:ListObjectParents.Description: Lists parent objects that are associated with a given object in pagination fashion.
clouddirectory:ListObjectParents.Title: ListObjectParents

clouddirectory:ListObjectPolicies.Description: Returns policies attached to an object in pagination fashion.
clouddirectory:ListObjectPolicies.Title: ListObjectPolicies

clouddirectory:ListPolicyAttachments.Description: Returns all of the ObjectIdentifiers to which a given policy is attached.
clouddirectory:ListPolicyAttachments.Title: ListPolicyAttachments

clouddirectory:ListPublishedSchemaArns.Description: Retrieves each published schema Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
clouddirectory:ListPublishedSchemaArns.Title: ListPublishedSchemaArns

clouddirectory:ListTagsForResource.Description: Returns tags for a resource. Tagging is currently supported only for directories with a limit of 50 tags per directory. All 50 tags are returned for a given directory with this API call.
clouddirectory:ListTagsForResource.Title: ListTagsForResource

clouddirectory:LookupPolicy.Description: Lists all policies from the root of the Directory to the object specified. If there are no policies present, an empty list is returned. If policies are present, and if some objects don't have the policies attached, it returns the ObjectIdentifier for such objects. If policies are present, it returns ObjectIdentifier, policyId, and policyType. Paths that don't lead to the root from the target object are ignored. For more information, see Policies.
clouddirectory:LookupPolicy.Title: LookupPolicy

clouddirectory:PublishSchema.Description: Publishes a development schema with a version. If description and attributes are specified, PublishSchema overrides the development schema description and attributes. If not, the development schema description and attributes are used.
clouddirectory:PublishSchema.Title: PublishSchema

clouddirectory:PutSchemaFromJson.Description: Allows a schema to be updated using JSON upload. Only available for development schemas. See JSON Schema Format for more information.
clouddirectory:PutSchemaFromJson.Title: PutSchemaFromJson

clouddirectory:RemoveFacetFromObject.Description: Removes the specified facet from the specified object.
clouddirectory:RemoveFacetFromObject.Title: RemoveFacetFromObject

clouddirectory:TagResource.Description: An API operation for adding tags to a resource.
clouddirectory:TagResource.Title: TagResource

clouddirectory:UntagResource.Description: An API operation for removing tags from a resource.
clouddirectory:UntagResource.Title: UntagResource

clouddirectory:UpdateSchema.Description: Updates the schema name with a new name. Only development schema names can be updated.
clouddirectory:UpdateSchema.Title: UpdateSchema

cloudformation:CancelUpdateStack.Description: Cancels an update on the specified stack. If the call completes successfully, the stack rolls back the update and reverts to the previous stack configuration.
cloudformation:CancelUpdateStack.Title: CancelUpdateStack

cloudformation:ContinueUpdateRollback.Description: For a specified stack that is in the UPDATE_ROLLBACK_FAILED state, continues rolling it back to the UPDATE_ROLLBACK_COMPLETE state. Depending on the cause of the failure, you can manually fix the error and continue the rollback. By continuing the rollback, you can return your stack to a working state (the UPDATE_ROLLBACK_COMPLETE state), and then try to update the stack again.
cloudformation:ContinueUpdateRollback.Title: ContinueUpdateRollback

cloudformation:CreateChangeSet.Description: Creates a list of changes that will be applied to a stack so that you can review the changes before executing them. You can create a change set for a stack that doesn't exist or an existing stack. If you create a change set for a stack that doesn't exist, the change set shows all of the resources that AWS CloudFormation will create. If you create a change set for an existing stack, AWS CloudFormation compares the stack's information with the information that you submit in the change set and lists the differences. Use change sets to understand which resources AWS CloudFormation will create or change, and how it will change resources in an existing stack, before you create or update a stack.
cloudformation:CreateChangeSet.Title: CreateChangeSet

cloudformation:CreateStack.Description: Creates a stack as specified in the template. After the call completes successfully, the stack creation starts. You can check the status of the stack via the DescribeStacks API.
cloudformation:CreateStack.Title: CreateStack

cloudformation:DeleteStack.Description: Deletes a specified stack. Once the call completes successfully, stack deletion starts. Deleted stacks do not show up in the DescribeStacks API if the deletion has been completed successfully.
cloudformation:DeleteStack.Title: DeleteStack

cloudformation:DescribeAccountLimits.Description: Retrieves your account's AWS CloudFormation limits, such as the maximum number of stacks that you can create in your account.
cloudformation:DescribeAccountLimits.Title: DescribeAccountLimits

cloudformation:DescribeChangeSet.Description: Returns the inputs for the change set and a list of changes that AWS CloudFormation will make if you execute the change set. For more information, see Updating Stacks Using Change Sets in the AWS CloudFormation User Guide.
cloudformation:DescribeChangeSet.Title: DescribeChangeSet

cloudformation:DescribeStackEvents.Description: Returns all stack related events for a specified stack in reverse chronological order. For more information about a stack's event history, go to Stacks in the AWS CloudFormation User Guide.
cloudformation:DescribeStackEvents.Title: DescribeStackEvents

cloudformation:DescribeStackResource.Description: Returns a description of the specified resource in the specified stack.
cloudformation:DescribeStackResource.Title: DescribeStackResource

cloudformation:DescribeStackResources.Description: Returns AWS resource descriptions for running and deleted stacks. If StackName is specified, all the associated resources that are part of the stack are returned. If PhysicalResourceId is specified, the associated resources of the stack that the resource belongs to are returned.
cloudformation:DescribeStackResources.Title: DescribeStackResources

cloudformation:DescribeStacks.Description: Returns the description for the specified stack; if no stack name was specified, then it returns the description for all the stacks created.
cloudformation:DescribeStacks.Title: DescribeStacks

cloudformation:EstimateTemplateCost.Description: Returns the estimated monthly cost of a template. The return value is an AWS Simple Monthly Calculator URL with a query string that describes the resources required to run the template.
cloudformation:EstimateTemplateCost.Title: EstimateTemplateCost

cloudformation:ExecuteChangeSet.Description: Updates a stack using the input information that was provided when the specified change set was created. After the call successfully completes, AWS CloudFormation starts updating the stack. Use the DescribeStacks action to view the status of the update.
cloudformation:ExecuteChangeSet.Title: ExecuteChangeSet

cloudformation:GetStackPolicy.Description: Returns the stack policy for a specified stack. If a stack doesn't have a policy, a null value is returned.
cloudformation:GetStackPolicy.Title: GetStackPolicy

cloudformation:GetTemplate.Description: Returns the template body for a specified stack. You can get the template for running or deleted stacks.
cloudformation:GetTemplate.Title: GetTemplate

cloudformation:GetTemplateSummary.Description: Returns information about a new or existing template. The GetTemplateSummary action is useful for viewing parameter information, such as default parameter values and parameter types, before you create or update a stack or stack set.
cloudformation:GetTemplateSummary.Title: GetTemplateSummary

cloudformation:ListChangeSets.Description: Returns the ID and status of each active change set for a stack. For example, AWS CloudFormation lists change sets that are in the CREATE_IN_PROGRESS or CREATE_PENDING state.
cloudformation:ListChangeSets.Title: ListChangeSets

cloudformation:ListStackResources.Description: Returns descriptions of all resources of the specified stack.
cloudformation:ListStackResources.Title: ListStackResources

cloudformation:ListStacks.Description: Returns the summary information for stacks whose status matches the specified StackStatusFilter. Summary information for stacks that have been deleted is kept for 90 days after the stack is deleted. If no StackStatusFilter is specified, summary information for all stacks is returned (including existing stacks and stacks that have been deleted).
cloudformation:ListStacks.Title: ListStacks

cloudformation:SetStackPolicy.Description: Sets a stack policy for a specified stack.
cloudformation:SetStackPolicy.Title: SetStackPolicy

cloudformation:SignalResource.Description: Sends a signal to the specified resource with a success or failure status. You can use the SignalResource API in conjunction with a creation policy or update policy. AWS CloudFormation doesn't proceed with a stack creation or update until resources receive the required number of signals or the timeout period is exceeded. The SignalResource API is useful in cases where you want to send signals from anywhere other than an Amazon EC2 instance.
cloudformation:SignalResource.Title: SignalResource

cloudformation:UpdateStack.Description: Updates a stack as specified in the template. After the call completes successfully, the stack update starts. You can check the status of the stack via the DescribeStacks action.
cloudformation:UpdateStack.Title: UpdateStack

cloudformation:ValidateTemplate.Description: Validates a specified template. AWS CloudFormation first checks if the template is valid JSON. If it isn't, AWS CloudFormation checks if the template is valid YAML. If both these checks fail, AWS CloudFormation returns a template validation error.
cloudformation:ValidateTemplate.Title: ValidateTemplate

cloudfront:CreateCloudFrontOriginAccessI.Description: Creates a new origin access identity. If you're using Amazon S3 for your origin, you can use an origin access identity to require users to access your content using a CloudFront URL instead of the Amazon S3 URL. For more information about how to use origin access identities, see Serving Private Content through CloudFront in the Amazon CloudFront Developer Guide.
cloudfront:CreateCloudFrontOriginAccessI.Title: CreateCloudFrontOriginAccessIdentity

cloudfront:CreateDistribution.Description: Creates a new web distribution. Send a POST request to the /CloudFront API version/distribution/distribution ID resource.
cloudfront:CreateDistribution.Title: CreateDistribution

cloudfront:CreateStreamingDistribution.Description: Creates a new RMTP distribution. An RTMP distribution is similar to a web distribution, but an RTMP distribution streams media files using the Adobe Real-Time Messaging Protocol (RTMP) instead of serving files using HTTP.
cloudfront:CreateStreamingDistribution.Title: CreateStreamingDistribution

cloudfront:DeleteStreamingDistribution.Description: Delete a streaming distribution. To delete an RTMP distribution using the CloudFront API, perform the following steps.
cloudfront:DeleteStreamingDistribution.Title: DeleteStreamingDistribution

cloudfront:GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIden.Description: Get the information about an origin access identity.
cloudfront:GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIden.Title: GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIdentity

cloudfront:GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIden.Description: Get the configuration information about an origin access identity.
cloudfront:GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIden.Title: GetCloudFrontOriginAccessIdentityConfig

cloudfront:GetDistribution.Description: Get the information about a distribution.
cloudfront:GetDistribution.Title: GetDistribution

cloudfront:GetDistributionConfig.Description: Get the configuration information about a distribution.
cloudfront:GetDistributionConfig.Title: GetDistributionConfig

cloudfront:GetInvalidation.Description: Get the information about an invalidation.
cloudfront:GetInvalidation.Title: GetInvalidation

cloudfront:GetStreamingDistribution.Description: Gets information about a specified RTMP distribution, including the distribution configuration.
cloudfront:GetStreamingDistribution.Title: GetStreamingDistribution

cloudfront:GetStreamingDistributionConfi.Description: Get the configuration information about a streaming distribution.
cloudfront:GetStreamingDistributionConfi.Title: GetStreamingDistributionConfig

cloudfront:ListDistributionsByWebACLId.Description: List the distributions that are associated with a specified AWS WAF web ACL.
cloudfront:ListDistributionsByWebACLId.Title: ListDistributionsByWebACLId

cloudfront:UpdateDistribution.Description: Updates the configuration for a web distribution. Perform the following steps.
cloudfront:UpdateDistribution.Title: UpdateDistribution

cloudsearch:BuildSuggesters.Description: Indexes the search suggestions. For more information, see Configuring Suggesters in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:BuildSuggesters.Title: BuildSuggesters

cloudsearch:CreateDomain.Description: Creates a new search domain. For more information, see Creating a Search Domain in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:CreateDomain.Title: CreateDomain

cloudsearch:DefineAnalysisScheme.Description: Configures an analysis scheme that can be applied to a text or text-array field to define language-specific text processing options. For more information, see Configuring Analysis Schemes in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DefineAnalysisScheme.Title: DefineAnalysisScheme

cloudsearch:DefineExpression.Description: Configures an Expression for the search domain. Used to create new expressions and modify existing ones. If the expression exists, the new configuration replaces the old one. For more information, see Configuring Expressions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DefineExpression.Title: DefineExpression

cloudsearch:DefineIndexField.Description: Configures an IndexField for the search domain. Used to create new fields and modify existing ones. You must specify the name of the domain you are configuring and an index field configuration. The index field configuration specifies a unique name, the index field type, and the options you want to configure for the field. The options you can specify depend on the IndexFieldType . If the field exists, the new configuration replaces the old one. For more information, see Configuring Index Fields in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DefineIndexField.Title: DefineIndexField

cloudsearch:DefineSuggester.Description: Configures a suggester for a domain. A suggester enables you to display possible matches before users finish typing their queries. When you configure a suggester, you must specify the name of the text field you want to search for possible matches and a unique name for the suggester. For more information, see Getting Search Suggestions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DefineSuggester.Title: DefineSuggester

cloudsearch:DeleteAnalysisScheme.Description: Deletes an analysis scheme. For more information, see Configuring Analysis Schemes in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DeleteAnalysisScheme.Title: DeleteAnalysisScheme

cloudsearch:DeleteDomain.Description: Permanently deletes a search domain and all of its data. Once a domain has been deleted, it cannot be recovered. For more information, see Deleting a Search Domain in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DeleteDomain.Title: DeleteDomain

cloudsearch:DeleteExpression.Description: Removes an Expression from the search domain. For more information, see Configuring Expressions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DeleteExpression.Title: DeleteExpression

cloudsearch:DeleteIndexField.Description: Removes an IndexField from the search domain. For more information, see Configuring Index Fields in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DeleteIndexField.Title: DeleteIndexField

cloudsearch:DeleteSuggester.Description: Deletes a suggester. For more information, see Getting Search Suggestions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DeleteSuggester.Title: DeleteSuggester

cloudsearch:DescribeAnalysisSchemes.Description: Gets the analysis schemes configured for a domain. An analysis scheme defines language-specific text processing options for a text field. Can be limited to specific analysis schemes by name. By default, shows all analysis schemes and includes any pending changes to the configuration. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Configuring Analysis Schemes in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeAnalysisSchemes.Title: DescribeAnalysisSchemes

cloudsearch:DescribeAvailabilityOptions.Description: Gets the availability options configured for a domain. By default, shows the configuration with any pending changes. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Configuring Availability Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeAvailabilityOptions.Title: DescribeAvailabilityOptions

cloudsearch:DescribeDomains.Description: Gets information about the search domains owned by this account. Can be limited to specific domains. Shows all domains by default. To get the number of searchable documents in a domain, use the console or submit a matchall request to your domain's search endpoint: q=matchall&q.parser=structured&size=0. For more information, see Getting Information about a Search Domain in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeDomains.Title: DescribeDomains

cloudsearch:DescribeExpressions.Description: Gets the expressions configured for the search domain. Can be limited to specific expressions by name. By default, shows all expressions and includes any pending changes to the configuration. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Configuring Expressions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeExpressions.Title: DescribeExpressions

cloudsearch:DescribeIndexFields.Description: Gets information about the index fields configured for the search domain. Can be limited to specific fields by name. By default, shows all fields and includes any pending changes to the configuration. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Getting Domain Information in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeIndexFields.Title: DescribeIndexFields

cloudsearch:DescribeScalingParameters.Description: Gets the scaling parameters configured for a domain. A domain's scaling parameters specify the desired search instance type and replication count. For more information, see Configuring Scaling Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeScalingParameters.Title: DescribeScalingParameters

cloudsearch:DescribeServiceAccessPolicie.Description: Gets information about the access policies that control access to the domain's document and search endpoints. By default, shows the configuration with any pending changes. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Configuring Access for a Search Domain in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeServiceAccessPolicie.Title: DescribeServiceAccessPolicies

cloudsearch:DescribeSuggesters.Description: Gets the suggesters configured for a domain. A suggester enables you to display possible matches before users finish typing their queries. Can be limited to specific suggesters by name. By default, shows all suggesters and includes any pending changes to the configuration. Set the Deployed option to true to show the active configuration and exclude pending changes. For more information, see Getting Search Suggestions in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:DescribeSuggesters.Title: DescribeSuggesters

cloudsearch:IndexDocuments.Description: Tells the search domain to start indexing its documents using the latest indexing options. This operation must be invoked to activate options whose OptionStatus is RequiresIndexDocuments.
cloudsearch:IndexDocuments.Title: IndexDocuments

cloudsearch:ListDomainNames.Description: Lists all search domains owned by an account.
cloudsearch:ListDomainNames.Title: ListDomainNames

cloudsearch:UpdateAvailabilityOptions.Description: Configures the availability options for a domain. Enabling the Multi-AZ option expands an Amazon CloudSearch domain to an additional Availability Zone in the same Region to increase fault tolerance in the event of a service disruption. Changes to the Multi-AZ option can take about half an hour to become active. For more information, see Configuring Availability Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:UpdateAvailabilityOptions.Title: UpdateAvailabilityOptions

cloudsearch:UpdateScalingParameters.Description: Configures scaling parameters for a domain. A domain's scaling parameters specify the desired search instance type and replication count. Amazon CloudSearch will still automatically scale your domain based on the volume of data and traffic, but not below the desired instance type and replication count. If the Multi-AZ option is enabled, these values control the resources used per Availability Zone. For more information, see Configuring Scaling Options in the Amazon CloudSearch Developer Guide.
cloudsearch:UpdateScalingParameters.Title: UpdateScalingParameters

cloudsearch:UpdateServiceAccessPolicies.Description: Configures the access rules that control access to the domain's document and search endpoints. For more information, see Configuring Access for an Amazon CloudSearch Domain.
cloudsearch:UpdateServiceAccessPolicies.Title: UpdateServiceAccessPolicies

cloudsearch:document.Description: You use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) access policies to control access to the Amazon CloudSearch configuration service and each search domain's document, search, and suggest services. An IAM access policy is a JSON document that explicitly lists permissions that define what actions people or processes are allowed to perform. For an introduction to IAM access policies, see Overview of AWS IAM Policies.
cloudsearch:document.Title: Configuring Access for Amazon CloudSearch

cloudsearch:search.Description: You use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) access policies to control access to the Amazon CloudSearch configuration service and each search domain's document, search, and suggest services. An IAM access policy is a JSON document that explicitly lists permissions that define what actions people or processes are allowed to perform. For an introduction to IAM access policies, see Overview of AWS IAM Policies.
cloudsearch:search.Title: Configuring Access for Amazon CloudSearch

cloudsearch:suggest.Description: You use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) access policies to control access to the Amazon CloudSearch configuration service and each search domain's document, search, and suggest services. An IAM access policy is a JSON document that explicitly lists permissions that define what actions people or processes are allowed to perform. For an introduction to IAM access policies, see Overview of AWS IAM Policies.
cloudsearch:suggest.Title: Configuring Access for Amazon CloudSearch

cloudtrail:AddTags.Description: Adds one or more tags to a trail, up to a limit of 50. Tags must be unique per trail. Overwrites an existing tag's value when a new value is specified for an existing tag key. If you specify a key without a value, the tag will be created with the specified key and a value of null. You can tag a trail that applies to all regions only from the region in which the trail was created (that is, from its home region).
cloudtrail:AddTags.Title: AddTags

cloudtrail:CreateTrail.Description: Creates a trail that specifies the settings for delivery of log data to an Amazon S3 bucket. A maximum of five trails can exist in a region, irrespective of the region in which they were created.
cloudtrail:CreateTrail.Title: CreateTrail

cloudtrail:DeleteTrail.Description: Deletes a trail. This operation must be called from the region in which the trail was created. DeleteTrail cannot be called on the shadow trails (replicated trails in other regions) of a trail that is enabled in all regions.
cloudtrail:DeleteTrail.Title: DeleteTrail

cloudtrail:DescribeTrails.Description: Retrieves settings for the trail associated with the current region for your account.
cloudtrail:DescribeTrails.Title: DescribeTrails

cloudtrail:GetEventSelectors.Description: Describes the settings for the event selectors that you configured for your trail. The information returned for your event selectors includes the following:
cloudtrail:GetEventSelectors.Title: GetEventSelectors

cloudtrail:GetTrailStatus.Description: Returns a JSON-formatted list of information about the specified trail. Fields include information on delivery errors, Amazon SNS and Amazon S3 errors, and start and stop logging times for each trail. This operation returns trail status from a single region. To return trail status from all regions, you must call the operation on each region.
cloudtrail:GetTrailStatus.Title: GetTrailStatus

cloudtrail:ListPublicKeys.Description: Returns all public keys whose private keys were used to sign the digest files within the specified time range. The public key is needed to validate digest files that were signed with its corresponding private key.
cloudtrail:ListPublicKeys.Title: ListPublicKeys

cloudtrail:ListTags.Description: Lists the tags for the trail in the current region.
cloudtrail:ListTags.Title: ListTags

cloudtrail:LookupEvents.Description: Looks up API activity events captured by CloudTrail that create, update, or delete resources in your account. Events for a region can be looked up for the times in which you had CloudTrail turned on in that region during the last seven days. Lookup supports the following attributes:
cloudtrail:LookupEvents.Title: LookupEvents

cloudtrail:PutEventSelectors.Description: Configures an event selector for your trail. Use event selectors to specify whether you want your trail to log management and/or data events. When an event occurs in your account, CloudTrail evaluates the event selectors in all trails. For each trail, if the event matches any event selector, the trail processes and logs the event. If the event doesn't match any event selector, the trail doesn't log the event.
cloudtrail:PutEventSelectors.Title: PutEventSelectors

cloudtrail:RemoveTags.Description: Removes the specified tags from a trail.
cloudtrail:RemoveTags.Title: RemoveTags

cloudtrail:StartLogging.Description: Starts the recording of AWS API calls and log file delivery for a trail. For a trail that is enabled in all regions, this operation must be called from the region in which the trail was created. This operation cannot be called on the shadow trails (replicated trails in other regions) of a trail that is enabled in all regions.
cloudtrail:StartLogging.Title: StartLogging

cloudtrail:StopLogging.Description: Suspends the recording of AWS API calls and log file delivery for the specified trail. Under most circumstances, there is no need to use this action. You can update a trail without stopping it first. This action is the only way to stop recording. For a trail enabled in all regions, this operation must be called from the region in which the trail was created, or an InvalidHomeRegionException will occur. This operation cannot be called on the shadow trails (replicated trails in other regions) of a trail enabled in all regions.
cloudtrail:StopLogging.Title: StopLogging

cloudtrail:UpdateTrail.Description: Updates the settings that specify delivery of log files. Changes to a trail do not require stopping the CloudTrail service. Use this action to designate an existing bucket for log delivery. If the existing bucket has previously been a target for CloudTrail log files, an IAM policy exists for the bucket. UpdateTrail must be called from the region in which the trail was created; otherwise, an InvalidHomeRegionException is thrown.
cloudtrail:UpdateTrail.Title: UpdateTrail

cloudwatch:DeleteAlarms.Description: Deletes the specified alarms. In the event of an error, no alarms are deleted.
cloudwatch:DeleteAlarms.Title: DeleteAlarms

cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmHistory.Description: Retrieves the history for the specified alarm. You can filter the results by date range or item type. If an alarm name is not specified, the histories for all alarms are returned.
cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmHistory.Title: DescribeAlarmHistory

cloudwatch:DescribeAlarms.Description: Retrieves the specified alarms. If no alarms are specified, all alarms are returned. Alarms can be retrieved by using only a prefix for the alarm name, the alarm state, or a prefix for any action.
cloudwatch:DescribeAlarms.Title: DescribeAlarms

cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmsForMetric.Description: Retrieves the alarms for the specified metric. To filter the results, specify a statistic, period, or unit.
cloudwatch:DescribeAlarmsForMetric.Title: DescribeAlarmsForMetric

cloudwatch:DisableAlarmActions.Description: Disables the actions for the specified alarms. When an alarm's actions are disabled, the alarm actions do not execute when the alarm state changes.
cloudwatch:DisableAlarmActions.Title: DisableAlarmActions

cloudwatch:EnableAlarmActions.Description: Enables the actions for the specified alarms.
cloudwatch:EnableAlarmActions.Title: EnableAlarmActions

cloudwatch:GetMetricData.Description: When you are setting up Access Control and writing permissions policies that you can attach to an IAM identity (identity-based policies), you can use the following table as a reference. The table lists each CloudWatch API operation and the corresponding actions for which you can grant permissions to perform the action. You specify the actions in the policy's Action field, and you specify a wildcard character (*) as the resource value in the policy's Resource field.
cloudwatch:GetMetricData.Title: Amazon CloudWatch Permissions Reference

cloudwatch:GetMetricStatistics.Description: Gets statistics for the specified metric.
cloudwatch:GetMetricStatistics.Title: GetMetricStatistics

cloudwatch:ListMetrics.Description: List the specified metrics. You can use the returned metrics with GetMetricStatistics to obtain statistical data.
cloudwatch:ListMetrics.Title: ListMetrics

cloudwatch:PutMetricAlarm.Description: Creates or updates an alarm and associates it with the specified metric. Optionally, this operation can associate one or more Amazon SNS resources with the alarm.
cloudwatch:PutMetricAlarm.Title: PutMetricAlarm

cloudwatch:PutMetricData.Description: Publishes metric data points to Amazon CloudWatch. CloudWatch associates the data points with the specified metric. If the specified metric does not exist, CloudWatch creates the metric. When CloudWatch creates a metric, it can take up to fifteen minutes for the metric to appear in calls to ListMetrics.
cloudwatch:PutMetricData.Title: PutMetricData

cloudwatch:SetAlarmState.Description: Temporarily sets the state of an alarm for testing purposes. When the updated state differs from the previous value, the action configured for the appropriate state is invoked. For example, if your alarm is configured to send an Amazon SNS message when an alarm is triggered, temporarily changing the alarm state to ALARM sends an SNS message. The alarm returns to its actual state (often within seconds). Because the alarm state change happens quickly, it is typically only visible in the alarm's History tab in the Amazon CloudWatch console or through DescribeAlarmHistory.
cloudwatch:SetAlarmState.Title: SetAlarmState

codebuild:ListBuilds.Description: Gets a list of build IDs, with each build ID representing a single build.
codebuild:ListBuilds.Title: ListBuilds

codebuild:ListBuildsForProject.Description: Gets a list of build IDs for the specified build project, with each build ID representing a single build.
codebuild:ListBuildsForProject.Title: ListBuildsForProject

codebuild:ListConnectedOAuthAccounts.Description: This topic provides examples of identity-based policies that demonstrate how an account administrator can attach permissions policies to IAM identities (that is, users, groups, and roles) and thereby grant permissions to perform operations on AWS CodeBuild resources.
codebuild:ListConnectedOAuthAccounts.Title:
Using
                        Identity-Based Policies (IAM Policies) for AWS CodeBuild

codebuild:ListProjects.Description: Gets a list of build project names, with each build project name representing a single build project.
codebuild:ListProjects.Title: ListProjects

codebuild:ListRepositories.Description: This topic provides examples of identity-based policies that demonstrate how an account administrator can attach permissions policies to IAM identities (that is, users, groups, and roles) and thereby grant permissions to perform operations on AWS CodeBuild resources.
codebuild:ListRepositories.Title:
Using
                        Identity-Based Policies (IAM Policies) for AWS CodeBuild

codebuild:PersistOAuthToken.Description: This topic provides examples of identity-based policies that demonstrate how an account administrator can attach permissions policies to IAM identities (that is, users, groups, and roles) and thereby grant permissions to perform operations on AWS CodeBuild resources.
codebuild:PersistOAuthToken.Title:
Using
                        Identity-Based Policies (IAM Policies) for AWS CodeBuild

codebuild:StopBuild.Description: Attempts to stop running a build.
codebuild:StopBuild.Title: StopBuild

codebuild:UpdateProject.Description: Changes the settings of a build project.
codebuild:UpdateProject.Title: UpdateProject

codecommit:BatchGetRepositories.Description: Returns information about one or more repositories.
codecommit:BatchGetRepositories.Title: BatchGetRepositories

codecommit:CreateBranch.Description: Creates a new branch in a repository and points the branch to a commit.
codecommit:CreateBranch.Title: CreateBranch

codecommit:DeleteBranch.Description: Deletes a branch from a repository, unless that branch is the default branch for the repository.
codecommit:DeleteBranch.Title: DeleteBranch

codecommit:DeleteRepository.Description: Deletes a repository. If a specified repository was already deleted, a null repository ID will be returned.
codecommit:DeleteRepository.Title: DeleteRepository

codecommit:GetBlob.Description: Returns the base-64 encoded content of an individual blob within a repository.
codecommit:GetBlob.Title: GetBlob

codecommit:GetBranch.Description: Returns information about a repository branch, including its name and the last commit ID.
codecommit:GetBranch.Title: GetBranch

codecommit:GetCommit.Description: Returns information about a commit, including commit message and committer information.
codecommit:GetCommit.Title: GetCommit

codecommit:GetDifferences.Description: Returns information about the differences in a valid commit specifier (such as a branch, tag, HEAD, commit ID or other fully qualified reference). Results can be limited to a specified path.
codecommit:GetDifferences.Title: GetDifferences

codecommit:GetRepositoryTriggers.Description: Gets information about triggers configured for a repository.
codecommit:GetRepositoryTriggers.Title: GetRepositoryTriggers

codecommit:ListBranches.Description: Gets information about one or more branches in a repository.
codecommit:ListBranches.Title: ListBranches

codecommit:ListRepositories.Description: Gets information about one or more repositories.
codecommit:ListRepositories.Title: ListRepositories

codecommit:PutRepositoryTriggers.Description: Replaces all triggers for a repository. This can be used to create or delete triggers.
codecommit:PutRepositoryTriggers.Title: PutRepositoryTriggers

codecommit:TestRepositoryTriggers.Description: Tests the functionality of repository triggers by sending information to the trigger target. If real data is available in the repository, the test will send data from the last commit. If no data is available, sample data will be generated.
codecommit:TestRepositoryTriggers.Title: TestRepositoryTriggers

codecommit:UpdateDefaultBranch.Description: Sets or changes the default branch name for the specified repository.
codecommit:UpdateDefaultBranch.Title: UpdateDefaultBranch

codecommit:UpdateRepositoryDescription.Description: Sets or changes the comment or description for a repository.
codecommit:UpdateRepositoryDescription.Title: UpdateRepositoryDescription

codecommit:UpdateRepositoryName.Description: Renames a repository. The repository name must be unique across the calling AWS account. In addition, repository names are limited to 100 alphanumeric, dash, and underscore characters, and cannot include certain characters. The suffix ".git" is prohibited. For a full description of the limits on repository names, see Limits in the AWS CodeCommit User Guide.
codecommit:UpdateRepositoryName.Title: UpdateRepositoryName

codedeploy:BatchGetApplicationRevisions.Description: Gets information about one or more application revisions.
codedeploy:BatchGetApplicationRevisions.Title: BatchGetApplicationRevisions

codedeploy:BatchGetApplications.Description: Gets information about one or more applications.
codedeploy:BatchGetApplications.Title: BatchGetApplications

codedeploy:BatchGetDeploymentGroups.Description: Gets information about one or more deployment groups.
codedeploy:BatchGetDeploymentGroups.Title: BatchGetDeploymentGroups

codedeploy:BatchGetDeploymentInstances.Description: Gets information about one or more instance that are part of a deployment group.
codedeploy:BatchGetDeploymentInstances.Title: BatchGetDeploymentInstances

codedeploy:BatchGetDeployments.Description: Gets information about one or more deployments.
codedeploy:BatchGetDeployments.Title: BatchGetDeployments

codedeploy:BatchGetOnPremisesInstances.Description: Gets information about one or more on-premises instances.
codedeploy:BatchGetOnPremisesInstances.Title: BatchGetOnPremisesInstances

codedeploy:CreateDeployment.Description: Deploys an application revision through the specified deployment group.
codedeploy:CreateDeployment.Title: CreateDeployment

codedeploy:CreateDeploymentGroup.Description: Creates a deployment group to which application revisions will be deployed.
codedeploy:CreateDeploymentGroup.Title: CreateDeploymentGroup

codedeploy:GetApplicationRevision.Description: Gets information about an application revision.
codedeploy:GetApplicationRevision.Title: GetApplicationRevision

codedeploy:GetDeploymentConfig.Description: Gets information about a deployment configuration.
codedeploy:GetDeploymentConfig.Title: GetDeploymentConfig

codedeploy:GetDeploymentGroup.Description: Gets information about a deployment group.
codedeploy:GetDeploymentGroup.Title: GetDeploymentGroup

codedeploy:GetDeploymentInstance.Description: Gets information about an instance as part of a deployment.
codedeploy:GetDeploymentInstance.Title: GetDeploymentInstance

codedeploy:GetOnPremisesInstance.Description: Gets information about an on-premises instance.
codedeploy:GetOnPremisesInstance.Title: GetOnPremisesInstance

codedeploy:ListApplicationRevisions.Description: Lists information about revisions for an application.
codedeploy:ListApplicationRevisions.Title: ListApplicationRevisions

codedeploy:ListApplications.Description: Lists the applications registered with the applicable IAM user or AWS account.
codedeploy:ListApplications.Title: ListApplications

codedeploy:ListDeploymentConfigs.Description: Lists the deployment configurations with the applicable IAM user or AWS account.
codedeploy:ListDeploymentConfigs.Title: ListDeploymentConfigs

codedeploy:ListDeploymentGroups.Description: Lists the deployment groups for an application registered with the applicable IAM user or AWS account.
codedeploy:ListDeploymentGroups.Title: ListDeploymentGroups

codedeploy:ListDeploymentInstances.Description: Lists the instance for a deployment associated with the applicable IAM user or AWS account.
codedeploy:ListDeploymentInstances.Title: ListDeploymentInstances

codedeploy:ListDeployments.Description: Lists the deployments in a deployment group for an application registered with the applicable IAM user or AWS account.
codedeploy:ListDeployments.Title: ListDeployments

codedeploy:ListOnPremisesInstances.Description: Gets a list of names for one or more on-premises instances.
codedeploy:ListOnPremisesInstances.Title: ListOnPremisesInstances

codedeploy:RegisterApplicationRevision.Description: Registers with AWS CodeDeploy a revision for the specified application.
codedeploy:RegisterApplicationRevision.Title: RegisterApplicationRevision

codedeploy:RemoveTagsFromOnPremisesInsta.Description: Removes one or more tags from one or more on-premises instances.
codedeploy:RemoveTagsFromOnPremisesInsta.Title: RemoveTagsFromOnPremisesInstances

codedeploy:StopDeployment.Description: Attempts to stop an ongoing deployment.
codedeploy:StopDeployment.Title: StopDeployment

codedeploy:UpdateApplication.Description: Changes the name of an application.
codedeploy:UpdateApplication.Title: UpdateApplication

codedeploy:UpdateDeploymentGroup.Description: Changes information about a deployment group.
codedeploy:UpdateDeploymentGroup.Title: UpdateDeploymentGroup

codepipeline:AcknowledgeJob.Description: Returns information about a specified job and whether that job has been received by the job worker. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:AcknowledgeJob.Title: AcknowledgeJob

codepipeline:AcknowledgeThirdPartyJob.Description: Confirms a job worker has received the specified job. Only used for partner actions.
codepipeline:AcknowledgeThirdPartyJob.Title: AcknowledgeThirdPartyJob

codepipeline:CreateCustomActionType.Description: Creates a new custom action that can be used in all pipelines associated with the AWS account. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:CreateCustomActionType.Title: CreateCustomActionType

codepipeline:DeleteCustomActionType.Description: Marks a custom action as deleted. PollForJobs for the custom action will fail after the action is marked for deletion. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:DeleteCustomActionType.Title: DeleteCustomActionType

codepipeline:DisableStageTransition.Description: Prevents artifacts in a pipeline from transitioning to the next stage in the pipeline.
codepipeline:DisableStageTransition.Title: DisableStageTransition

codepipeline:EnableStageTransition.Description: Enables artifacts in a pipeline to transition to a stage in a pipeline.
codepipeline:EnableStageTransition.Title: EnableStageTransition

codepipeline:GetJobDetails.Description: Returns information about a job. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:GetJobDetails.Title: GetJobDetails

codepipeline:GetPipeline.Description: Returns the metadata, structure, stages, and actions of a pipeline. Can be used to return the entire structure of a pipeline in JSON format, which can then be modified and used to update the pipeline structure with UpdatePipeline.
codepipeline:GetPipeline.Title: GetPipeline

codepipeline:GetPipelineExecution.Description: Returns information about an execution of a pipeline, including details about artifacts, the pipeline execution ID, and the name, version, and status of the pipeline.
codepipeline:GetPipelineExecution.Title: GetPipelineExecution

codepipeline:GetPipelineState.Description: Returns information about the state of a pipeline, including the stages and actions.
codepipeline:GetPipelineState.Title: GetPipelineState

codepipeline:GetThirdPartyJobDetails.Description: Requests the details of a job for a third party action. Only used for partner actions.
codepipeline:GetThirdPartyJobDetails.Title: GetThirdPartyJobDetails

codepipeline:ListActionTypes.Description: Gets a summary of all AWS CodePipeline action types associated with your account.
codepipeline:ListActionTypes.Title: ListActionTypes

codepipeline:ListPipelineExecutions.Description: Gets a summary of the most recent executions for a pipeline.
codepipeline:ListPipelineExecutions.Title: ListPipelineExecutions

codepipeline:ListPipelines.Description: Gets a summary of all of the pipelines associated with your account.
codepipeline:ListPipelines.Title: ListPipelines

codepipeline:PollForJobs.Description: Returns information about any jobs for AWS CodePipeline to act upon.
codepipeline:PollForJobs.Title: PollForJobs

codepipeline:PollForThirdPartyJobs.Description: Determines whether there are any third party jobs for a job worker to act on. Only used for partner actions.
codepipeline:PollForThirdPartyJobs.Title: PollForThirdPartyJobs

codepipeline:PutActionRevision.Description: Provides information to AWS CodePipeline about new revisions to a source.
codepipeline:PutActionRevision.Title: PutActionRevision

codepipeline:PutApprovalResult.Description: Provides the response to a manual approval request to AWS CodePipeline. Valid responses include Approved and Rejected.
codepipeline:PutApprovalResult.Title: PutApprovalResult

codepipeline:PutJobFailureResult.Description: Represents the failure of a job as returned to the pipeline by a job worker. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:PutJobFailureResult.Title: PutJobFailureResult

codepipeline:PutJobSuccessResult.Description: Represents the success of a job as returned to the pipeline by a job worker. Only used for custom actions.
codepipeline:PutJobSuccessResult.Title: PutJobSuccessResult

codepipeline:PutThirdPartyJobFailureResu.Description: Represents the failure of a third party job as returned to the pipeline by a job worker. Only used for partner actions.
codepipeline:PutThirdPartyJobFailureResu.Title: PutThirdPartyJobFailureResult

codepipeline:PutThirdPartyJobSuccessResu.Description: Represents the success of a third party job as returned to the pipeline by a job worker. Only used for partner actions.
codepipeline:PutThirdPartyJobSuccessResu.Title: PutThirdPartyJobSuccessResult

codepipeline:RetryStageExecution.Description: Resumes the pipeline execution by retrying the last failed actions in a stage.
codepipeline:RetryStageExecution.Title: RetryStageExecution

codepipeline:StartPipelineExecution.Description: Starts the specified pipeline. Specifically, it begins processing the latest commit to the source location specified as part of the pipeline.
codepipeline:StartPipelineExecution.Title: StartPipelineExecution

codepipeline:UpdatePipeline.Description: Updates a specified pipeline with edits or changes to its structure. Use a JSON file with the pipeline structure in conjunction with UpdatePipeline to provide the full structure of the pipeline. Updating the pipeline increases the version number of the pipeline by 1.
codepipeline:UpdatePipeline.Title: UpdatePipeline

codestar:AssociateTeamMember.Description: Adds an IAM user to the team for an AWS CodeStar project.
codestar:AssociateTeamMember.Title: AssociateTeamMember

codestar:CreateProject.Description: Reserved for future use. To create a project, use the AWS CodeStar console.
codestar:CreateProject.Title: CreateProject

codestar:CreateUserProfile.Description: Creates a profile for a user that includes user preferences, such as the display name and email address assocciated with the user, in AWS CodeStar. The user profile is not project-specific. Information in the user profile is displayed wherever the user's information appears to other users in AWS CodeStar.
codestar:CreateUserProfile.Title: CreateUserProfile

codestar:DeleteProject.Description: Deletes a project, including project resources. Does not delete users associated with the project, but does delete the IAM roles that allowed access to the project.
codestar:DeleteProject.Title: DeleteProject

codestar:DeleteUserProfile.Description: Deletes a user profile in AWS CodeStar, including all personal preference data associated with that profile, such as display name and email address. It does not delete the history of that user, for example the history of commits made by that user.
codestar:DeleteUserProfile.Title: DeleteUserProfile

codestar:DescribeProject.Description: Describes a project and its resources.
codestar:DescribeProject.Title: DescribeProject

codestar:DescribeUserProfile.Description: Describes a user in AWS CodeStar and the user attributes across all projects.
codestar:DescribeUserProfile.Title: DescribeUserProfile

codestar:DisassociateTeamMember.Description: Removes a user from a project. Removing a user from a project also removes the IAM policies from that user that allowed access to the project and its resources. Disassociating a team member does not remove that user's profile from AWS CodeStar. It does not remove the user from IAM.
codestar:DisassociateTeamMember.Title: DisassociateTeamMember

codestar:ListProjects.Description: Lists all projects in AWS CodeStar associated with your AWS account.
codestar:ListProjects.Title: ListProjects

codestar:ListResources.Description: Lists resources associated with a project in AWS CodeStar.
codestar:ListResources.Title: ListResources

codestar:ListTeamMembers.Description: Lists all team members associated with a project.
codestar:ListTeamMembers.Title: ListTeamMembers

codestar:ListUserProfiles.Description: Lists all the user profiles configured for your AWS account in AWS CodeStar.
codestar:ListUserProfiles.Title: ListUserProfiles

codestar:UpdateProject.Description: Updates a project in AWS CodeStar.
codestar:UpdateProject.Title: UpdateProject

codestar:UpdateTeamMember.Description: Updates a team member's attributes in an AWS CodeStar project. For example, you can change a team member's role in the project, or change whether they have remote access to project resources.
codestar:UpdateTeamMember.Title: UpdateTeamMember

codestar:UpdateUserProfile.Description: Updates a user's profile in AWS CodeStar. The user profile is not project-specific. Information in the user profile is displayed wherever the user's information appears to other users in AWS CodeStar.
codestar:UpdateUserProfile.Title: UpdateUserProfile

cognito-identity:CreateIdentityPool.Description: Creates a new identity pool. The identity pool is a store of user identity information that is specific to your AWS account. The limit on identity pools is 60 per account. The keys for SupportedLoginProviders are as follows:
cognito-identity:CreateIdentityPool.Title: CreateIdentityPool

cognito-identity:DeleteIdentities.Description: Deletes identities from an identity pool. You can specify a list of 1-60 identities that you want to delete.
cognito-identity:DeleteIdentities.Title: DeleteIdentities

cognito-identity:DeleteIdentityPool.Description: Deletes an identity pool. Once a pool is deleted, users will not be able to authenticate with the pool.
cognito-identity:DeleteIdentityPool.Title: DeleteIdentityPool

cognito-identity:DescribeIdentity.Description: Returns metadata related to the given identity, including when the identity was created and any associated linked logins.
cognito-identity:DescribeIdentity.Title: DescribeIdentity

cognito-identity:DescribeIdentityPool.Description: Gets details about a particular identity pool, including the pool name, ID description, creation date, and current number of users.
cognito-identity:DescribeIdentityPool.Title: DescribeIdentityPool

cognito-identity:GetIdentityPoolRoles.Description: Gets the roles for an identity pool.
cognito-identity:GetIdentityPoolRoles.Title: GetIdentityPoolRoles

cognito-identity:GetOpenIdTokenForDevelo.Description: Registers (or retrieves) a Cognito IdentityId and an OpenID Connect token for a user authenticated by your backend authentication process. Supplying multiple logins will create an implicit linked account. You can only specify one developer provider as part of the Logins map, which is linked to the identity pool. The developer provider is the "domain" by which Cognito will refer to your users.
cognito-identity:GetOpenIdTokenForDevelo.Title: GetOpenIdTokenForDeveloperIdentity

cognito-identity:ListIdentities.Description: Lists the identities in an identity pool.
cognito-identity:ListIdentities.Title: ListIdentities

cognito-identity:ListIdentityPools.Description: Lists all of the Cognito identity pools registered for your account.
cognito-identity:ListIdentityPools.Title: ListIdentityPools

cognito-identity:LookupDeveloperIdentity.Description: Retrieves the IdentityID associated with a DeveloperUserIdentifier or the list of DeveloperUserIdentifier values associated with an IdentityId for an existing identity. Either IdentityID or DeveloperUserIdentifier must not be null. If you supply only one of these values, the other value will be searched in the database and returned as a part of the response. If you supply both, DeveloperUserIdentifier will be matched against IdentityID. If the values are verified against the database, the response returns both values and is the same as the request. Otherwise a ResourceConflictException is thrown.
cognito-identity:LookupDeveloperIdentity.Title: LookupDeveloperIdentity

cognito-identity:MergeDeveloperIdentitie.Description: Merges two users having different IdentityIds, existing in the same identity pool, and identified by the same developer provider. You can use this action to request that discrete users be merged and identified as a single user in the Cognito environment.
