ec2:DeleteVpnGateway.Description: Deletes the specified virtual private gateway. We recommend that before you delete a virtual private gateway, you detach it from the VPC and delete the VPN connection. Note that you don't need to delete the virtual private gateway if you plan to delete and recreate the VPN connection between your VPC and your network.
ec2:DeleteVpnGateway.Title: DeleteVpnGateway

ec2:DeregisterImage.Description: Deregisters the specified AMI. After you deregister an AMI, it can't be used to launch new instances; however, it doesn't affect any instances that you've already launched from the AMI. You'll continue to incur usage costs for those instances until you terminate them.
ec2:DeregisterImage.Title: DeregisterImage

ec2:DescribeAccountAttributes.Description: Describes attributes of your AWS account. The following are the supported account attributes:
ec2:DescribeAccountAttributes.Title: DescribeAccountAttributes

ec2:DescribeAddresses.Description: Describes one or more of your Elastic IP addresses.
ec2:DescribeAddresses.Title: DescribeAddresses

ec2:DescribeAvailabilityZones.Description: Describes one or more of the Availability Zones that are available to you. The results include zones only for the region you're currently using. If there is an event impacting an Availability Zone, you can use this request to view the state and any provided message for that Availability Zone.
ec2:DescribeAvailabilityZones.Title: DescribeAvailabilityZones

ec2:DescribeBundleTasks.Description: Describes one or more of your bundling tasks.
ec2:DescribeBundleTasks.Title: DescribeBundleTasks

ec2:DescribeClassicLinkInstances.Description: Describes one or more of your linked EC2-Classic instances. This request only returns information about EC2-Classic instances linked to a VPC through ClassicLink; you cannot use this request to return information about other instances.
ec2:DescribeClassicLinkInstances.Title: DescribeClassicLinkInstances

ec2:DescribeConversionTasks.Description: Describes one or more of your conversion tasks. For more information, see the VM Import/Export User Guide.
ec2:DescribeConversionTasks.Title: DescribeConversionTasks

ec2:DescribeCustomerGateways.Description: Describes one or more of your VPN customer gateways.
ec2:DescribeCustomerGateways.Title: DescribeCustomerGateways

ec2:DescribeDhcpOptions.Description: Describes one or more of your DHCP options sets.
ec2:DescribeDhcpOptions.Title: DescribeDhcpOptions

ec2:DescribeEgressOnlyInternetGateways.Description: Describes one or more of your egress-only Internet gateways.
ec2:DescribeEgressOnlyInternetGateways.Title: DescribeEgressOnlyInternetGateways

ec2:DescribeExportTasks.Description: Describes one or more of your export tasks.
ec2:DescribeExportTasks.Title: DescribeExportTasks

ec2:DescribeFlowLogs.Description: Describes one or more flow logs. To view the information in your flow logs (the log streams for the network interfaces), you must use the CloudWatch Logs console or the CloudWatch Logs API.
ec2:DescribeFlowLogs.Title: DescribeFlowLogs

ec2:DescribeFpgaImages.Description: Describes one or more available Amazon FPGA Images (AFIs). These include public AFIs, private AFIs that you own, and AFIs owned by other AWS accounts for which you have load permissions.
ec2:DescribeFpgaImages.Title: DescribeFpgaImages

ec2:DescribeHostReservationOfferings.Description: Describes the Dedicated Host Reservations that are available to purchase.
ec2:DescribeHostReservationOfferings.Title: DescribeHostReservationOfferings

ec2:DescribeHostReservations.Description: Describes Dedicated Host Reservations which are associated with Dedicated Hosts in your account.
ec2:DescribeHostReservations.Title: DescribeHostReservations

ec2:DescribeHosts.Description: Describes one or more of your Dedicated Hosts.
ec2:DescribeHosts.Title: DescribeHosts

ec2:DescribeIamInstanceProfileAssociatio.Description: Describes your IAM instance profile associations.
ec2:DescribeIamInstanceProfileAssociatio.Title: DescribeIamInstanceProfileAssociations

ec2:DescribeIdFormat.Description: Describes the ID format settings for your resources on a per-region basis, for example, to view which resource types are enabled for longer IDs. This request only returns information about resource types whose ID formats can be modified; it does not return information about other resource types.
ec2:DescribeIdFormat.Title: DescribeIdFormat

ec2:DescribeIdentityIdFormat.Description: Describes the ID format settings for resources for the specified IAM user, IAM role, or root user. For example, you can view the resource types that are enabled for longer IDs. This request only returns information about resource types whose ID formats can be modified; it does not return information about other resource types. For more information, see Resource IDs in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribeIdentityIdFormat.Title: DescribeIdentityIdFormat

ec2:DescribeImageAttribute.Description: Describes the specified attribute of the specified AMI. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:DescribeImageAttribute.Title: DescribeImageAttribute

ec2:DescribeImages.Description: Describes one or more of the images (AMIs, AKIs, and ARIs) available to you. Images available to you include public images, private images that you own, and private images owned by other AWS accounts but for which you have explicit launch permissions.
ec2:DescribeImages.Title: DescribeImages

ec2:DescribeImportImageTasks.Description: Displays details about an import virtual machine or import snapshot tasks that are already created.
ec2:DescribeImportImageTasks.Title: DescribeImportImageTasks

ec2:DescribeInstanceAttribute.Description: Describes the specified attribute of the specified instance. You can specify only one attribute at a time. Valid attribute values are: instanceType | kernel | ramdisk | userData | disableApiTermination | instanceInitiatedShutdownBehavior | rootDeviceName | blockDeviceMapping | productCodes | sourceDestCheck | groupSet | ebsOptimized | sriovNetSupport
ec2:DescribeInstanceAttribute.Title: DescribeInstanceAttribute

ec2:DescribeInstanceStatus.Description: Describes the status of one or more instances. By default, only running instances are described, unless you specifically indicate to return the status of all instances.
ec2:DescribeInstanceStatus.Title: DescribeInstanceStatus

ec2:DescribeInstances.Description: Describes one or more of your instances.
ec2:DescribeInstances.Title: DescribeInstances

ec2:DescribeInternetGateways.Description: Describes one or more of your Internet gateways.
ec2:DescribeInternetGateways.Title: DescribeInternetGateways

ec2:DescribeKeyPairs.Description: Describes one or more of your key pairs.
ec2:DescribeKeyPairs.Title: DescribeKeyPairs

ec2:DescribeMovingAddresses.Description: Describes your Elastic IP addresses that are being moved to the EC2-VPC platform, or that are being restored to the EC2-Classic platform. This request does not return information about any other Elastic IP addresses in your account.
ec2:DescribeMovingAddresses.Title: DescribeMovingAddresses

ec2:DescribeNatGateways.Description: Describes one or more of the your NAT gateways.
ec2:DescribeNatGateways.Title: DescribeNatGateways

ec2:DescribeNetworkAcls.Description: Describes one or more of your network ACLs.
ec2:DescribeNetworkAcls.Title: DescribeNetworkAcls

ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Description: Describes a network interface attribute. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Title: DescribeNetworkInterfaceAttribute

ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaces.Description: Describes one or more of your network interfaces.
ec2:DescribeNetworkInterfaces.Title: DescribeNetworkInterfaces

ec2:DescribePlacementGroups.Description: Describes one or more of your placement groups. For more information about placement groups and cluster instances, see Cluster Instances in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribePlacementGroups.Title: DescribePlacementGroups

ec2:DescribePrefixLists.Description: Describes available AWS services in a prefix list format, which includes the prefix list name and prefix list ID of the service and the IP address range for the service. A prefix list ID is required for creating an outbound security group rule that allows traffic from a VPC to access an AWS service through a VPC endpoint.
ec2:DescribePrefixLists.Title: DescribePrefixLists

ec2:DescribeRegions.Description: Describes one or more regions that are currently available to you.
ec2:DescribeRegions.Title: DescribeRegions

ec2:DescribeReservedInstances.Description: Describes one or more of the Reserved Instances that you purchased.
ec2:DescribeReservedInstances.Title: DescribeReservedInstances

ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesListings.Description: Describes your account's Reserved Instance listings in the Reserved Instance Marketplace.
ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesListings.Title: DescribeReservedInstancesListings

ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesModificatio.Description: Describes the modifications made to your Reserved Instances. If no parameter is specified, information about all your Reserved Instances modification requests is returned. If a modification ID is specified, only information about the specific modification is returned.
ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesModificatio.Title: DescribeReservedInstancesModifications

ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesOfferings.Description: Describes Reserved Instance offerings that are available for purchase. With Reserved Instances, you purchase the right to launch instances for a period of time. During that time period, you do not receive insufficient capacity errors, and you pay a lower usage rate than the rate charged for On-Demand instances for the actual time used.
ec2:DescribeReservedInstancesOfferings.Title: DescribeReservedInstancesOfferings

ec2:DescribeRouteTables.Description: Describes one or more of your route tables.
ec2:DescribeRouteTables.Title: DescribeRouteTables

ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups.Description: Describes one or more of your security groups.
ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups.Title: DescribeSecurityGroups

ec2:DescribeSnapshotAttribute.Description: Describes the specified attribute of the specified snapshot. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:DescribeSnapshotAttribute.Title: DescribeSnapshotAttribute

ec2:DescribeSnapshots.Description: Describes one or more of the EBS snapshots available to you. Available snapshots include public snapshots available for any AWS account to launch, private snapshots that you own, and private snapshots owned by another AWS account but for which you've been given explicit create volume permissions.
ec2:DescribeSnapshots.Title: DescribeSnapshots

ec2:DescribeSpotDatafeedSubscription.Description: Describes the data feed for Spot instances. For more information, see Spot Instance Data Feed in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribeSpotDatafeedSubscription.Title: DescribeSpotDatafeedSubscription

ec2:DescribeSpotFleetInstances.Description: Describes the running instances for the specified Spot fleet.
ec2:DescribeSpotFleetInstances.Title: DescribeSpotFleetInstances

ec2:DescribeSpotFleetRequestHistory.Description: Describes the events for the specified Spot fleet request during the specified time.
ec2:DescribeSpotFleetRequestHistory.Title: DescribeSpotFleetRequestHistory

ec2:DescribeSpotInstanceRequests.Description: Describes the Spot instance requests that belong to your account. Spot instances are instances that Amazon EC2 launches when the bid price that you specify exceeds the current Spot price. Amazon EC2 periodically sets the Spot price based on available Spot instance capacity and current Spot instance requests. For more information, see Spot Instance Requests in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribeSpotInstanceRequests.Title: DescribeSpotInstanceRequests

ec2:DescribeSpotPriceHistory.Description: Describes the Spot price history. For more information, see Spot Instance Pricing History in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribeSpotPriceHistory.Title: DescribeSpotPriceHistory

ec2:DescribeStaleSecurityGroups.Description: [EC2-VPC only] Describes the stale security group rules for security groups in a specified VPC. Rules are stale when they reference a deleted security group in a peer VPC, or a security group in a peer VPC for which the VPC peering connection has been deleted.
ec2:DescribeStaleSecurityGroups.Title: DescribeStaleSecurityGroups

ec2:DescribeSubnets.Description: Describes one or more of your subnets.
ec2:DescribeSubnets.Title: DescribeSubnets

ec2:DescribeTags.Description: Describes one or more of the tags for your EC2 resources.
ec2:DescribeTags.Title: DescribeTags

ec2:DescribeVolumeAttribute.Description: Describes the specified attribute of the specified volume. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:DescribeVolumeAttribute.Title: DescribeVolumeAttribute

ec2:DescribeVolumeStatus.Description: Describes the status of the specified volumes. Volume status provides the result of the checks performed on your volumes to determine events that can impair the performance of your volumes. The performance of a volume can be affected if an issue occurs on the volume's underlying host. If the volume's underlying host experiences a power outage or system issue, after the system is restored, there could be data inconsistencies on the volume. Volume events notify you if this occurs. Volume actions notify you if any action needs to be taken in response to the event.
ec2:DescribeVolumeStatus.Title: DescribeVolumeStatus

ec2:DescribeVolumesModifications.Description: Reports the current modification status of EBS volumes.
ec2:DescribeVolumesModifications.Title: DescribeVolumesModifications

ec2:DescribeVpcAttribute.Description: Describes the specified attribute of the specified VPC. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:DescribeVpcAttribute.Title: DescribeVpcAttribute

ec2:DescribeVpcClassicLink.Description: Describes the ClassicLink status of one or more VPCs.
ec2:DescribeVpcClassicLink.Title: DescribeVpcClassicLink

ec2:DescribeVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Description: Describes the ClassicLink DNS support status of one or more VPCs. If enabled, the DNS hostname of a linked EC2-Classic instance resolves to its private IP address when addressed from an instance in the VPC to which it's linked. Similarly, the DNS hostname of an instance in a VPC resolves to its private IP address when addressed from a linked EC2-Classic instance. For more information, see ClassicLink in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DescribeVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Title: DescribeVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport

ec2:DescribeVpcEndpointServices.Description: Describes all supported AWS services that can be specified when creating a VPC endpoint.
ec2:DescribeVpcEndpointServices.Title: DescribeVpcEndpointServices

ec2:DescribeVpcEndpoints.Description: Describes one or more of your VPC endpoints.
ec2:DescribeVpcEndpoints.Title: DescribeVpcEndpoints

ec2:DescribeVpcPeeringConnections.Description: Describes one or more of your VPC peering connections.
ec2:DescribeVpcPeeringConnections.Title: DescribeVpcPeeringConnections

ec2:DescribeVpcs.Description: Describes one or more of your VPCs.
ec2:DescribeVpcs.Title: DescribeVpcs

ec2:DescribeVpnConnections.Description: Describes one or more of your VPN connections.
ec2:DescribeVpnConnections.Title: DescribeVpnConnections

ec2:DescribeVpnGateways.Description: Describes one or more of your virtual private gateways.
ec2:DescribeVpnGateways.Title: DescribeVpnGateways

ec2:DetachClassicLinkVpc.Description: Unlinks (detaches) a linked EC2-Classic instance from a VPC. After the instance has been unlinked, the VPC security groups are no longer associated with it. An instance is automatically unlinked from a VPC when it's stopped.
ec2:DetachClassicLinkVpc.Title: DetachClassicLinkVpc

ec2:DetachInternetGateway.Description: Detaches an Internet gateway from a VPC, disabling connectivity between the Internet and the VPC. The VPC must not contain any running instances with Elastic IP addresses or public IPv4 addresses.
ec2:DetachInternetGateway.Title: DetachInternetGateway

ec2:DetachNetworkInterface.Description: Detaches a network interface from an instance.
ec2:DetachNetworkInterface.Title: DetachNetworkInterface

ec2:DetachVolume.Description: Detaches an EBS volume from an instance. Make sure to unmount any file systems on the device within your operating system before detaching the volume. Failure to do so can result in the volume becoming stuck in the busy state while detaching. If this happens, detachment can be delayed indefinitely until you unmount the volume, force detachment, reboot the instance, or all three. If an EBS volume is the root device of an instance, it can't be detached while the instance is running. To detach the root volume, stop the instance first.
ec2:DetachVolume.Title: DetachVolume

ec2:DetachVpnGateway.Description: Detaches a virtual private gateway from a VPC. You do this if you're planning to turn off the VPC and not use it anymore. You can confirm a virtual private gateway has been completely detached from a VPC by describing the virtual private gateway (any attachments to the virtual private gateway are also described).
ec2:DetachVpnGateway.Title: DetachVpnGateway

ec2:DisableVgwRoutePropagation.Description: Disables a virtual private gateway (VGW) from propagating routes to a specified route table of a VPC.
ec2:DisableVgwRoutePropagation.Title: DisableVgwRoutePropagation

ec2:DisableVpcClassicLink.Description: Disables ClassicLink for a VPC. You cannot disable ClassicLink for a VPC that has EC2-Classic instances linked to it.
ec2:DisableVpcClassicLink.Title: DisableVpcClassicLink

ec2:DisableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Description: Disables ClassicLink DNS support for a VPC. If disabled, DNS hostnames resolve to public IP addresses when addressed between a linked EC2-Classic instance and instances in the VPC to which it's linked. For more information about ClassicLink, see ClassicLink in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:DisableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Title: DisableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport

ec2:DisassociateAddress.Description: Disassociates an Elastic IP address from the instance or network interface it's associated with.
ec2:DisassociateAddress.Title: DisassociateAddress

ec2:DisassociateIamInstanceProfile.Description: Disassociates an IAM instance profile from a running or stopped instance.
ec2:DisassociateIamInstanceProfile.Title: DisassociateIamInstanceProfile

ec2:DisassociateRouteTable.Description: Disassociates a subnet from a route table.
ec2:DisassociateRouteTable.Title: DisassociateRouteTable

ec2:DisassociateSubnetCidrBlock.Description: Disassociates a CIDR block from a subnet. Currently, you can disassociate an IPv6 CIDR block only. You must detach or delete all gateways and resources that are associated with the CIDR block before you can disassociate it.
ec2:DisassociateSubnetCidrBlock.Title: DisassociateSubnetCidrBlock

ec2:DisassociateVpcCidrBlock.Description: Disassociates a CIDR block from a VPC. To disassociate the CIDR block, you must specify its association ID. You can get the association ID by using DescribeVpcs. You must detach or delete all gateways and resources that are associated with the CIDR block before you can disassociate it.
ec2:DisassociateVpcCidrBlock.Title: DisassociateVpcCidrBlock

ec2:EnableVgwRoutePropagation.Description: Enables a virtual private gateway (VGW) to propagate routes to the specified route table of a VPC.
ec2:EnableVgwRoutePropagation.Title: EnableVgwRoutePropagation

ec2:EnableVolumeIO.Description: Enables I/O operations for a volume that had I/O operations disabled because the data on the volume was potentially inconsistent.
ec2:EnableVolumeIO.Title: EnableVolumeIO

ec2:EnableVpcClassicLink.Description: Enables a VPC for ClassicLink. You can then link EC2-Classic instances to your ClassicLink-enabled VPC to allow communication over private IP addresses. You cannot enable your VPC for ClassicLink if any of your VPC's route tables have existing routes for address ranges within the 10.0.0.0/8 IP address range, excluding local routes for VPCs in the 10.0.0.0/16 and 10.1.0.0/16 IP address ranges. For more information, see ClassicLink in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:EnableVpcClassicLink.Title: EnableVpcClassicLink

ec2:EnableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Description: Enables a VPC to support DNS hostname resolution for ClassicLink. If enabled, the DNS hostname of a linked EC2-Classic instance resolves to its private IP address when addressed from an instance in the VPC to which it's linked. Similarly, the DNS hostname of an instance in a VPC resolves to its private IP address when addressed from a linked EC2-Classic instance. For more information about ClassicLink, see ClassicLink in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:EnableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport.Title: EnableVpcClassicLinkDnsSupport

ec2:GetConsoleOutput.Description: Gets the console output for the specified instance.
ec2:GetConsoleOutput.Title: GetConsoleOutput

ec2:GetConsoleScreenshot.Description: Retrieve a JPG-format screenshot of a running instance to help with troubleshooting.
ec2:GetConsoleScreenshot.Title: GetConsoleScreenshot

ec2:GetHostReservationPurchasePreview.Description: Preview a reservation purchase with configurations that match those of your Dedicated Host. You must have active Dedicated Hosts in your account before you purchase a reservation.
ec2:GetHostReservationPurchasePreview.Title: GetHostReservationPurchasePreview

ec2:GetPasswordData.Description: Retrieves the encrypted administrator password for a running Windows instance.
ec2:GetPasswordData.Title: GetPasswordData

ec2:GetReservedInstancesExchangeQuote.Description: Returns a quote and exchange information for exchanging one or more specified Convertible Reserved Instances for a new Convertible Reserved Instance. If the exchange cannot be performed, the reason is returned in the response. Use AcceptReservedInstancesExchangeQuote to perform the exchange.
ec2:GetReservedInstancesExchangeQuote.Title: GetReservedInstancesExchangeQuote

ec2:ImportImage.Description: Import single or multi-volume disk images or EBS snapshots into an Amazon Machine Image (AMI). For more information, see Importing a VM as an Image Using VM Import/Export in the VM Import/Export User Guide.
ec2:ImportImage.Title: ImportImage

ec2:ImportInstance.Description: Creates an import instance task using metadata from the specified disk image. ImportInstance only supports single-volume VMs. To import multi-volume VMs, use ImportImage. For more information, see Importing a Virtual Machine Using the Amazon EC2 CLI.
ec2:ImportInstance.Title: ImportInstance

ec2:ImportKeyPair.Description: Imports the public key from an RSA key pair that you created with a third-party tool. Compare this with CreateKeyPair, in which AWS creates the key pair and gives the keys to you (AWS keeps a copy of the public key). With ImportKeyPair, you create the key pair and give AWS just the public key. The private key is never transferred between you and AWS.
ec2:ImportKeyPair.Title: ImportKeyPair

ec2:ImportSnapshot.Description: Imports a disk into an EBS snapshot.
ec2:ImportSnapshot.Title: ImportSnapshot

ec2:ImportVolume.Description: Creates an import volume task using metadata from the specified disk image.For more information, see Importing Disks to Amazon EBS.
ec2:ImportVolume.Title: ImportVolume

ec2:ModifyHosts.Description: Modify the auto-placement setting of a Dedicated Host. When auto-placement is enabled, AWS will place instances that you launch with a tenancy of host, but without targeting a specific host ID, onto any available Dedicated Host in your account which has auto-placement enabled. When auto-placement is disabled, you need to provide a host ID if you want the instance to launch onto a specific host. If no host ID is provided, the instance will be launched onto a suitable host which has auto-placement enabled.
ec2:ModifyHosts.Title: ModifyHosts

ec2:ModifyIdFormat.Description: Modifies the ID format for the specified resource on a per-region basis. You can specify that resources should receive longer IDs (17-character IDs) when they are created. The following resource types support longer IDs: instance | reservation | snapshot | volume.
ec2:ModifyIdFormat.Title: ModifyIdFormat

ec2:ModifyIdentityIdFormat.Description: Modifies the ID format of a resource for a specified IAM user, IAM role, or the root user for an account; or all IAM users, IAM roles, and the root user for an account. You can specify that resources should receive longer IDs (17-character IDs) when they are created.
ec2:ModifyIdentityIdFormat.Title: ModifyIdentityIdFormat

ec2:ModifyImageAttribute.Description: Modifies the specified attribute of the specified AMI. You can specify only one attribute at a time. You can use the Attribute parameter to specify the attribute or one of the following parameters: Description, LaunchPermission, or ProductCode.
ec2:ModifyImageAttribute.Title: ModifyImageAttribute

ec2:ModifyInstanceAttribute.Description: Modifies the specified attribute of the specified instance. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:ModifyInstanceAttribute.Title: ModifyInstanceAttribute

ec2:ModifyInstancePlacement.Description: Set the instance affinity value for a specific stopped instance and modify the instance tenancy setting.
ec2:ModifyInstancePlacement.Title: ModifyInstancePlacement

ec2:ModifyNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Description: Modifies the specified network interface attribute. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:ModifyNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Title: ModifyNetworkInterfaceAttribute

ec2:ModifyReservedInstances.Description: Modifies the Availability Zone, instance count, instance type, or network platform (EC2-Classic or EC2-VPC) of your Reserved Instances. The Reserved Instances to be modified must be identical, except for Availability Zone, network platform, and instance type.
ec2:ModifyReservedInstances.Title: ModifyReservedInstances

ec2:ModifySnapshotAttribute.Description: Adds or removes permission settings for the specified snapshot. You may add or remove specified AWS account IDs from a snapshot's list of create volume permissions, but you cannot do both in a single API call. If you need to both add and remove account IDs for a snapshot, you must use multiple API calls.
ec2:ModifySnapshotAttribute.Title: ModifySnapshotAttribute

ec2:ModifySpotFleetRequest.Description: Modifies the specified Spot fleet request.
ec2:ModifySpotFleetRequest.Title: ModifySpotFleetRequest

ec2:ModifySubnetAttribute.Description: Modifies a subnet attribute. You can only modify one attribute at a time.
ec2:ModifySubnetAttribute.Title: ModifySubnetAttribute

ec2:ModifyVolume.Description: You can modify several parameters of an existing EBS volume, including volume size, volume type, and IOPS capacity. If your EBS volume is attached to a current-generation EC2 instance type, you may be able to apply these changes without stopping the instance or detaching the volume from it. For more information about modifying an EBS volume running Linux, see Modifying the Size, IOPS, or Type of an EBS Volume on Linux. For more information about modifying an EBS volume running Windows, see Modifying the Size, IOPS, or Type of an EBS Volume on Windows.
ec2:ModifyVolume.Title: ModifyVolume

ec2:ModifyVpcAttribute.Description: Modifies the specified attribute of the specified VPC.
ec2:ModifyVpcAttribute.Title: ModifyVpcAttribute

ec2:ModifyVpcEndpoint.Description: Modifies attributes of a specified VPC endpoint. The attributes that you can modify depend on the type of VPC endpoint (interface or gateway). For more information, see VPC Endpoints in the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud User Guide.
ec2:ModifyVpcEndpoint.Title: ModifyVpcEndpoint

ec2:ModifyVpcPeeringConnectionOptions.Description: Modifies the VPC peering connection options on one side of a VPC peering connection. You can do the following:
ec2:ModifyVpcPeeringConnectionOptions.Title: ModifyVpcPeeringConnectionOptions

ec2:MonitorInstances.Description: Enables detailed monitoring for a running instance. Otherwise, basic monitoring is enabled. For more information, see Monitoring Your Instances and Volumes in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:MonitorInstances.Title: MonitorInstances

ec2:MoveAddressToVpc.Description: Moves an Elastic IP address from the EC2-Classic platform to the EC2-VPC platform. The Elastic IP address must be allocated to your account for more than 24 hours, and it must not be associated with an instance. After the Elastic IP address is moved, it is no longer available for use in the EC2-Classic platform, unless you move it back using the RestoreAddressToClassic request. You cannot move an Elastic IP address that was originally allocated for use in the EC2-VPC platform to the EC2-Classic platform.
ec2:MoveAddressToVpc.Title: MoveAddressToVpc

ec2:PurchaseHostReservation.Description: Purchase a reservation with configurations that match those of your Dedicated Host. You must have active Dedicated Hosts in your account before you purchase a reservation. This action results in the specified reservation being purchased and charged to your account.
ec2:PurchaseHostReservation.Title: PurchaseHostReservation

ec2:PurchaseReservedInstancesOffering.Description: Purchases a Reserved Instance for use with your account. With Reserved Instances, you pay a lower hourly rate compared to On-Demand instance pricing.
ec2:PurchaseReservedInstancesOffering.Title: PurchaseReservedInstancesOffering

ec2:PurchaseScheduledInstances.Description: Purchases one or more Scheduled Instances with the specified schedule.
ec2:PurchaseScheduledInstances.Title: PurchaseScheduledInstances

ec2:RebootInstances.Description: Requests a reboot of one or more instances. This operation is asynchronous; it only queues a request to reboot the specified instances. The operation succeeds if the instances are valid and belong to you. Requests to reboot terminated instances are ignored.
ec2:RebootInstances.Title: RebootInstances

ec2:RegisterImage.Description: Registers an AMI. When you're creating an AMI, this is the final step you must complete before you can launch an instance from the AMI. For more information about creating AMIs, see Creating Your Own AMIs in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:RegisterImage.Title: RegisterImage

ec2:RejectVpcPeeringConnection.Description: Rejects a VPC peering connection request. The VPC peering connection must be in the pending-acceptance state. Use the DescribeVpcPeeringConnections request to view your outstanding VPC peering connection requests. To delete an active VPC peering connection, or to delete a VPC peering connection request that you initiated, use DeleteVpcPeeringConnection.
ec2:RejectVpcPeeringConnection.Title: RejectVpcPeeringConnection

ec2:ReleaseAddress.Description: Releases the specified Elastic IP address.
ec2:ReleaseAddress.Title: ReleaseAddress

ec2:ReleaseHosts.Description: When you no longer want to use an On-Demand Dedicated Host it can be released. On-Demand billing is stopped and the host goes into released state. The host ID of Dedicated Hosts that have been released can no longer be specified in another request, e.g., ModifyHosts. You must stop or terminate all instances on a host before it can be released.
ec2:ReleaseHosts.Title: ReleaseHosts

ec2:ReplaceIamInstanceProfileAssociation.Description: Replaces an IAM instance profile for the specified running instance. You can use this action to change the IAM instance profile that's associated with an instance without having to disassociate the existing IAM instance profile first.
ec2:ReplaceIamInstanceProfileAssociation.Title: ReplaceIamInstanceProfileAssociation

ec2:ReplaceNetworkAclAssociation.Description: Changes which network ACL a subnet is associated with. By default when you create a subnet, it's automatically associated with the default network ACL. For more information about network ACLs, see Network ACLs in the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud User Guide.
ec2:ReplaceNetworkAclAssociation.Title: ReplaceNetworkAclAssociation

ec2:ReplaceNetworkAclEntry.Description: Replaces an entry (rule) in a network ACL. For more information about network ACLs, see Network ACLs in the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud User Guide.
ec2:ReplaceNetworkAclEntry.Title: ReplaceNetworkAclEntry

ec2:ReplaceRoute.Description: Replaces an existing route within a route table in a VPC. You must provide only one of the following: Internet gateway or virtual private gateway, NAT instance, NAT gateway, VPC peering connection, network interface, or egress-only Internet gateway.
ec2:ReplaceRoute.Title: ReplaceRoute

ec2:ReplaceRouteTableAssociation.Description: Changes the route table associated with a given subnet in a VPC. After the operation completes, the subnet uses the routes in the new route table it's associated with. For more information about route tables, see Route Tables in the Amazon Virtual Private Cloud User Guide.
ec2:ReplaceRouteTableAssociation.Title: ReplaceRouteTableAssociation

ec2:ReportInstanceStatus.Description: Submits feedback about the status of an instance. The instance must be in the running state. If your experience with the instance differs from the instance status returned by DescribeInstanceStatus, use ReportInstanceStatus to report your experience with the instance. Amazon EC2 collects this information to improve the accuracy of status checks.
ec2:ReportInstanceStatus.Title: ReportInstanceStatus

ec2:RequestSpotInstances.Description: Creates a Spot instance request. Spot instances are instances that Amazon EC2 launches when the bid price that you specify exceeds the current Spot price. Amazon EC2 periodically sets the Spot price based on available Spot Instance capacity and current Spot instance requests. For more information, see Spot Instance Requests in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:RequestSpotInstances.Title: RequestSpotInstances

ec2:ResetImageAttribute.Description: Resets an attribute of an AMI to its default value.
ec2:ResetImageAttribute.Title: ResetImageAttribute

ec2:ResetInstanceAttribute.Description: Resets an attribute of an instance to its default value. To reset the kernel or ramdisk, the instance must be in a stopped state. To reset the sourceDestCheck, the instance can be either running or stopped.
ec2:ResetInstanceAttribute.Title: ResetInstanceAttribute

ec2:ResetNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Description: Resets a network interface attribute. You can specify only one attribute at a time.
ec2:ResetNetworkInterfaceAttribute.Title: ResetNetworkInterfaceAttribute

ec2:ResetSnapshotAttribute.Description: Resets permission settings for the specified snapshot.
ec2:ResetSnapshotAttribute.Title: ResetSnapshotAttribute

ec2:RestoreAddressToClassic.Description: Restores an Elastic IP address that was previously moved to the EC2-VPC platform back to the EC2-Classic platform. You cannot move an Elastic IP address that was originally allocated for use in EC2-VPC. The Elastic IP address must not be associated with an instance or network interface.
ec2:RestoreAddressToClassic.Title: RestoreAddressToClassic

ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress.Description: [EC2-VPC only] Removes one or more egress rules from a security group for EC2-VPC. This action doesn't apply to security groups for use in EC2-Classic. To remove a rule, the values that you specify (for example, ports) must match the existing rule's values exactly.
ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupEgress.Title: RevokeSecurityGroupEgress

ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress.Description: Removes one or more ingress rules from a security group. To remove a rule, the values that you specify (for example, ports) must match the existing rule's values exactly.
ec2:RevokeSecurityGroupIngress.Title: RevokeSecurityGroupIngress

ec2:RunInstances.Description: Launches the specified number of instances using an AMI for which you have permissions.
ec2:RunInstances.Title: RunInstances

ec2:StartInstances.Description: Starts an Amazon EBS-backed instance that you've previously stopped.
ec2:StartInstances.Title: StartInstances

ec2:TerminateInstances.Description: Shuts down one or more instances. This operation is idempotent; if you terminate an instance more than once, each call succeeds.
ec2:TerminateInstances.Title: TerminateInstances

ec2:UnassignIpv6Addresses.Description: Unassigns one or more IPv6 addresses from a network interface.
ec2:UnassignIpv6Addresses.Title: UnassignIpv6Addresses

ec2:UnassignPrivateIpAddresses.Description: Unassigns one or more secondary private IP addresses from a network interface.
ec2:UnassignPrivateIpAddresses.Title: UnassignPrivateIpAddresses

ec2:UnmonitorInstances.Description: Disables detailed monitoring for a running instance. For more information, see Monitoring Your Instances and Volumes in the Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud User Guide.
ec2:UnmonitorInstances.Title: UnmonitorInstances

ec2:UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsE.Description: [EC2-VPC only] Updates the description of an egress (outbound) security group rule. You can replace an existing description, or add a description to a rule that did not have one previously.
ec2:UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsE.Title: UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsEgress

ec2:UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsI.Description: Updates the description of an ingress (inbound) security group rule. You can replace an existing description, or add a description to a rule that did not have one previously.
ec2:UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsI.Title: UpdateSecurityGroupRuleDescriptionsIngress

ecr:BatchCheckLayerAvailability.Description: Check the availability of multiple image layers in a specified registry and repository.
ecr:BatchCheckLayerAvailability.Title: BatchCheckLayerAvailability

ecr:BatchDeleteImage.Description: Deletes a list of specified images within a specified repository. Images are specified with either imageTag or imageDigest.
ecr:BatchDeleteImage.Title: BatchDeleteImage

ecr:BatchGetImage.Description: Gets detailed information for specified images within a specified repository. Images are specified with either imageTag or imageDigest.
ecr:BatchGetImage.Title: BatchGetImage

ecr:CompleteLayerUpload.Description: Informs Amazon ECR that the image layer upload has completed for a specified registry, repository name, and upload ID. You can optionally provide a sha256 digest of the image layer for data validation purposes.
ecr:CompleteLayerUpload.Title: CompleteLayerUpload

ecr:DeleteRepository.Description: Deletes an existing image repository. If a repository contains images, you must use the force option to delete it.
ecr:DeleteRepository.Title: DeleteRepository

ecr:DeleteRepositoryPolicy.Description: Deletes the repository policy from a specified repository.
ecr:DeleteRepositoryPolicy.Title: DeleteRepositoryPolicy

ecr:DescribeRepositories.Description: Describes image repositories in a registry.
ecr:DescribeRepositories.Title: DescribeRepositories

ecr:GetAuthorizationToken.Description: Retrieves a token that is valid for a specified registry for 12 hours. This command allows you to use the docker CLI to push and pull images with Amazon ECR. If you do not specify a registry, the default registry is assumed.
ecr:GetAuthorizationToken.Title: GetAuthorizationToken

ecr:GetDownloadUrlForLayer.Description: Retrieves the pre-signed Amazon S3 download URL corresponding to an image layer. You can only get URLs for image layers that are referenced in an image.
ecr:GetDownloadUrlForLayer.Title: GetDownloadUrlForLayer

ecr:GetRepositoryPolicy.Description: Retrieves the repository policy for a specified repository.
ecr:GetRepositoryPolicy.Title: GetRepositoryPolicy

ecr:InitiateLayerUpload.Description: Notify Amazon ECR that you intend to upload an image layer.
ecr:InitiateLayerUpload.Title: InitiateLayerUpload

ecr:ListImages.Description: Lists all the image IDs for a given repository.
ecr:ListImages.Title: ListImages

ecr:PutImage.Description: Creates or updates the image manifest and tags associated with an image.
ecr:PutImage.Title: PutImage

ecr:SetRepositoryPolicy.Description: Applies a repository policy on a specified repository to control access permissions.
ecr:SetRepositoryPolicy.Title: SetRepositoryPolicy

ecr:UploadLayerPart.Description: Uploads an image layer part to Amazon ECR.
ecr:UploadLayerPart.Title: UploadLayerPart

ecs:CreateCluster.Description: Creates a new Amazon ECS cluster. By default, your account receives a default cluster when you launch your first container instance. However, you can create your own cluster with a unique name with the CreateCluster action.
ecs:CreateCluster.Title: CreateCluster

ecs:CreateService.Description: Runs and maintains a desired number of tasks from a specified task definition. If the number of tasks running in a service drops below desiredCount, Amazon ECS spawns another copy of the task in the specified cluster. To update an existing service, see UpdateService.
ecs:CreateService.Title: CreateService

ecs:DeleteCluster.Description: Deletes the specified cluster. You must deregister all container instances from this cluster before you may delete it. You can list the container instances in a cluster with ListContainerInstances and deregister them with DeregisterContainerInstance.
ecs:DeleteCluster.Title: DeleteCluster

ecs:DeleteService.Description: Deletes a specified service within a cluster. You can delete a service if you have no running tasks in it and the desired task count is zero. If the service is actively maintaining tasks, you cannot delete it, and you must update the service to a desired task count of zero. For more information, see UpdateService.
ecs:DeleteService.Title: DeleteService

ecs:DeregisterContainerInstance.Description: Deregisters an Amazon ECS container instance from the specified cluster. This instance is no longer available to run tasks.
ecs:DeregisterContainerInstance.Title: DeregisterContainerInstance

ecs:DeregisterTaskDefinition.Description: Deregisters the specified task definition by family and revision. Upon deregistration, the task definition is marked as INACTIVE. Existing tasks and services that reference an INACTIVE task definition continue to run without disruption. Existing services that reference an INACTIVE task definition can still scale up or down by modifying the service's desired count.
ecs:DeregisterTaskDefinition.Title: DeregisterTaskDefinition

ecs:DescribeClusters.Description: Describes one or more of your clusters.
ecs:DescribeClusters.Title: DescribeClusters

ecs:DescribeContainerInstances.Description: Describes Amazon EC2 Container Service container instances. Returns metadata about registered and remaining resources on each container instance requested.
ecs:DescribeContainerInstances.Title: DescribeContainerInstances

ecs:DescribeServices.Description: Describes the specified services running in your cluster.
ecs:DescribeServices.Title: DescribeServices

ecs:DescribeTaskDefinition.Description: Describes a task definition. You can specify a family and revision to find information about a specific task definition, or you can simply specify the family to find the latest ACTIVE revision in that family.
ecs:DescribeTaskDefinition.Title: DescribeTaskDefinition

ecs:DescribeTasks.Description: Describes a specified task or tasks.
ecs:DescribeTasks.Title: DescribeTasks

ecs:DiscoverPollEndpoint.Description: Returns an endpoint for the Amazon EC2 Container Service agent to poll for updates.
ecs:DiscoverPollEndpoint.Title: DiscoverPollEndpoint

ecs:ListClusters.Description: Returns a list of existing clusters.
ecs:ListClusters.Title: ListClusters

ecs:ListContainerInstances.Description: Returns a list of container instances in a specified cluster. You can filter the results of a ListContainerInstances operation with cluster query language statements inside the filter parameter. For more information, see Cluster Query Language in the Amazon EC2 Container Service Developer Guide.
ecs:ListContainerInstances.Title: ListContainerInstances

ecs:ListServices.Description: Lists the services that are running in a specified cluster.
ecs:ListServices.Title: ListServices

ecs:ListTaskDefinitionFamilies.Description: Returns a list of task definition families that are registered to your account (which may include task definition families that no longer have any ACTIVE task definition revisions).
ecs:ListTaskDefinitionFamilies.Title: ListTaskDefinitionFamilies

ecs:ListTaskDefinitions.Description: Returns a list of task definitions that are registered to your account. You can filter the results by family name with the familyPrefix parameter or by status with the status parameter.
ecs:ListTaskDefinitions.Title: ListTaskDefinitions

ecs:ListTasks.Description: Returns a list of tasks for a specified cluster. You can filter the results by family name, by a particular container instance, or by the desired status of the task with the family, containerInstance, and desiredStatus parameters.
ecs:ListTasks.Title: ListTasks

ecs:RegisterContainerInstance.Description: Registers an EC2 instance into the specified cluster. This instance becomes available to place containers on.
ecs:RegisterContainerInstance.Title: RegisterContainerInstance

ecs:RegisterTaskDefinition.Description: Registers a new task definition from the supplied family and containerDefinitions. Optionally, you can add data volumes to your containers with the volumes parameter. For more information about task definition parameters and defaults, see Amazon ECS Task Definitions in the Amazon EC2 Container Service Developer Guide.
ecs:RegisterTaskDefinition.Title: RegisterTaskDefinition

ecs:RunTask.Description: Starts a new task using the specified task definition.
ecs:RunTask.Title: RunTask

ecs:StartTask.Description: Starts a new task from the specified task definition on the specified container instance or instances.
ecs:StartTask.Title: StartTask

ecs:SubmitContainerStateChange.Description: Sent to acknowledge that a container changed states.
ecs:SubmitContainerStateChange.Title: SubmitContainerStateChange

ecs:SubmitTaskStateChange.Description: Sent to acknowledge that a task changed states.
ecs:SubmitTaskStateChange.Title: SubmitTaskStateChange

ecs:UpdateContainerAgent.Description: Updates the Amazon ECS container agent on a specified container instance. Updating the Amazon ECS container agent does not interrupt running tasks or services on the container instance. The process for updating the agent differs depending on whether your container instance was launched with the Amazon ECS-optimized AMI or another operating system.
ecs:UpdateContainerAgent.Title: UpdateContainerAgent

ecs:UpdateService.Description: Modifies the desired count, deployment configuration, or task definition used in a service.
ecs:UpdateService.Title: UpdateService

elasticache:AddTagsToResource.Description: Adds up to 50 cost allocation tags to the named resource. A cost allocation tag is a key-value pair where the key and value are case-sensitive. You can use cost allocation tags to categorize and track your AWS costs.
elasticache:AddTagsToResource.Title: AddTagsToResource

elasticache:AuthorizeCacheSecurityGroupI.Description: Allows network ingress to a cache security group. Applications using ElastiCache must be running on Amazon EC2, and Amazon EC2 security groups are used as the authorization mechanism.
elasticache:AuthorizeCacheSecurityGroupI.Title: AuthorizeCacheSecurityGroupIngress

elasticache:CopySnapshot.Description: Makes a copy of an existing snapshot.
elasticache:CopySnapshot.Title: CopySnapshot

elasticache:CreateCacheCluster.Description: Creates a cluster. All nodes in the cluster run the same protocol-compliant cache engine software, either Memcached or Redis.
elasticache:CreateCacheCluster.Title: CreateCacheCluster

elasticache:CreateCacheParameterGroup.Description: Creates a new Amazon ElastiCache cache parameter group. An ElastiCache cache parameter group is a collection of parameters and their values that are applied to all of the nodes in any cluster or replication group using the CacheParameterGroup.
elasticache:CreateCacheParameterGroup.Title: CreateCacheParameterGroup

elasticache:CreateCacheSecurityGroup.Description: Creates a new cache security group. Use a cache security group to control access to one or more clusters.
elasticache:CreateCacheSecurityGroup.Title: CreateCacheSecurityGroup

elasticache:CreateCacheSubnetGroup.Description: Creates a new cache subnet group.
elasticache:CreateCacheSubnetGroup.Title: CreateCacheSubnetGroup

elasticache:CreateReplicationGroup.Description: Creates a Redis (cluster mode disabled) or a Redis (cluster mode enabled) replication group.
elasticache:CreateReplicationGroup.Title: CreateReplicationGroup

elasticache:CreateSnapshot.Description: Creates a copy of an entire cluster or replication group at a specific moment in time.
elasticache:CreateSnapshot.Title: CreateSnapshot

elasticache:DeleteCacheCluster.Description: Deletes a previously provisioned cluster. DeleteCacheCluster deletes all associated cache nodes, node endpoints and the cluster itself. When you receive a successful response from this operation, Amazon ElastiCache immediately begins deleting the cluster; you cannot cancel or revert this operation.
elasticache:DeleteCacheCluster.Title: DeleteCacheCluster

elasticache:DeleteCacheParameterGroup.Description: Deletes the specified cache parameter group. You cannot delete a cache parameter group if it is associated with any cache clusters.
elasticache:DeleteCacheParameterGroup.Title: DeleteCacheParameterGroup

elasticache:DeleteReplicationGroup.Description: Deletes an existing replication group. By default, this operation deletes the entire replication group, including the primary/primaries and all of the read replicas. If the replication group has only one primary, you can optionally delete only the read replicas, while retaining the primary by setting RetainPrimaryCluster=true.
elasticache:DeleteReplicationGroup.Title: DeleteReplicationGroup

elasticache:DeleteSnapshot.Description: Deletes an existing snapshot. When you receive a successful response from this operation, ElastiCache immediately begins deleting the snapshot; you cannot cancel or revert this operation.
elasticache:DeleteSnapshot.Title: DeleteSnapshot

elasticache:DescribeCacheClusters.Description: Returns information about all provisioned clusters if no cluster identifier is specified, or about a specific cache cluster if a cluster identifier is supplied.
elasticache:DescribeCacheClusters.Title: DescribeCacheClusters

elasticache:DescribeCacheEngineVersions.Description: Returns a list of the available cache engines and their versions.
elasticache:DescribeCacheEngineVersions.Title: DescribeCacheEngineVersions

elasticache:DescribeCacheParameterGroups.Description: Returns a list of cache parameter group descriptions. If a cache parameter group name is specified, the list contains only the descriptions for that group.
elasticache:DescribeCacheParameterGroups.Title: DescribeCacheParameterGroups

elasticache:DescribeCacheParameters.Description: Returns the detailed parameter list for a particular cache parameter group.
elasticache:DescribeCacheParameters.Title: DescribeCacheParameters

elasticache:DescribeCacheSecurityGroups.Description: Returns a list of cache security group descriptions. If a cache security group name is specified, the list contains only the description of that group.
elasticache:DescribeCacheSecurityGroups.Title: DescribeCacheSecurityGroups

elasticache:DescribeCacheSubnetGroups.Description: Returns a list of cache subnet group descriptions. If a subnet group name is specified, the list contains only the description of that group.
elasticache:DescribeCacheSubnetGroups.Title: DescribeCacheSubnetGroups

elasticache:DescribeEngineDefaultParamet.Description: Returns the default engine and system parameter information for the specified cache engine.
elasticache:DescribeEngineDefaultParamet.Title: DescribeEngineDefaultParameters

elasticache:DescribeEvents.Description: Returns events related to clusters, cache security groups, and cache parameter groups. You can obtain events specific to a particular cluster, cache security group, or cache parameter group by providing the name as a parameter.
elasticache:DescribeEvents.Title: DescribeEvents

elasticache:DescribeReplicationGroups.Description: Returns information about a particular replication group. If no identifier is specified, DescribeReplicationGroups returns information about all replication groups.
elasticache:DescribeReplicationGroups.Title: DescribeReplicationGroups

elasticache:DescribeReservedCacheNodes.Description: Returns information about reserved cache nodes for this account, or about a specified reserved cache node.
elasticache:DescribeReservedCacheNodes.Title: DescribeReservedCacheNodes

elasticache:DescribeReservedCacheNodesOf.Description: Lists available reserved cache node offerings.
elasticache:DescribeReservedCacheNodesOf.Title: DescribeReservedCacheNodesOfferings

elasticache:DescribeSnapshots.Description: Returns information about cluster or replication group snapshots. By default, DescribeSnapshots lists all of your snapshots; it can optionally describe a single snapshot, or just the snapshots associated with a particular cache cluster.
elasticache:DescribeSnapshots.Title: DescribeSnapshots

elasticache:ListAllowedNodeTypeModificat.Description: Lists all available node types that you can scale your Redis cluster's or replication group's current node type up to.
elasticache:ListAllowedNodeTypeModificat.Title: ListAllowedNodeTypeModifications

elasticache:ListTagsForResource.Description: Lists all cost allocation tags currently on the named resource. A cost allocation tag is a key-value pair where the key is case-sensitive and the value is optional. You can use cost allocation tags to categorize and track your AWS costs.
elasticache:ListTagsForResource.Title: ListTagsForResource

elasticache:ModifyCacheCluster.Description: Modifies the settings for a cluster. You can use this operation to change one or more cluster configuration parameters by specifying the parameters and the new values.
elasticache:ModifyCacheCluster.Title: ModifyCacheCluster

elasticache:ModifyCacheParameterGroup.Description: Modifies the parameters of a cache parameter group. You can modify up to 20 parameters in a single request by submitting a list parameter name and value pairs.
elasticache:ModifyCacheParameterGroup.Title: ModifyCacheParameterGroup

elasticache:ModifyCacheSubnetGroup.Description: Modifies an existing cache subnet group.
elasticache:ModifyCacheSubnetGroup.Title: ModifyCacheSubnetGroup

elasticache:ModifyReplicationGroup.Description: Modifies the settings for a replication group.
elasticache:ModifyReplicationGroup.Title: ModifyReplicationGroup

elasticache:PurchaseReservedCacheNodesOf.Description: Allows you to purchase a reserved cache node offering.
elasticache:PurchaseReservedCacheNodesOf.Title: PurchaseReservedCacheNodesOffering

elasticache:RebootCacheCluster.Description: Reboots some, or all, of the cache nodes within a provisioned cluster. This operation applies any modified cache parameter groups to the cluster. The reboot operation takes place as soon as possible, and results in a momentary outage to the cluster. During the reboot, the cluster status is set to REBOOTING.
elasticache:RebootCacheCluster.Title: RebootCacheCluster

elasticache:RemoveTagsFromResource.Description: Removes the tags identified by the TagKeys list from the named resource.
elasticache:RemoveTagsFromResource.Title: RemoveTagsFromResource

elasticache:ResetCacheParameterGroup.Description: Modifies the parameters of a cache parameter group to the engine or system default value. You can reset specific parameters by submitting a list of parameter names. To reset the entire cache parameter group, specify the ResetAllParameters and CacheParameterGroupName parameters.
elasticache:ResetCacheParameterGroup.Title: ResetCacheParameterGroup

elasticache:RevokeCacheSecurityGroupIngr.Description: Revokes ingress from a cache security group. Use this operation to disallow access from an Amazon EC2 security group that had been previously authorized.
elasticache:RevokeCacheSecurityGroupIngr.Title: RevokeCacheSecurityGroupIngress

elasticbeanstalk:ApplyEnvironmentManaged.Description: Applies a scheduled managed action immediately. A managed action can be applied only if its status is Scheduled. Get the status and action ID of a managed action with DescribeEnvironmentManagedActions.
elasticbeanstalk:ApplyEnvironmentManaged.Title: ApplyEnvironmentManagedAction

elasticbeanstalk:CheckDNSAvailability.Description: Checks if the specified CNAME is available.
elasticbeanstalk:CheckDNSAvailability.Title: CheckDNSAvailability

elasticbeanstalk:CreateApplication.Description: Creates an application that has one configuration template named default and no application versions.
elasticbeanstalk:CreateApplication.Title: CreateApplication

elasticbeanstalk:CreateApplicationVersio.Description: Creates an application version for the specified application. You can create an application version from a source bundle in Amazon S3, a commit in AWS CodeCommit, or the output of an AWS CodeBuild build as follows:
elasticbeanstalk:CreateApplicationVersio.Title: CreateApplicationVersion

elasticbeanstalk:CreateConfigurationTemp.Description: Creates a configuration template. Templates are associated with a specific application and are used to deploy different versions of the application with the same configuration settings.
elasticbeanstalk:CreateConfigurationTemp.Title: CreateConfigurationTemplate

elasticbeanstalk:CreateEnvironment.Description: Launches an environment for the specified application using the specified configuration.
elasticbeanstalk:CreateEnvironment.Title: CreateEnvironment

elasticbeanstalk:CreateStorageLocation.Description: Creates a bucket in Amazon S3 to store application versions, logs, and other files used by Elastic Beanstalk environments. The Elastic Beanstalk console and EB CLI call this API the first time you create an environment in a region. If the storage location already exists, CreateStorageLocation still returns the bucket name but does not create a new bucket.
elasticbeanstalk:CreateStorageLocation.Title: CreateStorageLocation

elasticbeanstalk:DeleteApplication.Description: Deletes the specified application along with all associated versions and configurations. The application versions will not be deleted from your Amazon S3 bucket.
elasticbeanstalk:DeleteApplication.Title: DeleteApplication

elasticbeanstalk:DeleteApplicationVersio.Description: Deletes the specified version from the specified application.
elasticbeanstalk:DeleteApplicationVersio.Title: DeleteApplicationVersion

elasticbeanstalk:DeleteEnvironmentConfig.Description: Deletes the draft configuration associated with the running environment.
elasticbeanstalk:DeleteEnvironmentConfig.Title: DeleteEnvironmentConfiguration

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeApplicationVers.Description: Retrieve a list of application versions.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeApplicationVers.Title: DescribeApplicationVersions

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeApplications.Description: Returns the descriptions of existing applications.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeApplications.Title: DescribeApplications

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeConfigurationOp.Description: Describes the configuration options that are used in a particular configuration template or environment, or that a specified solution stack defines. The description includes the values the options, their default values, and an indication of the required action on a running environment if an option value is changed.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeConfigurationOp.Title: DescribeConfigurationOptions

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeConfigurationSe.Description: Returns a description of the settings for the specified configuration set, that is, either a configuration template or the configuration set associated with a running environment.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeConfigurationSe.Title: DescribeConfigurationSettings

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentHeal.Description: Returns information about the overall health of the specified environment. The DescribeEnvironmentHealth operation is only available with AWS Elastic Beanstalk Enhanced Health.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentHeal.Title: DescribeEnvironmentHealth

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentMana.Description: Lists an environment's completed and failed managed actions.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentMana.Title: DescribeEnvironmentManagedActionHistory

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentMana.Description: Lists an environment's upcoming and in-progress managed actions.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentMana.Title: DescribeEnvironmentManagedActions

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentReso.Description: Returns AWS resources for this environment.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEnvironmentReso.Title: DescribeEnvironmentResources

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEvents.Description: Returns list of event descriptions matching criteria up to the last 6 weeks.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeEvents.Title: DescribeEvents

elasticbeanstalk:DescribeInstancesHealth.Description: Retrives detailed information about the health of instances in your AWS Elastic Beanstalk. This operation requires enhanced health reporting.
elasticbeanstalk:DescribeInstancesHealth.Title: DescribeInstancesHealth

elasticbeanstalk:ListAvailableSolutionSt.Description: Returns a list of the available solution stack names, with the public version first and then in reverse chronological order.
elasticbeanstalk:ListAvailableSolutionSt.Title: ListAvailableSolutionStacks

elasticbeanstalk:ListTagsForResource.Description: Returns the tags applied to an AWS Elastic Beanstalk resource. The response contains a list of tag key-value pairs.
elasticbeanstalk:ListTagsForResource.Title: ListTagsForResource

elasticbeanstalk:RebuildEnvironment.Description: Deletes and recreates all of the AWS resources (for example: the Auto Scaling group, load balancer, etc.) for a specified environment and forces a restart.
elasticbeanstalk:RebuildEnvironment.Title: RebuildEnvironment

elasticbeanstalk:RequestEnvironmentInfo.Description: Initiates a request to compile the specified type of information of the deployed environment.
elasticbeanstalk:RequestEnvironmentInfo.Title: RequestEnvironmentInfo

elasticbeanstalk:RestartAppServer.Description: Causes the environment to restart the application container server running on each Amazon EC2 instance.
elasticbeanstalk:RestartAppServer.Title: RestartAppServer

elasticbeanstalk:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo.Description: Retrieves the compiled information from a RequestEnvironmentInfo request.
elasticbeanstalk:RetrieveEnvironmentInfo.Title: RetrieveEnvironmentInfo

elasticbeanstalk:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs.Description: Swaps the CNAMEs of two environments.
elasticbeanstalk:SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs.Title: SwapEnvironmentCNAMEs

elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplication.Description: Updates the specified application to have the specified properties.
elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplication.Title: UpdateApplication

elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplicationResour.Description: Modifies lifecycle settings for an application.
elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplicationResour.Title: UpdateApplicationResourceLifecycle

elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplicationVersio.Description: Updates the specified application version to have the specified properties.
elasticbeanstalk:UpdateApplicationVersio.Title: UpdateApplicationVersion

elasticbeanstalk:UpdateConfigurationTemp.Description: Updates the specified configuration template to have the specified properties or configuration option values.
elasticbeanstalk:UpdateConfigurationTemp.Title: UpdateConfigurationTemplate

elasticbeanstalk:UpdateEnvironment.Description: Updates the environment description, deploys a new application version, updates the configuration settings to an entirely new configuration template, or updates select configuration option values in the running environment.
elasticbeanstalk:UpdateEnvironment.Title: UpdateEnvironment

elasticbeanstalk:ValidateConfigurationSe.Description: Takes a set of configuration settings and either a configuration template or environment, and determines whether those values are valid.
elasticbeanstalk:ValidateConfigurationSe.Title: ValidateConfigurationSettings

elasticfilesystem:CreateFileSystem.Description: Creates a new, empty file system. The operation requires a creation token in the request that Amazon EFS uses to ensure idempotent creation (calling the operation with same creation token has no effect). If a file system does not currently exist that is owned by the caller's AWS account with the specified creation token, this operation does the following:
elasticfilesystem:CreateFileSystem.Title: CreateFileSystem

elasticfilesystem:CreateMountTarget.Description: Creates a mount target for a file system. You can then mount the file system on EC2 instances via the mount target.
elasticfilesystem:CreateMountTarget.Title: CreateMountTarget

elasticfilesystem:CreateTags.Description: Creates or overwrites tags associated with a file system. Each tag is a key-value pair. If a tag key specified in the request already exists on the file system, this operation overwrites its value with the value provided in the request. If you add the Name tag to your file system, Amazon EFS returns it in the response to the DescribeFileSystems operation.
elasticfilesystem:CreateTags.Title: CreateTags

elasticfilesystem:DeleteFileSystem.Description: Deletes a file system, permanently severing access to its contents. Upon return, the file system no longer exists and you can't access any contents of the deleted file system.
elasticfilesystem:DeleteFileSystem.Title: DeleteFileSystem

elasticfilesystem:DeleteTags.Description: Deletes the specified tags from a file system. If the DeleteTags request includes a tag key that does not exist, Amazon EFS ignores it and doesn't cause an error. For more information about tags and related restrictions, see Tag Restrictions in the AWS Billing and Cost Management User Guide.
elasticfilesystem:DeleteTags.Title: DeleteTags

elasticfilesystem:DescribeFileSystems.Description: Returns the description of a specific Amazon EFS file system if either the file system CreationToken or the FileSystemId is provided. Otherwise, it returns descriptions of all file systems owned by the caller's AWS account in the AWS Region of the endpoint that you're calling.
elasticfilesystem:DescribeFileSystems.Title: DescribeFileSystems

elasticfilesystem:DescribeMountTargetSec.Description: Returns the security groups currently in effect for a mount target. This operation requires that the network interface of the mount target has been created and the lifecycle state of the mount target is not deleted.
elasticfilesystem:DescribeMountTargetSec.Title: DescribeMountTargetSecurityGroups

elasticfilesystem:DescribeMountTargets.Description: Returns the descriptions of all the current mount targets, or a specific mount target, for a file system. When requesting all of the current mount targets, the order of mount targets returned in the response is unspecified.
elasticfilesystem:DescribeMountTargets.Title: DescribeMountTargets

elasticfilesystem:DescribeTags.Description: Returns the tags associated with a file system. The order of tags returned in the response of one DescribeTags call and the order of tags returned across the responses of a multi-call iteration (when using pagination) is unspecified.
elasticfilesystem:DescribeTags.Title: DescribeTags

elasticfilesystem:ModifyMountTargetSecur.Description: Modifies the set of security groups in effect for a mount target.
elasticfilesystem:ModifyMountTargetSecur.Title: ModifyMountTargetSecurityGroups

elasticloadbalancing:AddTags.Description: Adds the specified tags to the specified Elastic Load Balancing resource. You can tag your Application Load Balancers, Network Load Balancers, and your target groups.
elasticloadbalancing:AddTags.Title: AddTags

elasticloadbalancing:ApplySecurityGroups.Description: Associates one or more security groups with your load balancer in a virtual private cloud (VPC). The specified security groups override the previously associated security groups.
elasticloadbalancing:ApplySecurityGroups.Title: ApplySecurityGroupsToLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:AttachLoadBalancerT.Description: Adds one or more subnets to the set of configured subnets for the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:AttachLoadBalancerT.Title: AttachLoadBalancerToSubnets

elasticloadbalancing:ConfigureHealthChec.Description: Specifies the health check settings to use when evaluating the health state of your EC2 instances.
elasticloadbalancing:ConfigureHealthChec.Title: ConfigureHealthCheck

elasticloadbalancing:CreateAppCookieStic.Description: Generates a stickiness policy with sticky session lifetimes that follow that of an application-generated cookie. This policy can be associated only with HTTP/HTTPS listeners.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateAppCookieStic.Title: CreateAppCookieStickinessPolicy

elasticloadbalancing:CreateLBCookieStick.Description: Generates a stickiness policy with sticky session lifetimes controlled by the lifetime of the browser (user-agent) or a specified expiration period. This policy can be associated only with HTTP/HTTPS listeners.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateLBCookieStick.Title: CreateLBCookieStickinessPolicy

elasticloadbalancing:CreateListener.Description: Creates a listener for the specified Application Load Balancer or Network Load Balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateListener.Title: CreateListener

elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancer.Description: Creates an Application Load Balancer or a Network Load Balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancer.Title: CreateLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancerL.Description: Creates one or more listeners for the specified load balancer. If a listener with the specified port does not already exist, it is created; otherwise, the properties of the new listener must match the properties of the existing listener.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancerL.Title: CreateLoadBalancerListeners

elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancerP.Description: Creates a policy with the specified attributes for the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateLoadBalancerP.Title: CreateLoadBalancerPolicy

elasticloadbalancing:CreateRule.Description: Creates a rule for the specified listener. The listener must be associated with an Application Load Balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:CreateRule.Title: CreateRule

elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancer.Description: Deletes the specified Application Load Balancer or Network Load Balancer and its attached listeners.
elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancer.Title: DeleteLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancerL.Description: Deletes the specified listeners from the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancerL.Title: DeleteLoadBalancerListeners

elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancerP.Description: Deletes the specified policy from the specified load balancer. This policy must not be enabled for any listeners.
elasticloadbalancing:DeleteLoadBalancerP.Title: DeleteLoadBalancerPolicy

elasticloadbalancing:DeregisterInstances.Description: Deregisters the specified instances from the specified load balancer. After the instance is deregistered, it no longer receives traffic from the load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DeregisterInstances.Title: DeregisterInstancesFromLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:DeregisterTargets.Description: Deregisters the specified targets from the specified target group. After the targets are deregistered, they no longer receive traffic from the load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DeregisterTargets.Title: DeregisterTargets

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeInstanceHea.Description: Describes the state of the specified instances with respect to the specified load balancer. If no instances are specified, the call describes the state of all instances that are currently registered with the load balancer. If instances are specified, their state is returned even if they are no longer registered with the load balancer. The state of terminated instances is not returned.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeInstanceHea.Title: DescribeInstanceHealth

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeListeners.Description: Describes the specified listeners or the listeners for the specified Application Load Balancer or Network Load Balancer. You must specify either a load balancer or one or more listeners.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeListeners.Title: DescribeListeners

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Description: Describes the attributes for the specified Application Load Balancer or Network Load Balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Title: DescribeLoadBalancerAttributes

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Description: Describes the specified load balancer policy types or all load balancer policy types.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Title: DescribeLoadBalancerPolicyTypes

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Description: Describes the specified load balancers or all of your load balancers.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeLoadBalance.Title: DescribeLoadBalancers

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeRules.Description: Describes the specified rules or the rules for the specified listener. You must specify either a listener or one or more rules.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeRules.Title: DescribeRules

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeSSLPolicies.Description: Describes the specified policies or all policies used for SSL negotiation.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeSSLPolicies.Title: DescribeSSLPolicies

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTags.Description: Describes the tags for the specified resources. You can describe the tags for one or more Application Load Balancers, Network Load Balancers, and target groups.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTags.Title: DescribeTags

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetGroup.Description: Describes the attributes for the specified target group.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetGroup.Title: DescribeTargetGroupAttributes

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetGroup.Description: Describes the specified target groups or all of your target groups. By default, all target groups are described. Alternatively, you can specify one of the following to filter the results: the ARN of the load balancer, the names of one or more target groups, or the ARNs of one or more target groups.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetGroup.Title: DescribeTargetGroups

elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetHealt.Description: Describes the health of the specified targets or all of your targets.
elasticloadbalancing:DescribeTargetHealt.Title: DescribeTargetHealth

elasticloadbalancing:DetachLoadBalancerF.Description: Removes the specified subnets from the set of configured subnets for the load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DetachLoadBalancerF.Title: DetachLoadBalancerFromSubnets

elasticloadbalancing:DisableAvailability.Description: Removes the specified Availability Zones from the set of Availability Zones for the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:DisableAvailability.Title: DisableAvailabilityZonesForLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:EnableAvailabilityZ.Description: Adds the specified Availability Zones to the set of Availability Zones for the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:EnableAvailabilityZ.Title: EnableAvailabilityZonesForLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:ModifyListener.Description: Modifies the specified properties of the specified listener.
elasticloadbalancing:ModifyListener.Title: ModifyListener

elasticloadbalancing:ModifyLoadBalancerA.Description: Modifies the specified attributes of the specified Application Load Balancer or Network Load Balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:ModifyLoadBalancerA.Title: ModifyLoadBalancerAttributes

elasticloadbalancing:ModifyTargetGroup.Description: Modifies the health checks used when evaluating the health state of the targets in the specified target group.
elasticloadbalancing:ModifyTargetGroup.Title: ModifyTargetGroup

elasticloadbalancing:ModifyTargetGroupAt.Description: Modifies the specified attributes of the specified target group.
elasticloadbalancing:ModifyTargetGroupAt.Title: ModifyTargetGroupAttributes

elasticloadbalancing:RegisterInstancesWi.Description: Adds the specified instances to the specified load balancer.
elasticloadbalancing:RegisterInstancesWi.Title: RegisterInstancesWithLoadBalancer

elasticloadbalancing:RegisterTargets.Description: Registers the specified targets with the specified target group.
elasticloadbalancing:RegisterTargets.Title: RegisterTargets

elasticloadbalancing:RemoveTags.Description: Removes the specified tags from the specified Elastic Load Balancing resource.
elasticloadbalancing:RemoveTags.Title: RemoveTags

elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerList.Description: Sets the certificate that terminates the specified listener's SSL connections. The specified certificate replaces any prior certificate that was used on the same load balancer and port.
elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerList.Title: SetLoadBalancerListenerSSLCertificate

elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerPoli.Description: Replaces the set of policies associated with the specified port on which the EC2 instance is listening with a new set of policies. At this time, only the back-end server authentication policy type can be applied to the instance ports; this policy type is composed of multiple public key policies.
elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerPoli.Title: SetLoadBalancerPoliciesForBackendServer

elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerPoli.Description: Replaces the current set of policies for the specified load balancer port with the specified set of policies.
elasticloadbalancing:SetLoadBalancerPoli.Title: SetLoadBalancerPoliciesOfListener

elasticloadbalancing:SetRulePriorities.Description: Sets the priorities of the specified rules.
elasticloadbalancing:SetRulePriorities.Title: SetRulePriorities

elasticloadbalancing:SetSecurityGroups.Description: Associates the specified security groups with the specified Application Load Balancer. The specified security groups override the previously associated security groups.
elasticloadbalancing:SetSecurityGroups.Title: SetSecurityGroups

elasticloadbalancing:SetSubnets.Description: Enables the Availability Zone for the specified subnets for the specified Application Load Balancer. The specified subnets replace the previously enabled subnets.
elasticloadbalancing:SetSubnets.Title: SetSubnets

elasticmapreduce:AddInstanceGroups.Description: Adds one or more instance groups to a running cluster.
elasticmapreduce:AddInstanceGroups.Title: AddInstanceGroups

elasticmapreduce:AddJobFlowSteps.Description: AddJobFlowSteps adds new steps to a running cluster. A maximum of 256 steps are allowed in each job flow.
elasticmapreduce:AddJobFlowSteps.Title: AddJobFlowSteps

elasticmapreduce:AddTags.Description: Adds tags to an Amazon EMR resource. Tags make it easier to associate clusters in various ways, such as grouping clusters to track your Amazon EMR resource allocation costs. For more information, see Tagging Amazon EMR Resources.
elasticmapreduce:AddTags.Title: AddTags

elasticmapreduce:CreateSecurityConfigura.Description: Creates a security configuration, which is stored in the service and can be specified when a cluster is created.
elasticmapreduce:CreateSecurityConfigura.Title: CreateSecurityConfiguration
