inspector:DescribeFindings.Description: Describes the findings that are specified by the ARNs of the findings.
inspector:DescribeFindings.Title: DescribeFindings

inspector:DescribeResourceGroups.Description: Describes the resource groups that are specified by the ARNs of the resource groups.
inspector:DescribeResourceGroups.Title: DescribeResourceGroups

inspector:DescribeRulesPackages.Description: Describes the rules packages that are specified by the ARNs of the rules packages.
inspector:DescribeRulesPackages.Title: DescribeRulesPackages

inspector:GetTelemetryMetadata.Description: Information about the data that is collected for the specified assessment run.
inspector:GetTelemetryMetadata.Title: GetTelemetryMetadata

inspector:ListAssessmentRunAgents.Description: Lists the agents of the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.
inspector:ListAssessmentRunAgents.Title: ListAssessmentRunAgents

inspector:ListAssessmentRuns.Description: Lists the assessment runs that correspond to the assessment templates that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment templates.
inspector:ListAssessmentRuns.Title: ListAssessmentRuns

inspector:ListAssessmentTargets.Description: Lists the ARNs of the assessment targets within this AWS account. For more information about assessment targets, see Amazon Inspector Assessment Targets.
inspector:ListAssessmentTargets.Title: ListAssessmentTargets

inspector:ListAssessmentTemplates.Description: Lists the assessment templates that correspond to the assessment targets that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment targets.
inspector:ListAssessmentTemplates.Title: ListAssessmentTemplates

inspector:ListEventSubscriptions.Description: Lists all the event subscriptions for the assessment template that is specified by the ARN of the assessment template. For more information, see SubscribeToEvent and UnsubscribeFromEvent.
inspector:ListEventSubscriptions.Title: ListEventSubscriptions

inspector:ListFindings.Description: Lists findings that are generated by the assessment runs that are specified by the ARNs of the assessment runs.
inspector:ListFindings.Title: ListFindings

inspector:ListRulesPackages.Description: Lists all available Amazon Inspector rules packages.
inspector:ListRulesPackages.Title: ListRulesPackages

inspector:ListTagsForResource.Description: Lists all tags associated with an assessment template.
inspector:ListTagsForResource.Title: ListTagsForResource

inspector:PreviewAgents.Description: Previews the agents installed on the EC2 instances that are part of the specified assessment target.
inspector:PreviewAgents.Title: PreviewAgents

inspector:RegisterCrossAccountAccessRole.Description: Registers the IAM role that Amazon Inspector uses to list your EC2 instances at the start of the assessment run or when you call the PreviewAgents action.
inspector:RegisterCrossAccountAccessRole.Title: RegisterCrossAccountAccessRole

inspector:RemoveAttributesFromFindings.Description: Removes entire attributes (key and value pairs) from the findings that are specified by the ARNs of the findings where an attribute with the specified key exists.
inspector:RemoveAttributesFromFindings.Title: RemoveAttributesFromFindings

inspector:SetTagsForResource.Description: Sets tags (key and value pairs) to the assessment template that is specified by the ARN of the assessment template.
inspector:SetTagsForResource.Title: SetTagsForResource

inspector:StartAssessmentRun.Description: Starts the assessment run specified by the ARN of the assessment template. For this API to function properly, you must not exceed the limit of running up to 500 concurrent agents per AWS account.
inspector:StartAssessmentRun.Title: StartAssessmentRun

inspector:StopAssessmentRun.Description: Stops the assessment run that is specified by the ARN of the assessment run.
inspector:StopAssessmentRun.Title: StopAssessmentRun

inspector:SubscribeToEvent.Description: Enables the process of sending Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS) notifications about a specified event to a specified SNS topic.
inspector:SubscribeToEvent.Title: SubscribeToEvent

inspector:UnsubscribeFromEvent.Description: Disables the process of sending Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS) notifications about a specified event to a specified SNS topic.
inspector:UnsubscribeFromEvent.Title: UnsubscribeFromEvent

inspector:UpdateAssessmentTarget.Description: Updates the assessment target that is specified by the ARN of the assessment target.
inspector:UpdateAssessmentTarget.Title: UpdateAssessmentTarget

iot:AcceptCertificateTransfer.Description: Accepts a pending certificate transfer. The default state of the certificate is INACTIVE.
iot:AcceptCertificateTransfer.Title: AcceptCertificateTransfer

iot:AttachPrincipalPolicy.Description: Attaches the specified policy to the specified principal (certificate or other credential).
iot:AttachPrincipalPolicy.Title: AttachPrincipalPolicy

iot:AttachThingPrincipal.Description: Attaches the specified principal to the specified thing.
iot:AttachThingPrincipal.Title: AttachThingPrincipal

iot:CancelCertificateTransfer.Description: Cancels a pending transfer for the specified certificate.
iot:CancelCertificateTransfer.Title: CancelCertificateTransfer

iot:Connect.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:Connect.Title: Authorization

iot:CreateCertificateFromCsr.Description: Creates an X.509 certificate using the specified certificate signing request.
iot:CreateCertificateFromCsr.Title: CreateCertificateFromCsr

iot:CreateKeysAndCertificate.Description: Creates a 2048-bit RSA key pair and issues an X.509 certificate using the issued public key.
iot:CreateKeysAndCertificate.Title: CreateKeysAndCertificate

iot:CreatePolicyVersion.Description: Creates a new version of the specified AWS IoT policy. To update a policy, create a new policy version. A managed policy can have up to five versions. If the policy has five versions, you must use DeletePolicyVersion to delete an existing version before you create a new one.
iot:CreatePolicyVersion.Title: CreatePolicyVersion

iot:CreateThing.Description: Creates a thing record in the thing registry.
iot:CreateThing.Title: CreateThing

iot:CreateTopicRule.Description: Creates a rule. Creating rules is an administrator-level action. Any user who has permission to create rules will be able to access data processed by the rule.
iot:CreateTopicRule.Title: CreateTopicRule

iot:DeletePolicyVersion.Description: Deletes the specified version of the specified policy. You cannot delete the default version of a policy using this API. To delete the default version of a policy, use DeletePolicy. To find out which version of a policy is marked as the default version, use ListPolicyVersions.
iot:DeletePolicyVersion.Title: DeletePolicyVersion

iot:DeleteRegistrationCode.Description: Deletes a CA certificate registration code.
iot:DeleteRegistrationCode.Title: DeleteRegistrationCode

iot:DeleteThingShadow.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:DeleteThingShadow.Title: Authorization

iot:DeleteThingType.Description: Deletes the specified thing type . You cannot delete a thing type if it has things associated with it. To delete a thing type, first mark it as deprecated by calling DeprecateThingType, then remove any associated things by calling UpdateThing to change the thing type on any associated thing, and finally use DeleteThingType to delete the thing type.
iot:DeleteThingType.Title: DeleteThingType

iot:DeprecateThingType.Description: Deprecates a thing type. You can not associate new things with deprecated thing type.
iot:DeprecateThingType.Title: DeprecateThingType

iot:DescribeCertificate.Description: Gets information about the specified certificate. You may specify the certificate using either its ID or PEM.
iot:DescribeCertificate.Title: DescribeCertificate

iot:DescribeEndpoint.Description: Returns a unique endpoint specific to the AWS account making the call.
iot:DescribeEndpoint.Title: DescribeEndpoint

iot:DescribeThing.Description: Gets information about the specified thing.
iot:DescribeThing.Title: DescribeThing

iot:DescribeThingType.Description: Gets information about the specified thing type.
iot:DescribeThingType.Title: DescribeThingType

iot:DetachPrincipalPolicy.Description: Removes the specified policy from the specified certificate.
iot:DetachPrincipalPolicy.Title: DetachPrincipalPolicy

iot:DetachThingPrincipal.Description: Detaches the specified principal from the specified thing.
iot:DetachThingPrincipal.Title: DetachThingPrincipal

iot:GetPolicy.Description: Gets information about the specified policy with the policy document of the default version.
iot:GetPolicy.Title: GetPolicy

iot:GetPolicyVersion.Description: Gets information about the specified policy version.
iot:GetPolicyVersion.Title: GetPolicyVersion

iot:GetRegistrationCode.Description: Gets a registration code used to register a CA certificate with AWS IoT.
iot:GetRegistrationCode.Title: GetRegistrationCode

iot:GetThingShadow.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:GetThingShadow.Title: Authorization

iot:GetTopicRule.Description: Gets information about the specified rule.
iot:GetTopicRule.Title: GetTopicRule

iot:ListCertificates.Description: Lists the certificates registered in your AWS account.
iot:ListCertificates.Title: ListCertificates

iot:ListOutgoingCertificates.Description: Lists certificates that are being transfered but not yet accepted.
iot:ListOutgoingCertificates.Title: ListOutgoingCertificates

iot:ListPolicyPrincipals.Description: Lists the principals associated with the specified policy.
iot:ListPolicyPrincipals.Title: ListPolicyPrincipals

iot:ListPolicyVersions.Description: Lists the versions of the specified policy and identifies the default version.
iot:ListPolicyVersions.Title: ListPolicyVersions

iot:ListPrincipalPolicies.Description: Lists the policies attached to the specified principal. If you use an Cognito identity, the ID must be in AmazonCognito Identity format.
iot:ListPrincipalPolicies.Title: ListPrincipalPolicies

iot:ListPrincipalThings.Description: Lists the things associated with the specified principal.
iot:ListPrincipalThings.Title: ListPrincipalThings

iot:ListThingPrincipals.Description: Lists the principals associated with the specified thing.
iot:ListThingPrincipals.Title: ListThingPrincipals

iot:ListThings.Description: Lists your things. Use the attributeName and attributeValue parameters to filter your things. For example, calling ListThings with attributeName=Color and attributeValue=Red retrieves all things in the registry that contain an attribute Color with the value Red.
iot:ListThings.Title: ListThings

iot:ListTopicRules.Description: Lists the rules for the specific topic.
iot:ListTopicRules.Title: ListTopicRules

iot:Publish.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:Publish.Title: Authorization

iot:Receive.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:Receive.Title: Authorization

iot:RegisterCACertificate.Description: Registers a CA certificate with AWS IoT. This CA certificate can then be used to sign device certificates, which can be then registered with AWS IoT. You can register up to 10 CA certificates per AWS account that have the same subject field. This enables you to have up to 10 certificate authorities sign your device certificates. If you have more than one CA certificate registered, make sure you pass the CA certificate when you register your device certificates with the RegisterCertificate API.
iot:RegisterCACertificate.Title: RegisterCACertificate

iot:RegisterCertificate.Description: Registers a device certificate with AWS IoT. If you have more than one CA certificate that has the same subject field, you must specify the CA certificate that was used to sign the device certificate being registered.
iot:RegisterCertificate.Title: RegisterCertificate

iot:RejectCertificateTransfer.Description: Rejects a pending certificate transfer. After AWS IoT rejects a certificate transfer, the certificate status changes from PENDING_TRANSFER to INACTIVE.
iot:RejectCertificateTransfer.Title: RejectCertificateTransfer

iot:ReplaceTopicRule.Description: Replaces the specified rule. You must specify all parameters for the new rule. Creating rules is an administrator-level action. Any user who has permission to create rules will be able to access data processed by the rule.
iot:ReplaceTopicRule.Title: ReplaceTopicRule

iot:SetDefaultPolicyVersion.Description: Sets the specified version of the specified policy as the policy's default (operative) version. This action affects all certificates to which the policy is attached. To list the principals the policy is attached to, use the ListPrincipalPolicy API.
iot:SetDefaultPolicyVersion.Title: SetDefaultPolicyVersion

iot:Subscribe.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:Subscribe.Title: Authorization

iot:TransferCertificate.Description: Transfers the specified certificate to the specified AWS account.
iot:TransferCertificate.Title: TransferCertificate

iot:UpdateCertificate.Description: Updates the status of the specified certificate. This operation is idempotent.
iot:UpdateCertificate.Title: UpdateCertificate

iot:UpdateThing.Description: Updates the data for a thing.
iot:UpdateThing.Title: UpdateThing

iot:UpdateThingShadow.Description: Policies determine what an authenticated identity can do. An authenticated identity is used by devices, mobile applications, web applications, and desktop applications. An authenticated identity can even be a user typing AWS IoT CLI commands. The identity can execute AWS IoT operations only if it has a policy that grants it permission.
iot:UpdateThingShadow.Title: Authorization

kinesis:AddTagsToStream.Description: Adds or updates tags for the specified Amazon Kinesis stream. Each stream can have up to 50 tags. However, each call to AddTagsToStream can take only up to 10 tags. Therefore, if you want to add more than 10 tags to your stream, you must call this API more than once. You can call it multiple times, but you can't have more than 50 tags on a stream at any given time.
kinesis:AddTagsToStream.Title: AddTagsToStream

kinesis:CreateStream.Description: Creates an Amazon Kinesis stream. A stream captures and transports data records that are continuously emitted from different data sources or producers. Scale-out within a stream is explicitly supported by means of shards, which are uniquely identified groups of data records in a stream.
kinesis:CreateStream.Title: CreateStream

kinesis:DecreaseStreamRetentionPeriod.Description: Decreases the Amazon Kinesis stream's retention period, which is the length of time data records are accessible after they are added to the stream. The minimum value of a stream's retention period is 24 hours.
kinesis:DecreaseStreamRetentionPeriod.Title: DecreaseStreamRetentionPeriod

kinesis:DeleteStream.Description: Deletes an Amazon Kinesis stream and all its shards and data. You must shut down any applications that are operating on the stream before you delete the stream. If an application attempts to operate on a deleted stream, it will receive the exception ResourceNotFoundException.
kinesis:DeleteStream.Title: DeleteStream

kinesis:DescribeLimits.Description: Describes the shard limits and usage for the account.
kinesis:DescribeLimits.Title: DescribeLimits

kinesis:DescribeStream.Description: Describes the specified Amazon Kinesis stream.
kinesis:DescribeStream.Title: DescribeStream

kinesis:EnableEnhancedMonitoring.Description: Enables enhanced Amazon Kinesis stream monitoring for shard-level metrics.
kinesis:EnableEnhancedMonitoring.Title: EnableEnhancedMonitoring

kinesis:GetRecords.Description: Gets data records from an Amazon Kinesis stream's shard.
kinesis:GetRecords.Title: GetRecords

kinesis:GetShardIterator.Description: Gets an Amazon Kinesis shard iterator. A shard iterator expires five minutes after it is returned to the requester.
kinesis:GetShardIterator.Title: GetShardIterator

kinesis:IncreaseStreamRetentionPeriod.Description: Increases the Amazon Kinesis stream's retention period, which is the length of time data records are accessible after they are added to the stream. The maximum value of a stream's retention period is 168 hours (7 days).
kinesis:IncreaseStreamRetentionPeriod.Title: IncreaseStreamRetentionPeriod

kinesis:ListTagsForStream.Description: Lists the tags for the specified Amazon Kinesis stream.
kinesis:ListTagsForStream.Title: ListTagsForStream

kinesis:MergeShards.Description: Merges two adjacent shards in an Amazon Kinesis stream and combines them into a single shard to reduce the stream's capacity to ingest and transport data. Two shards are considered adjacent if the union of the hash key ranges for the two shards form a contiguous set with no gaps. For example, if you have two shards, one with a hash key range of 276...381 and the other with a hash key range of 382...454, then you could merge these two shards into a single shard that would have a hash key range of 276...454. After the merge, the single child shard receives data for all hash key values covered by the two parent shards.
kinesis:MergeShards.Title: MergeShards

kinesis:PutRecord.Description: Writes a single data record into an Amazon Kinesis stream. Call PutRecord to send data into the stream for real-time ingestion and subsequent processing, one record at a time. Each shard can support writes up to 1,000 records per second, up to a maximum data write total of 1 MB per second.
kinesis:PutRecord.Title: PutRecord

kinesis:PutRecords.Description: Writes multiple data records into an Amazon Kinesis stream in a single call (also referred to as a PutRecords request). Use this operation to send data into the stream for data ingestion and processing.
kinesis:PutRecords.Title: PutRecords

kinesis:RemoveTagsFromStream.Description: Removes tags from the specified Amazon Kinesis stream. Removed tags are deleted and cannot be recovered after this operation successfully completes.
kinesis:RemoveTagsFromStream.Title: RemoveTagsFromStream

kinesis:SplitShard.Description: Splits a shard into two new shards in the Amazon Kinesis stream to increase the stream's capacity to ingest and transport data. SplitShard is called when there is a need to increase the overall capacity of a stream because of an expected increase in the volume of data records being ingested.
kinesis:SplitShard.Title: SplitShard

kinesis:StartStreamEncryption.Description: Enables or updates server-side encryption using an AWS KMS key for a specified stream.
kinesis:StartStreamEncryption.Title: StartStreamEncryption

kinesis:StopStreamEncryption.Description: Disables server-side encryption for a specified stream.
kinesis:StopStreamEncryption.Title: StopStreamEncryption

kinesis:UpdateShardCount.Description: Updates the shard count of the specified stream to the specified number of shards.
kinesis:UpdateShardCount.Title: UpdateShardCount

kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationInput.Description: Adds a streaming source to your Amazon Kinesis application. For conceptual information, see Configuring Application Input.
kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationInput.Title: AddApplicationInput

kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationOutput.Description: Adds an external destination to your Amazon Kinesis Analytics application.
kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationOutput.Title: AddApplicationOutput

kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationReference.Description: Adds a reference data source to an existing application.
kinesisanalytics:AddApplicationReference.Title: AddApplicationReferenceDataSource

kinesisanalytics:CreateApplication.Description: Creates an Amazon Kinesis Analytics application. You can configure each application with one streaming source as input, application code to process the input, and up to five streaming destinations where you want Amazon Kinesis Analytics to write the output data from your application. For an overview, see How it Works.
kinesisanalytics:CreateApplication.Title: CreateApplication

kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplication.Description: Deletes the specified application. Amazon Kinesis Analytics halts application execution and deletes the application, including any application artifacts (such as in-application streams, reference table, and application code).
kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplication.Title: DeleteApplication

kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplicationOutput.Description: Deletes output destination configuration from your application configuration. Amazon Kinesis Analytics will no longer write data from the corresponding in-application stream to the external output destination.
kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplicationOutput.Title: DeleteApplicationOutput

kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplicationRefere.Description: Deletes a reference data source configuration from the specified application configuration.
kinesisanalytics:DeleteApplicationRefere.Title: DeleteApplicationReferenceDataSource

kinesisanalytics:DescribeApplication.Description: Returns information about a specific Amazon Kinesis Analytics application.
kinesisanalytics:DescribeApplication.Title: DescribeApplication

kinesisanalytics:DiscoverInputSchema.Description: Infers a schema by evaluating sample records on the specified streaming source (Amazon Kinesis stream or Amazon Kinesis Firehose delivery stream). In the response, the operation returns the inferred schema and also the sample records that the operation used to infer the schema.
kinesisanalytics:DiscoverInputSchema.Title: DiscoverInputSchema

kinesisanalytics:ListApplications.Description: Returns a list of Amazon Kinesis Analytics applications in your account. For each application, the response includes the application name, Amazon Resource Name (ARN), and status. If the response returns the HasMoreApplications value as true, you can send another request by adding the ExclusiveStartApplicationName in the request body, and set the value of this to the last application name from the previous response.
kinesisanalytics:ListApplications.Title: ListApplications

kinesisanalytics:StartApplication.Description: Starts the specified Amazon Kinesis Analytics application. After creating an application, you must exclusively call this operation to start your application.
kinesisanalytics:StartApplication.Title: StartApplication

kinesisanalytics:StopApplication.Description: Stops the application from processing input data. You can stop an application only if it is in the running state. You can use the DescribeApplication operation to find the application state. After the application is stopped, Amazon Kinesis Analytics stops reading data from the input, the application stops processing data, and there is no output written to the destination.
kinesisanalytics:StopApplication.Title: StopApplication

kinesisanalytics:UpdateApplication.Description: Updates an existing Amazon Kinesis Analytics application. Using this API, you can update application code, input configuration, and output configuration.
kinesisanalytics:UpdateApplication.Title: UpdateApplication

kms:BypassPolicyLockoutSafetyCheck.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:BypassPolicyLockoutSafetyCheck.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:CallerAccount.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:CallerAccount.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:CancelKeyDeletion.Description: Cancels the deletion of a customer master key (CMK). When this operation is successful, the CMK is set to the Disabled state. To enable a CMK, use EnableKey. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:CancelKeyDeletion.Title: CancelKeyDeletion

kms:CreateAlias.Description: Creates a display name for a customer master key (CMK). You can use an alias to identify a CMK in selected operations, such as Encrypt and GenerateDataKey.
kms:CreateAlias.Title: CreateAlias

kms:CreateGrant.Description: Adds a grant to a customer master key (CMK). The grant specifies who can use the CMK and under what conditions. When setting permissions, grants are an alternative to key policies.
kms:CreateGrant.Title: CreateGrant

kms:CreateKey.Description: Creates a customer master key (CMK) in the caller's AWS account.
kms:CreateKey.Title: CreateKey

kms:Decrypt.Description: Decrypts ciphertext. Ciphertext is plaintext that has been previously encrypted by using any of the following operations:
kms:Decrypt.Title: Decrypt

kms:DeleteAlias.Description: Deletes the specified alias. You cannot perform this operation on an alias in a different AWS account.
kms:DeleteAlias.Title: DeleteAlias

kms:DeleteImportedKeyMaterial.Description: Deletes key material that you previously imported. This operation makes the specified customer master key (CMK) unusable. For more information about importing key material into AWS KMS, see Importing Key Material in the AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:DeleteImportedKeyMaterial.Title: DeleteImportedKeyMaterial

kms:DescribeKey.Description: Provides detailed information about the specified customer master key (CMK).
kms:DescribeKey.Title: DescribeKey

kms:DisableKey.Description: Sets the state of a customer master key (CMK) to disabled, thereby preventing its use for cryptographic operations. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:DisableKey.Title: DisableKey

kms:DisableKeyRotation.Description: Disables automatic rotation of the key material for the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:DisableKeyRotation.Title: DisableKeyRotation

kms:EnableKey.Description: Sets the state of a customer master key (CMK) to enabled, thereby permitting its use for cryptographic operations. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:EnableKey.Title: EnableKey

kms:EnableKeyRotation.Description: Enables automatic rotation of the key material for the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:EnableKeyRotation.Title: EnableKeyRotation

kms:Encrypt.Description: Encrypts plaintext into ciphertext by using a customer master key (CMK). The Encrypt operation has two primary use cases:
kms:Encrypt.Title: Encrypt

kms:EncryptionContext.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:EncryptionContext.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:EncryptionContextKeys.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:EncryptionContextKeys.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:GenerateDataKey.Description: Returns a data encryption key that you can use in your application to encrypt data locally.
kms:GenerateDataKey.Title: GenerateDataKey

kms:GenerateDataKeyWithoutPlaintext.Description: Returns a data encryption key encrypted under a customer master key (CMK). This operation is identical to GenerateDataKey but returns only the encrypted copy of the data key.
kms:GenerateDataKeyWithoutPlaintext.Title: GenerateDataKeyWithoutPlaintext

kms:GenerateRandom.Description: Returns a random byte string that is cryptographically secure.
kms:GenerateRandom.Title: GenerateRandom

kms:GetKeyPolicy.Description: Gets a key policy attached to the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:GetKeyPolicy.Title: GetKeyPolicy

kms:GetKeyRotationStatus.Description: Gets a Boolean value that indicates whether automatic rotation of the key material is enabled for the specified customer master key (CMK).
kms:GetKeyRotationStatus.Title: GetKeyRotationStatus

kms:GetParametersForImport.Description: Returns the items you need in order to import key material into AWS KMS from your existing key management infrastructure. For more information about importing key material into AWS KMS, see Importing Key Material in the AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide.
kms:GetParametersForImport.Title: GetParametersForImport

kms:GrantConstraintType.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:GrantConstraintType.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:GrantIsForAWSResource.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:GrantIsForAWSResource.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:GrantOperations.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:GrantOperations.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:ImportKeyMaterial.Description: Imports key material into an existing AWS KMS customer master key (CMK) that was created without key material. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account. For more information about creating CMKs with no key material and then importing key material, see Importing Key Material in the AWS Key Management Service Developer Guide.
kms:ImportKeyMaterial.Title: ImportKeyMaterial

kms:ListAliases.Description: Gets a list of all aliases in the caller's AWS account and region. You cannot list aliases in other accounts. For more information about aliases, see CreateAlias.
kms:ListAliases.Title: ListAliases

kms:ListGrants.Description: Gets a list of all grants for the specified customer master key (CMK).
kms:ListGrants.Title: ListGrants

kms:ListKeyPolicies.Description: Gets the names of the key policies that are attached to a customer master key (CMK). This operation is designed to get policy names that you can use in a GetKeyPolicy operation. However, the only valid policy name is default. You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:ListKeyPolicies.Title: ListKeyPolicies

kms:ListKeys.Description: Gets a list of all customer master keys (CMKs) in the caller's AWS account and region.
kms:ListKeys.Title: ListKeys

kms:ListResourceTags.Description: Returns a list of all tags for the specified customer master key (CMK).
kms:ListResourceTags.Title: ListResourceTags

kms:ListRetirableGrants.Description: Returns a list of all grants for which the grant's RetiringPrincipal matches the one specified.
kms:ListRetirableGrants.Title: ListRetirableGrants

kms:PutKeyPolicy.Description: Attaches a key policy to the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:PutKeyPolicy.Title: PutKeyPolicy

kms:ReEncryptOnSameKey.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:ReEncryptOnSameKey.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

kms:RevokeGrant.Description: Revokes the specified grant for the specified customer master key (CMK). You can revoke a grant to actively deny operations that depend on it.
kms:RevokeGrant.Title: RevokeGrant

kms:ScheduleKeyDeletion.Description: Schedules the deletion of a customer master key (CMK). You may provide a waiting period, specified in days, before deletion occurs. If you do not provide a waiting period, the default period of 30 days is used. When this operation is successful, the state of the CMK changes to PendingDeletion. Before the waiting period ends, you can use CancelKeyDeletion to cancel the deletion of the CMK. After the waiting period ends, AWS KMS deletes the CMK and all AWS KMS data associated with it, including all aliases that refer to it.
kms:ScheduleKeyDeletion.Title: ScheduleKeyDeletion

kms:TagResource.Description: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:TagResource.Title: TagResource

kms:UntagResource.Description: Removes the specified tag or tags from the specified customer master key (CMK). You cannot perform this operation on a CMK in a different AWS account.
kms:UntagResource.Title: UntagResource

kms:UpdateAlias.Description: Associates an existing alias with a different customer master key (CMK). Each CMK can have multiple aliases, but the aliases must be unique within the account and region. You cannot perform this operation on an alias in a different AWS account.
kms:UpdateAlias.Title: UpdateAlias

kms:UpdateKeyDescription.Description: Updates the description of a customer master key (CMK). To see the decription of a CMK, use DescribeKey.
kms:UpdateKeyDescription.Title: UpdateKeyDescription

kms:ViaService.Description: When you use key policies and IAM policies to control access to your AWS KMS resources, you can use a policy statement's Condition element to specify the circumstances in which the statement takes effect. For example, you might want a policy statement to take effect only after a specific date. Or, you might want a policy statement to control access based on whether a specific value exists in the API request.
kms:ViaService.Title: Using Policy Conditions with AWS KMS

lambda:AddPermission.Description: Adds a permission to the resource policy associated with the specified AWS Lambda function. You use resource policies to grant permissions to event sources that use push model. In a push model, event sources (such as Amazon S3 and custom applications) invoke your Lambda function. Each permission you add to the resource policy allows an event source, permission to invoke the Lambda function.
lambda:AddPermission.Title: AddPermission

lambda:CreateAlias.Description: Creates an alias that points to the specified Lambda function version. For more information, see Introduction to AWS Lambda Aliases.
lambda:CreateAlias.Title: CreateAlias

lambda:CreateEventSourceMapping.Description: Identifies a stream as an event source for a Lambda function. It can be either an Amazon Kinesis stream or an Amazon DynamoDB stream. AWS Lambda invokes the specified function when records are posted to the stream.
lambda:CreateEventSourceMapping.Title: CreateEventSourceMapping

lambda:CreateFunction.Description: Creates a new Lambda function. The function metadata is created from the request parameters, and the code for the function is provided by a .zip file in the request body. If the function name already exists, the operation will fail. Note that the function name is case-sensitive.
lambda:CreateFunction.Title: CreateFunction

lambda:DeleteAlias.Description: Deletes the specified Lambda function alias. For more information, see Introduction to AWS Lambda Aliases.
lambda:DeleteAlias.Title: DeleteAlias

lambda:DeleteEventSourceMapping.Description: Removes an event source mapping. This means AWS Lambda will no longer invoke the function for events in the associated source.
lambda:DeleteEventSourceMapping.Title: DeleteEventSourceMapping

lambda:DeleteFunction.Description: Deletes the specified Lambda function code and configuration.
lambda:DeleteFunction.Title: DeleteFunction

lambda:GetAlias.Description: Returns the specified alias information such as the alias ARN, description, and function version it is pointing to. For more information, see Introduction to AWS Lambda Aliases.
lambda:GetAlias.Title: GetAlias

lambda:GetEventSourceMapping.Description: Returns configuration information for the specified event source mapping (see CreateEventSourceMapping).
lambda:GetEventSourceMapping.Title: GetEventSourceMapping

lambda:GetFunction.Description: Returns the configuration information of the Lambda function and a presigned URL link to the .zip file you uploaded with CreateFunction so you can download the .zip file. Note that the URL is valid for up to 10 minutes. The configuration information is the same information you provided as parameters when uploading the function.
lambda:GetFunction.Title: GetFunction

lambda:GetFunctionConfiguration.Description: Returns the configuration information of the Lambda function. This the same information you provided as parameters when uploading the function by using CreateFunction.
lambda:GetFunctionConfiguration.Title: GetFunctionConfiguration

lambda:GetPolicy.Description: Returns the resource policy associated with the specified Lambda function.
lambda:GetPolicy.Title: GetPolicy

lambda:InvokeAsync.Description: Submits an invocation request to AWS Lambda. Upon receiving the request, Lambda executes the specified function asynchronously. To see the logs generated by the Lambda function execution, see the CloudWatch Logs console.
lambda:InvokeAsync.Title: InvokeAsync

lambda:InvokeFunction.Description: This topic provides examples of identity-based policies in which an account administrator can attach permissions policies to IAM identities (that is, users, groups, and roles).
lambda:InvokeFunction.Title:
Using Identity-Based Policies (IAM Policies)
                        for AWS Lambda

lambda:ListAliases.Description: Returns list of aliases created for a Lambda function. For each alias, the response includes information such as the alias ARN, description, alias name, and the function version to which it points. For more information, see Introduction to AWS Lambda Aliases.
lambda:ListAliases.Title: ListAliases

lambda:ListEventSourceMappings.Description: Returns a list of event source mappings you created using the CreateEventSourceMapping (see CreateEventSourceMapping).
lambda:ListEventSourceMappings.Title: ListEventSourceMappings

lambda:ListFunctions.Description: Returns a list of your Lambda functions. For each function, the response includes the function configuration information. You must use GetFunction to retrieve the code for your function.
lambda:ListFunctions.Title: ListFunctions

lambda:ListTags.Description: Returns a list of tags assigned to a function when supplied the function ARN (Amazon Resource Name).
lambda:ListTags.Title: ListTags

lambda:ListVersionsByFunction.Description: List all versions of a function. For information about the versioning feature, see AWS Lambda Function Versioning and Aliases.
lambda:ListVersionsByFunction.Title: ListVersionsByFunction

lambda:PublishVersion.Description: Publishes a version of your function from the current snapshot of $LATEST. That is, AWS Lambda takes a snapshot of the function code and configuration information from $LATEST and publishes a new version. The code and configuration cannot be modified after publication. For information about the versioning feature, see AWS Lambda Function Versioning and Aliases.
lambda:PublishVersion.Title: PublishVersion

lambda:RemovePermission.Description: You can remove individual permissions from an resource policy associated with a Lambda function by providing a statement ID that you provided when you added the permission.
lambda:RemovePermission.Title: RemovePermission

lambda:TagResource.Description: Creates a list of tags (key-value pairs) on the Lambda function. Requires the Lambda function ARN (Amazon Resource Name). If a key is specified without a value, Lambda creates a tag with the specified key and a value of null.
lambda:TagResource.Title: TagResource

lambda:UntagResource.Description: Removes tags from a Lambda function. Requires the function ARN (Amazon Resource Name).
lambda:UntagResource.Title: UntagResource

lambda:UpdateAlias.Description: Using this API you can update the function version to which the alias points and the alias description. For more information, see Introduction to AWS Lambda Aliases.
lambda:UpdateAlias.Title: UpdateAlias

lambda:UpdateEventSourceMapping.Description: You can update an event source mapping. This is useful if you want to change the parameters of the existing mapping without losing your position in the stream. You can change which function will receive the stream records, but to change the stream itself, you must create a new mapping.
lambda:UpdateEventSourceMapping.Title: UpdateEventSourceMapping

lambda:UpdateFunctionCode.Description: Updates the code for the specified Lambda function. This operation must only be used on an existing Lambda function and cannot be used to update the function configuration.
lambda:UpdateFunctionCode.Title: UpdateFunctionCode

lambda:UpdateFunctionConfiguration.Description: Updates the configuration parameters for the specified Lambda function by using the values provided in the request. You provide only the parameters you want to change. This operation must only be used on an existing Lambda function and cannot be used to update the function's code.
lambda:UpdateFunctionConfiguration.Title: UpdateFunctionConfiguration

lex:CreateBotVersion.Description: Creates a new version of the bot based on the $LATEST version. If the $LATEST version of this resource hasn't changed since you created the last version, Amazon Lex doesn't create a new version. It returns the last created version.
lex:CreateBotVersion.Title: CreateBotVersion

lex:CreateIntentVersion.Description: Creates a new version of an intent based on the $LATEST version of the intent. If the $LATEST version of this intent hasn't changed since you last updated it, Amazon Lex doesn't create a new version. It returns the last version you created.
lex:CreateIntentVersion.Title: CreateIntentVersion

lex:CreateSlotTypeVersion.Description: Creates a new version of a slot type based on the $LATEST version of the specified slot type. If the $LATEST version of this resource has not changed since the last version that you created, Amazon Lex doesn't create a new version. It returns the last version that you created.
lex:CreateSlotTypeVersion.Title: CreateSlotTypeVersion

lex:DeleteBot.Description: Deletes all versions of the bot, including the $LATEST version. To delete a specific version of the bot, use the DeleteBotVersion operation.
lex:DeleteBot.Title: DeleteBot

lex:DeleteBotAlias.Description: Deletes an alias for the specified bot.
lex:DeleteBotAlias.Title: DeleteBotAlias

lex:DeleteBotChannelAssociation.Description: Deletes the association between an Amazon Lex bot and a messaging platform.
lex:DeleteBotChannelAssociation.Title: DeleteBotChannelAssociation

lex:DeleteBotVersion.Description: Deletes a specific version of a bot. To delete all versions of a bot, use the DeleteBot operation.
lex:DeleteBotVersion.Title: DeleteBotVersion

lex:DeleteIntent.Description: Deletes all versions of the intent, including the $LATEST version. To delete a specific version of the intent, use the DeleteIntentVersion operation.
lex:DeleteIntent.Title: DeleteIntent

lex:DeleteIntentVersion.Description: Deletes a specific version of an intent. To delete all versions of a intent, use the DeleteIntent operation.
lex:DeleteIntentVersion.Title: DeleteIntentVersion

lex:DeleteSlotType.Description: Deletes all versions of the slot type, including the $LATEST version. To delete a specific version of the slot type, use the DeleteSlotTypeVersion operation.
lex:DeleteSlotType.Title: DeleteSlotType

lex:DeleteSlotTypeVersion.Description: Deletes a specific version of a slot type. To delete all versions of a slot type, use the DeleteSlotType operation.
lex:DeleteSlotTypeVersion.Title: DeleteSlotTypeVersion

lex:GetBot.Description: Returns metadata information for a specific bot. You must provide the bot name and the bot version or alias.
lex:GetBot.Title: GetBot

lex:GetBotAlias.Description: Returns information about an Amazon Lex bot alias. For more information about aliases, see Versioning and Aliases.
lex:GetBotAlias.Title: GetBotAlias

lex:GetBotAliases.Description: Returns a list of aliases for a specified Amazon Lex bot.
lex:GetBotAliases.Title: GetBotAliases

lex:GetBotChannelAssociation.Description: Returns information about the association between an Amazon Lex bot and a messaging platform.
lex:GetBotChannelAssociation.Title: GetBotChannelAssociation

lex:GetBotChannelAssociations.Description: Returns a list of all of the channels associated with the specified bot.
lex:GetBotChannelAssociations.Title: GetBotChannelAssociations

lex:GetBotVersions.Description: Gets information about all of the versions of a bot.
lex:GetBotVersions.Title: GetBotVersions

lex:GetBuiltinIntent.Description: Returns information about a built-in intent.
lex:GetBuiltinIntent.Title: GetBuiltinIntent

lex:GetBuiltinIntents.Description: Gets a list of built-in intents that meet the specified criteria.
lex:GetBuiltinIntents.Title: GetBuiltinIntents

lex:GetBuiltinSlotTypes.Description: Gets a list of built-in slot types that meet the specified criteria.
lex:GetBuiltinSlotTypes.Title: GetBuiltinSlotTypes

lex:GetIntent.Description: Returns information about an intent. In addition to the intent name, you must specify the intent version.
lex:GetIntent.Title: GetIntent

lex:GetIntentVersions.Description: Gets information about all of the versions of an intent.
lex:GetIntentVersions.Title: GetIntentVersions

lex:GetSlotType.Description: Returns information about a specific version of a slot type. In addition to specifying the slot type name, you must specify the slot type version.
lex:GetSlotType.Title: GetSlotType

lex:GetSlotTypeVersions.Description: Gets information about all versions of a slot type.
lex:GetSlotTypeVersions.Title: GetSlotTypeVersions

lex:GetSlotTypes.Description: Returns slot type information as follows:
lex:GetSlotTypes.Title: GetSlotTypes

lex:GetUtterancesView.Description: Use the GetUtterancesView operation to get information about the utterances that your users have made to your bot. You can use this list to tune the utterances that your bot responds to.
lex:GetUtterancesView.Title: GetUtterancesView

lex:PutBot.Description: Creates an Amazon Lex conversational bot or replaces an existing bot. When you create or update a bot you are only required to specify a name. You can use this to add intents later, or to remove intents from an existing bot. When you create a bot with a name only, the bot is created or updated but Amazon Lex returns the response FAILED. You can build the bot after you add one or more intents. For more information about Amazon Lex bots, see Amazon Lex: How It Works.
lex:PutBot.Title: PutBot

lex:PutBotAlias.Description: Creates an alias for the specified version of the bot or replaces an alias for the specified bot. To change the version of the bot that the alias points to, replace the alias. For more information about aliases, see Versioning and Aliases.
lex:PutBotAlias.Title: PutBotAlias

lex:PutIntent.Description: Creates an intent or replaces an existing intent.
lex:PutIntent.Title: PutIntent

lex:PutSlotType.Description: Creates a custom slot type or replaces an existing custom slot type.
lex:PutSlotType.Title: PutSlotType

lightsail:AttachStaticIp.Description: Attaches a static IP address to a specific Amazon Lightsail instance.
lightsail:AttachStaticIp.Title: AttachStaticIp

lightsail:CloseInstancePublicPorts.Description: Closes the public ports on a specific Amazon Lightsail instance.
lightsail:CloseInstancePublicPorts.Title: CloseInstancePublicPorts

lightsail:CreateDomain.Description: Creates a domain resource for the specified domain (e.g., example.com).
lightsail:CreateDomain.Title: CreateDomain

lightsail:CreateDomainEntry.Description: Creates one of the following entry records associated with the domain: A record, CNAME record, TXT record, or MX record.
lightsail:CreateDomainEntry.Title: CreateDomainEntry

lightsail:CreateInstanceSnapshot.Description: Creates a snapshot of a specific virtual private server, or instance. You can use a snapshot to create a new instance that is based on that snapshot.
lightsail:CreateInstanceSnapshot.Title: CreateInstanceSnapshot

lightsail:CreateInstances.Description: Creates one or more Amazon Lightsail virtual private servers, or instances.
lightsail:CreateInstances.Title: CreateInstances

lightsail:CreateInstancesFromSnapshot.Description: Uses a specific snapshot as a blueprint for creating one or more new instances that are based on that identical configuration.
lightsail:CreateInstancesFromSnapshot.Title: CreateInstancesFromSnapshot

lightsail:DeleteDomain.Description: Deletes the specified domain recordset and all of its domain records.
lightsail:DeleteDomain.Title: DeleteDomain

lightsail:DeleteInstance.Description: Deletes a specific Amazon Lightsail virtual private server, or instance.
lightsail:DeleteInstance.Title: DeleteInstance

lightsail:DeleteInstanceSnapshot.Description: Deletes a specific snapshot of a virtual private server (or instance).
lightsail:DeleteInstanceSnapshot.Title: DeleteInstanceSnapshot

lightsail:DeleteKeyPair.Description: Deletes a specific SSH key pair.
lightsail:DeleteKeyPair.Title: DeleteKeyPair

lightsail:DetachStaticIp.Description: Detaches a static IP from the Amazon Lightsail instance to which it is attached.
lightsail:DetachStaticIp.Title: DetachStaticIp

lightsail:DownloadDefaultKeyPair.Description: Downloads the default SSH key pair from the user's account.
lightsail:DownloadDefaultKeyPair.Title: DownloadDefaultKeyPair

lightsail:GetActiveNames.Description: Returns the names of all active (not deleted) resources.
lightsail:GetActiveNames.Title: GetActiveNames

lightsail:GetBlueprints.Description: Returns the list of available instance images, or blueprints. You can use a blueprint to create a new virtual private server already running a specific operating system, as well as a preinstalled app or development stack. The software each instance is running depends on the blueprint image you choose.
lightsail:GetBlueprints.Title: GetBlueprints

lightsail:GetBundles.Description: Returns the list of bundles that are available for purchase. A bundle describes the specs for your virtual private server (or instance).
lightsail:GetBundles.Title: GetBundles

lightsail:GetDomain.Description: Returns information about a specific domain recordset.
lightsail:GetDomain.Title: GetDomain

lightsail:GetDomains.Description: Returns a list of all domains in the user's account.
lightsail:GetDomains.Title: GetDomains

lightsail:GetInstance.Description: Returns information about a specific Amazon Lightsail instance, which is a virtual private server.
lightsail:GetInstance.Title: GetInstance

lightsail:GetInstanceAccessDetails.Description: Returns temporary SSH keys you can use to connect to a specific virtual private server, or instance.
lightsail:GetInstanceAccessDetails.Title: GetInstanceAccessDetails

lightsail:GetInstanceMetricData.Description: Returns the data points for the specified Amazon Lightsail instance metric, given an instance name.
lightsail:GetInstanceMetricData.Title: GetInstanceMetricData

lightsail:GetInstancePortStates.Description: Returns the port states for a specific virtual private server, or instance.
lightsail:GetInstancePortStates.Title: GetInstancePortStates

lightsail:GetInstanceSnapshot.Description: Returns information about a specific instance snapshot.
lightsail:GetInstanceSnapshot.Title: GetInstanceSnapshot

lightsail:GetInstanceSnapshots.Description: Returns all instance snapshots for the user's account.
lightsail:GetInstanceSnapshots.Title: GetInstanceSnapshots

lightsail:GetInstanceState.Description: Returns the state of a specific instance. Works on one instance at a time.
lightsail:GetInstanceState.Title: GetInstanceState

lightsail:GetInstances.Description: Returns information about all Amazon Lightsail virtual private servers, or instances.
lightsail:GetInstances.Title: GetInstances

lightsail:GetKeyPair.Description: Returns information about a specific key pair.
lightsail:GetKeyPair.Title: GetKeyPair

lightsail:GetKeyPairs.Description: Returns information about all key pairs in the user's account.
lightsail:GetKeyPairs.Title: GetKeyPairs

lightsail:GetOperation.Description: Returns information about a specific operation. Operations include events such as when you create an instance, allocate a static IP, attach a static IP, and so on.
lightsail:GetOperation.Title: GetOperation

lightsail:GetOperationsForResource.Description: Gets operations for a specific resource (e.g., an instance or a static IP).
lightsail:GetOperationsForResource.Title: GetOperationsForResource

lightsail:GetRegions.Description: Returns a list of all valid regions for Amazon Lightsail. Use the include availability zones parameter to also return the availability zones in a region.
lightsail:GetRegions.Title: GetRegions

lightsail:GetStaticIp.Description: Returns information about a specific static IP.
lightsail:GetStaticIp.Title: GetStaticIp

lightsail:GetStaticIps.Description: Returns information about all static IPs in the user's account.
lightsail:GetStaticIps.Title: GetStaticIps

lightsail:ImportKeyPair.Description: Imports a public SSH key from a specific key pair.
lightsail:ImportKeyPair.Title: ImportKeyPair

lightsail:IsVpcPeered.Description: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether your Lightsail VPC is peered.
lightsail:IsVpcPeered.Title: IsVpcPeered

lightsail:OpenInstancePublicPorts.Description: Adds public ports to an Amazon Lightsail instance.
lightsail:OpenInstancePublicPorts.Title: OpenInstancePublicPorts

lightsail:PeerVpc.Description: Tries to peer the Lightsail VPC with the user's default VPC.
lightsail:PeerVpc.Title: PeerVpc

lightsail:RebootInstance.Description: Restarts a specific instance. When your Amazon Lightsail instance is finished rebooting, Lightsail assigns a new public IP address. To use the same IP address after restarting, create a static IP address and attach it to the instance.
lightsail:RebootInstance.Title: RebootInstance

lightsail:ReleaseStaticIp.Description: Deletes a specific static IP from your account.
lightsail:ReleaseStaticIp.Title: ReleaseStaticIp

lightsail:StartInstance.Description: Starts a specific Amazon Lightsail instance from a stopped state. To restart an instance, use the reboot instance operation.
lightsail:StartInstance.Title: StartInstance

lightsail:StopInstance.Description: Stops a specific Amazon Lightsail instance that is currently running.
lightsail:StopInstance.Title: StopInstance

lightsail:UnpeerVpc.Description: Attempts to unpeer the Lightsail VPC from the user's default VPC.
lightsail:UnpeerVpc.Title: UnpeerVpc

lightsail:UpdateDomainEntry.Description: Updates a domain recordset after it is created.
lightsail:UpdateDomainEntry.Title: UpdateDomainEntry

logs:CreateExportTask.Description: Creates an export task, which allows you to efficiently export data from a log group to an Amazon S3 bucket.
logs:CreateExportTask.Title: CreateExportTask

logs:CreateLogGroup.Description: Creates a log group with the specified name.
logs:CreateLogGroup.Title: CreateLogGroup

logs:CreateLogStream.Description: Creates a log stream for the specified log group.
logs:CreateLogStream.Title: CreateLogStream

logs:DeleteDestination.Description: Deletes the specified destination, and eventually disables all the subscription filters that publish to it. This operation does not delete the physical resource encapsulated by the destination.
logs:DeleteDestination.Title: DeleteDestination

logs:DeleteLogGroup.Description: Deletes the specified log group and permanently deletes all the archived log events associated with the log group.
logs:DeleteLogGroup.Title: DeleteLogGroup

logs:DeleteLogStream.Description: Deletes the specified log stream and permanently deletes all the archived log events associated with the log stream.
logs:DeleteLogStream.Title: DeleteLogStream

logs:DescribeDestinations.Description: Lists all your destinations. The results are ASCII-sorted by destination name.
logs:DescribeDestinations.Title: DescribeDestinations

logs:DescribeExportTasks.Description: Lists the specified export tasks. You can list all your export tasks or filter the results based on task ID or task status.
logs:DescribeExportTasks.Title: DescribeExportTasks

logs:DescribeLogGroups.Description: Lists the specified log groups. You can list all your log groups or filter the results by prefix. The results are ASCII-sorted by log group name.
logs:DescribeLogGroups.Title: DescribeLogGroups

logs:DescribeLogStreams.Description: Lists the log streams for the specified log group. You can list all the log streams or filter the results by prefix. You can also control how the results are ordered.
logs:DescribeLogStreams.Title: DescribeLogStreams

logs:DescribeMetricFilters.Description: Lists the specified metric filters. You can list all the metric filters or filter the results by log name, prefix, metric name, or metric namespace. The results are ASCII-sorted by filter name.
logs:DescribeMetricFilters.Title: DescribeMetricFilters

logs:DescribeSubscriptionFilters.Description: Lists the subscription filters for the specified log group. You can list all the subscription filters or filter the results by prefix. The results are ASCII-sorted by filter name.
logs:DescribeSubscriptionFilters.Title: DescribeSubscriptionFilters

logs:FilterLogEvents.Description: Lists log events from the specified log group. You can list all the log events or filter the results using a filter pattern, a time range, and the name of the log stream.
logs:FilterLogEvents.Title: FilterLogEvents

logs:GetLogEvents.Description: Lists log events from the specified log stream. You can list all the log events or filter using a time range.
logs:GetLogEvents.Title: GetLogEvents

logs:PutDestination.Description: Creates or updates a destination. A destination encapsulates a physical resource (such as an Amazon Kinesis stream) and enables you to subscribe to a real-time stream of log events for a different account, ingested using PutLogEvents. Currently, the only supported physical resource is a Kinesis stream belonging to the same account as the destination.
logs:PutDestination.Title: PutDestination

logs:PutDestinationPolicy.Description: Creates or updates an access policy associated with an existing destination. An access policy is an IAM policy document that is used to authorize claims to register a subscription filter against a given destination.
logs:PutDestinationPolicy.Title: PutDestinationPolicy

logs:PutLogEvents.Description: Uploads a batch of log events to the specified log stream.
logs:PutLogEvents.Title: PutLogEvents

logs:PutMetricFilter.Description: Creates or updates a metric filter and associates it with the specified log group. Metric filters allow you to configure rules to extract metric data from log events ingested through PutLogEvents.
logs:PutMetricFilter.Title: PutMetricFilter

logs:PutRetentionPolicy.Description: Sets the retention of the specified log group. A retention policy allows you to configure the number of days for which to retain log events in the specified log group.
logs:PutRetentionPolicy.Title: PutRetentionPolicy

logs:PutSubscriptionFilter.Description: Creates or updates a subscription filter and associates it with the specified log group. Subscription filters allow you to subscribe to a real-time stream of log events ingested through PutLogEvents and have them delivered to a specific destination. Currently, the supported destinations are:
logs:PutSubscriptionFilter.Title: PutSubscriptionFilter

logs:TestMetricFilter.Description: Tests the filter pattern of a metric filter against a sample of log event messages. You can use this operation to validate the correctness of a metric filter pattern.
logs:TestMetricFilter.Title: TestMetricFilter

machinelearning:AddTags.Description: Adds one or more tags to an object, up to a limit of 10. Each tag consists of a key and an optional value. If you add a tag using a key that is already associated with the ML object, AddTags updates the tag's value.
machinelearning:AddTags.Title: AddTags

machinelearning:CreateBatchPrediction.Description: Generates predictions for a group of observations. The observations to process exist in one or more data files referenced by a DataSource. This operation creates a new BatchPrediction, and uses an MLModel and the data files referenced by the DataSource as information sources.
machinelearning:CreateBatchPrediction.Title: CreateBatchPrediction

machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromRDS.Description: Creates a DataSource object from an Amazon Relational Database Service (Amazon RDS). A DataSource references data that can be used to perform CreateMLModel, CreateEvaluation, or CreateBatchPrediction operations.
machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromRDS.Title: CreateDataSourceFromRDS

machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromReds.Description: Creates a DataSource from a database hosted on an Amazon Redshift cluster. A DataSource references data that can be used to perform either CreateMLModel, CreateEvaluation, or CreateBatchPrediction operations.
machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromReds.Title: CreateDataSourceFromRedshift

machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromS3.Description: Creates a DataSource object. A DataSource references data that can be used to perform CreateMLModel, CreateEvaluation, or CreateBatchPrediction operations.
machinelearning:CreateDataSourceFromS3.Title: CreateDataSourceFromS3

machinelearning:CreateEvaluation.Description: Creates a new Evaluation of an MLModel. An MLModel is evaluated on a set of observations associated to a DataSource. Like a DataSource for an MLModel, the DataSource for an Evaluation contains values for the Target Variable. The Evaluation compares the predicted result for each observation to the actual outcome and provides a summary so that you know how effective the MLModel functions on the test data. Evaluation generates a relevant performance metric, such as BinaryAUC, RegressionRMSE or MulticlassAvgFScore based on the corresponding MLModelType: BINARY, REGRESSION or MULTICLASS.
machinelearning:CreateEvaluation.Title: CreateEvaluation

machinelearning:CreateMLModel.Description: Creates a new MLModel using the DataSource and the recipe as information sources.
machinelearning:CreateMLModel.Title: CreateMLModel

machinelearning:CreateRealtimeEndpoint.Description: Creates a real-time endpoint for the MLModel. The endpoint contains the URI of the MLModel; that is, the location to send real-time prediction requests for the specified MLModel.
machinelearning:CreateRealtimeEndpoint.Title: CreateRealtimeEndpoint

machinelearning:DeleteBatchPrediction.Description: Assigns the DELETED status to a BatchPrediction, rendering it unusable.
machinelearning:DeleteBatchPrediction.Title: DeleteBatchPrediction

machinelearning:DeleteDataSource.Description: Assigns the DELETED status to a DataSource, rendering it unusable.
machinelearning:DeleteDataSource.Title: DeleteDataSource

machinelearning:DeleteEvaluation.Description: Assigns the DELETED status to an Evaluation, rendering it unusable.
machinelearning:DeleteEvaluation.Title: DeleteEvaluation

machinelearning:DeleteMLModel.Description: Assigns the DELETED status to an MLModel, rendering it unusable.
machinelearning:DeleteMLModel.Title: DeleteMLModel

machinelearning:DeleteRealtimeEndpoint.Description: Deletes a real time endpoint of an MLModel.
machinelearning:DeleteRealtimeEndpoint.Title: DeleteRealtimeEndpoint

machinelearning:DeleteTags.Description: Deletes the specified tags associated with an ML object. After this operation is complete, you can't recover deleted tags.
machinelearning:DeleteTags.Title: DeleteTags

machinelearning:DescribeBatchPredictions.Description: Returns a list of BatchPrediction operations that match the search criteria in the request.
machinelearning:DescribeBatchPredictions.Title: DescribeBatchPredictions

machinelearning:DescribeDataSources.Description: Returns a list of DataSource that match the search criteria in the request.
machinelearning:DescribeDataSources.Title: DescribeDataSources

machinelearning:DescribeEvaluations.Description: Returns a list of DescribeEvaluations that match the search criteria in the request.
machinelearning:DescribeEvaluations.Title: DescribeEvaluations

machinelearning:DescribeMLModels.Description: Returns a list of MLModel that match the search criteria in the request.
machinelearning:DescribeMLModels.Title: DescribeMLModels

machinelearning:DescribeTags.Description: Describes one or more of the tags for your Amazon ML object.
machinelearning:DescribeTags.Title: DescribeTags

machinelearning:GetBatchPrediction.Description: Returns a BatchPrediction that includes detailed metadata, status, and data file information for a Batch Prediction request.
machinelearning:GetBatchPrediction.Title: GetBatchPrediction

machinelearning:GetDataSource.Description: Returns a DataSource that includes metadata and data file information, as well as the current status of the DataSource.
machinelearning:GetDataSource.Title: GetDataSource

machinelearning:GetEvaluation.Description: Returns an Evaluation that includes metadata as well as the current status of the Evaluation.
machinelearning:GetEvaluation.Title: GetEvaluation

machinelearning:GetMLModel.Description: Returns an MLModel that includes detailed metadata, data source information, and the current status of the MLModel.
machinelearning:GetMLModel.Title: GetMLModel

machinelearning:Predict.Description: Generates a prediction for the observation using the specified ML Model.
machinelearning:Predict.Title: Predict

machinelearning:UpdateBatchPrediction.Description: Updates the BatchPredictionName of a BatchPrediction.
machinelearning:UpdateBatchPrediction.Title: UpdateBatchPrediction

machinelearning:UpdateDataSource.Description: Updates the DataSourceName of a DataSource.
machinelearning:UpdateDataSource.Title: UpdateDataSource

machinelearning:UpdateEvaluation.Description: Updates the EvaluationName of an Evaluation.
machinelearning:UpdateEvaluation.Title: UpdateEvaluation

machinelearning:UpdateMLModel.Description: Updates the MLModelName and the ScoreThreshold of an MLModel.
machinelearning:UpdateMLModel.Title: UpdateMLModel

mechanicalturk:AcceptQualificationReques.Description: The AcceptQualificationRequest operation grants a Worker's request for a Qualification.
mechanicalturk:AcceptQualificationReques.Title: AcceptQualificationRequest

mechanicalturk:ApproveAssignment.Description: The ApproveAssignment operation approves the results of a completed assignment.
mechanicalturk:ApproveAssignment.Title: ApproveAssignment

mechanicalturk:AssociateQualificationWit.Description: The AssociateQualificationWithWorker operation gives a Worker a Qualification. AssociateQualificationWithWorker does not require that the Worker submit a Qualification request. It gives the Qualification directly to the Worker.
mechanicalturk:AssociateQualificationWit.Title: AssociateQualificationWithWorker

mechanicalturk:CreateHIT.Description: The CreateHIT operation creates a new HIT (Human Intelligence Task). The new HIT is made available for Workers to find and accept on the Amazon Mechanical Turk website.
mechanicalturk:CreateHIT.Title: CreateHIT

mechanicalturk:CreateHITType.Description: The CreateHITType operation creates a new HIT type.
mechanicalturk:CreateHITType.Title: CreateHITType

mechanicalturk:CreateHITWithHITType.Description: The CreateHITWithHITType operation creates a new Human Intelligence Task (HIT) using an existing HITTypeID generated by the CreateHITType operation.
mechanicalturk:CreateHITWithHITType.Title: CreateHITWithHITType

mechanicalturk:CreateQualificationType.Description: The CreateQualificationType operation creates a new Qualification type, which is represented by a QualificationType data structure.
mechanicalturk:CreateQualificationType.Title: CreateQualificationType

mechanicalturk:CreateWorkerBlock.Description: The CreateWorkerBlock operation allows you to prevent a Worker from working on your HITs. For example, you can block a Worker who is producing poor quality work. You can block up to 100,000 Workers.
mechanicalturk:CreateWorkerBlock.Title: CreateWorkerBlock

mechanicalturk:DeleteHIT.Description: The DeleteHIT operation disposes of a HIT that is no longer needed. Only the Requester who created the HIT can delete it.
mechanicalturk:DeleteHIT.Title: DeleteHIT

mechanicalturk:DeleteQualificationType.Description: The DeleteQualificationType disposes a Qualification type and disposes any HIT types that are associated with the Qualification type.
mechanicalturk:DeleteQualificationType.Title: DeleteQualificationType

mechanicalturk:DeleteWorkerBlock.Description: The DeleteWorkerBlock operation allows you to reinstate a blocked Worker to work on your HITs. This operation reverses the effects of the CreateWorkerBlock operation. You need the Worker ID to use this operation. If the Worker ID is missing or invalid, this operation fails and returns the message “WorkerId is invalid.” If the specified Worker is not blocked, this operation returns successfully.
mechanicalturk:DeleteWorkerBlock.Title: DeleteWorkerBlock

mechanicalturk:DisassociateQualification.Description: The DisassociateQualificationFromWorker revokes a previously granted Qualification from a user.
mechanicalturk:DisassociateQualification.Title: DisassociateQualificationFromWorker

mechanicalturk:GetAccountBalance.Description: The GetAccountBalance operation retrieves the amount of money in your Amazon Mechanical Turk account.
mechanicalturk:GetAccountBalance.Title: GetAccountBalance

mechanicalturk:GetAssignment.Description: The GetAssignment retrieves an assignment with an AssignmentStatus value of Submitted, Approved, or Rejected, using the assignment's ID. Requesters can only retrieve their own assignments for HITs that they have not disposed of.
mechanicalturk:GetAssignment.Title: GetAssignment

mechanicalturk:GetFileUploadURL.Description: The GetFileUploadURL operation generates and returns a temporary URL. You use the temporary URL to retrieve a file uploaded by a Worker as an answer to a FileUploadAnswer question for a HIT. The temporary URL is generated the instant the GetFileUploadURL operation is called, and is valid for 60 seconds. You can get a temporary file upload URL any time until the HIT is disposed. After the HIT is disposed, any uploaded files are deleted, and cannot be retrieved.
mechanicalturk:GetFileUploadURL.Title: GetFileUploadURL

mechanicalturk:GetHIT.Description: The GetHIT operation retrieves the details of the specified HIT.
mechanicalturk:GetHIT.Title: GetHIT

mechanicalturk:GetQualificationScore.Description: The GetQualificationScore operation returns the value of a Worker's Qualification for a given Qualification type.
mechanicalturk:GetQualificationScore.Title: GetQualificationScore

mechanicalturk:GetQualificationType.Description: The GetQualificationTypeoperation retrieves information about a Qualification type using its ID.
mechanicalturk:GetQualificationType.Title: GetQualificationType

mechanicalturk:ListAssignmentsForHIT.Description: The ListAssignmentsForHIT operation retrieves completed assignments for a HIT. You can use this operation to retrieve the results for a HIT.
mechanicalturk:ListAssignmentsForHIT.Title: ListAssignmentsForHIT

mechanicalturk:ListBonusPayments.Description: The ListBonusPayments operation retrieves the amounts of bonuses you have paid to Workers for a given HIT or assignment.
mechanicalturk:ListBonusPayments.Title: ListBonusPayments

mechanicalturk:ListHITs.Description: The ListHITs operation returns all of a Requester's HITs. The operation returns HITs of any status, except for HITs that have been deleted of with the DeleteHIT operation or that have been auto-deleted.
mechanicalturk:ListHITs.Title: ListHITs

mechanicalturk:ListHITsForQualificationT.Description: The ListHITsForQualificationType operation returns the HITs that use the given Qualification type for a Qualification requirement. The operation returns HITs of any status, except for HITs that have been deleted of with the DeleteHIT operation or that have been auto-deleted.
mechanicalturk:ListHITsForQualificationT.Title: ListHITsForQualificationType

mechanicalturk:ListQualificationRequests.Description: The ListQualificationRequests operation retrieves requests for Qualifications of a particular Qualification type. The owner of the Qualification type calls this operation to poll for pending requests, and accepts them using the AcceptQualification operation.
mechanicalturk:ListQualificationRequests.Title: ListQualificationRequests

mechanicalturk:ListQualificationTypes.Description: The ListQualificationTypes operation searches for Qualification types using the specified search query, and returns a list of Qualification types.
mechanicalturk:ListQualificationTypes.Title: ListQualificationTypes

mechanicalturk:ListReviewPolicyResultsFo.Description: The ListReviewPolicyResultsForHIT operation retrieves the computed results and the actions taken in the course of executing your Review Policies during a CreateHIT operation. For information about how to apply Review Policies when you call CreateHIT, see Review Policies. The GetReviewResultsForHIT operation can return results for both Assignment-level and HIT-level review results. You can also specify to only return results pertaining to a particular Assignment.
mechanicalturk:ListReviewPolicyResultsFo.Title: ListReviewPolicyResultsForHIT

mechanicalturk:ListReviewableHITs.Description: The ListReviewableHITs operation returns all of a Requester's HITs. The operation returns HITs of any status, except for HITs that have been deleted of with the DeleteHIT operation or that have been auto-deleted.
mechanicalturk:ListReviewableHITs.Title: ListReviewableHITs

mechanicalturk:ListWorkerBlocks.Description: The ListWorkersBlocks operation retrieves a list of Workers who are blocked from working on your HITs.
mechanicalturk:ListWorkerBlocks.Title: ListWorkerBlocks

mechanicalturk:ListWorkersWithQualificat.Description: The ListWorkersWithQualificationType operation returns all of the Workers with a given Qualification type.
mechanicalturk:ListWorkersWithQualificat.Title: ListWorkersWithQualificationType

mechanicalturk:NotifyWorkers.Description: The NotifyWorkers operation sends an email to one or more Workers that you specify with the Worker ID. You can specify up to 100 Worker IDs to send the same message with a single call to the NotifyWorkers operation. The NotifyWorkers operation will send a notification email to a Worker only if you have previously approved or rejected work from the Worker.
mechanicalturk:NotifyWorkers.Title: NotifyWorkers

mechanicalturk:RejectAssignment.Description: The RejectAssignment operation rejects the results of a completed assignment.
mechanicalturk:RejectAssignment.Title: RejectAssignment

mechanicalturk:RejectQualificationReques.Description: The RejectQualificationRequest operation rejects a user's request for a Qualification.
mechanicalturk:RejectQualificationReques.Title: RejectQualificationRequest

mechanicalturk:SendBonus.Description: The SendBonus operation issues a payment of money from your account to a Worker. This payment happens separately from the reward you pay to the Worker when you approve the Worker's assignment. The SendBonus operation requires the Worker's ID and the assignment ID as parameters to initiate payment of the bonus. You must include a message that explains the reason for the bonus payment, as the Worker may not be expecting the payment. Amazon Mechanical Turk collects a fee for bonus payments, similar to the HIT listing fee.
mechanicalturk:SendBonus.Title: SendBonus

mechanicalturk:SendTestEventNotification.Description: The SendTestEventNotification operation causes Amazon Mechanical Turk to send a notification message as if a HIT event occurred, according to the provided notification specification.
