s3:DeleteBucketWebsite.Description: This operation removes the website configuration for a bucket. Amazon S3 returns a 200 OK response upon successfully deleting a website configuration on the specified bucket. You will get a 200 OK response if the website configuration you are trying to delete does not exist on the bucket. Amazon S3 returns a 404 response if the bucket specified in the request does not exist.
s3:DeleteBucketWebsite.Title: DELETE Bucket website

s3:DeleteObject.Description: The DELETE operation removes the null version (if there is one) of an object and inserts a delete marker, which becomes the current version of the object. If there isn't a null version, Amazon S3 does not remove any objects.
s3:DeleteObject.Title: DELETE Object

s3:DeleteObjectVersion.Description: The DELETE operation removes the null version (if there is one) of an object and inserts a delete marker, which becomes the current version of the object. If there isn't a null version, Amazon S3 does not remove any objects.
s3:DeleteObjectVersion.Title: DELETE Object

s3:GetAccelerateConfiguration.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the accelerate subresource to return the Transfer Acceleration state of a bucket, which is either Enabled or Suspended. Amazon S3 Transfer Acceleration is a bucket-level feature that enables you to perform faster data transfers to and from Amazon S3.
s3:GetAccelerateConfiguration.Title: GET Bucket accelerate

s3:GetBucketAcl.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the acl subresource to return the access control list (ACL) of a bucket. To use GET to return the ACL of the bucket, you must have READ_ACP access to the bucket. If READ_ACP permission is granted to the anonymous user, you can return the ACL of the bucket without using an authorization header.
s3:GetBucketAcl.Title: GET Bucket acl

s3:GetBucketCORS.Description: Returns the cors configuration information set for the bucket.
s3:GetBucketCORS.Title: GET Bucket cors

s3:GetBucketLocation.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the location subresource to return a bucket's region. You set the bucket's region using the LocationConstraint request parameter in a PUT Bucket request. For more information, see PUT Bucket.
s3:GetBucketLocation.Title: GET Bucket location

s3:GetBucketLogging.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the logging subresource to return the logging status of a bucket and the permissions users have to view and modify that status. To use GET, you must be the bucket owner.
s3:GetBucketLogging.Title: GET Bucket logging

s3:GetBucketNotification.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the notification subresource to return the notification configuration of a bucket.
s3:GetBucketNotification.Title: GET Bucket notification

s3:GetBucketPolicy.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the policy subresource to return the policy of a specified bucket. To use this operation, you must have GetPolicy permissions on the specified bucket, and you must be the bucket owner.
s3:GetBucketPolicy.Title: GET Bucket policy

s3:GetBucketRequestPayment.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the requestPayment subresource to return the request payment configuration of a bucket. To use this version of the operation, you must be the bucket owner. For more information, see Requester Pays Buckets.
s3:GetBucketRequestPayment.Title: GET Bucket requestPayment

s3:GetBucketTagging.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the tagging subresource to return the tag set associated with the bucket.
s3:GetBucketTagging.Title: GET Bucket tagging

s3:GetBucketVersioning.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the versioning subresource to return the versioning state of a bucket. To retrieve the versioning state of a bucket, you must be the bucket owner.
s3:GetBucketVersioning.Title: GET Bucket versioning

s3:GetBucketWebsite.Description: This implementation of the GET operation returns the website configuration associated with a bucket. To host website on Amazon S3, you can configure a bucket as website by adding a website configuration. For more information about hosting websites, go to Hosting Websites on Amazon S3 in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide .
s3:GetBucketWebsite.Title: GET Bucket website

s3:GetLifecycleConfiguration.Description: Returns the lifecycle configuration information set on the bucket. For information about lifecycle configuration, go to Object Lifecycle Management in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.
s3:GetLifecycleConfiguration.Title: GET Bucket lifecycle

s3:GetObject.Description: This implementation of the GET operation retrieves objects from Amazon S3. To use GET, you must have READ access to the object. If you grant READ access to the anonymous user, you can return the object without using an authorization header.
s3:GetObject.Title: GET Object

s3:GetObjectAcl.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the acl subresource to return the access control list (ACL) of an object. To use this operation, you must have READ_ACP access to the object.
s3:GetObjectAcl.Title: GET Object ACL

s3:GetObjectTagging.Description: This implementation of the GET operation returns the tags associated with an object. You send the GET request against the tagging subresource associated with the object.
s3:GetObjectTagging.Title: GET Object tagging

s3:GetObjectTorrent.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the torrent subresource to return torrent files from a bucket. BitTorrent can save you bandwidth when you're distributing large files. For more information about BitTorrent, see Amazon S3 Torrent.
s3:GetObjectTorrent.Title: GET Object torrent

s3:GetObjectVersion.Description: This implementation of the GET operation retrieves objects from Amazon S3. To use GET, you must have READ access to the object. If you grant READ access to the anonymous user, you can return the object without using an authorization header.
s3:GetObjectVersion.Title: GET Object

s3:GetObjectVersionAcl.Description: By default, GET returns ACL information about the current version of an object. To return ACL information about a different version, use the versionId subresource.
s3:GetObjectVersionAcl.Title: Versioning

s3:GetObjectVersionTagging.Description: This implementation of the GET operation returns the tags associated with an object. You send the GET request against the tagging subresource associated with the object.
s3:GetObjectVersionTagging.Title: GET Object tagging

s3:GetObjectVersionTorrent.Description: This implementation of the GET operation uses the torrent subresource to return torrent files from a bucket. BitTorrent can save you bandwidth when you're distributing large files. For more information about BitTorrent, see Amazon S3 Torrent.
s3:GetObjectVersionTorrent.Title: GET Object torrent

s3:ListAllMyBuckets.Description: This implementation of the GET operation returns a list of all buckets owned by the authenticated sender of the request.
s3:ListAllMyBuckets.Title: GET Service

s3:ListBucket.Description: This implementation of the GET operation returns some or all (up to 1,000) of the objects in a bucket. You can use the request parameters as selection criteria to return a subset of the objects in a bucket. A 200 OK response can contain valid or invalid XML. Make sure to design your application to parse the contents of the response and handle it appropriately.
s3:ListBucket.Title: GET Bucket (List Objects) Version 1

s3:ListBucketMultipartUploads.Description: This operation lists in-progress multipart uploads. An in-progress multipart upload is a multipart upload that has been initiated using the Initiate Multipart Upload request, but has not yet been completed or aborted.
s3:ListBucketMultipartUploads.Title: List Multipart Uploads

s3:ListBucketVersions.Description: You can use the versions subresource to list metadata about all of the versions of objects in a bucket. You can also use request parameters as selection criteria to return metadata about a subset of all the object versions. For more information, see Request Parameters.
s3:ListBucketVersions.Title: GET Bucket Object versions

s3:ListMultipartUploadParts.Description: This operation lists the parts that have been uploaded for a specific multipart upload.
s3:ListMultipartUploadParts.Title: List Parts

s3:PutAccelerateConfiguration.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the accelerate subresource to set the Transfer Acceleration state of an existing bucket. Amazon S3 Transfer Acceleration is a bucket-level feature that enables you to perform faster data transfers to Amazon S3.
s3:PutAccelerateConfiguration.Title: PUT Bucket accelerate

s3:PutBucketAcl.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the acl subresource to set the permissions on an existing bucket using access control lists (ACL). For more information, go to Using ACLs. To set the ACL of a bucket, you must have WRITE_ACP permission.
s3:PutBucketAcl.Title: PUT Bucket acl

s3:PutBucketCORS.Description: Sets the cors configuration for your bucket. If the configuration exists, Amazon S3 replaces it.
s3:PutBucketCORS.Title: PUT Bucket cors

s3:PutBucketLogging.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the logging subresource to set the logging parameters for a bucket and to specify permissions for who can view and modify the logging parameters. To set the logging status of a bucket, you must be the bucket owner.
s3:PutBucketLogging.Title: PUT Bucket logging

s3:PutBucketNotification.Description: The Amazon S3 notification feature enables you to receive notifications when certain events happen in your bucket. For more information about event notifications, go to Configuring Event Notifications in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.
s3:PutBucketNotification.Title: PUT Bucket notification

s3:PutBucketPolicy.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the policy subresource to add to or replace a policy on a bucket. If the bucket already has a policy, the one in this request completely replaces it. To perform this operation, you must be the bucket owner.
s3:PutBucketPolicy.Title: PUT Bucket policy

s3:PutBucketRequestPayment.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the requestPayment subresource to set the request payment configuration of a bucket. By default, the bucket owner pays for downloads from the bucket. This configuration parameter enables the bucket owner (only) to specify that the person requesting the download will be charged for the download. For more information, see Requester Pays Buckets.
s3:PutBucketRequestPayment.Title: PUT Bucket requestPayment

s3:PutBucketTagging.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the tagging subresource to add a set of tags to an existing bucket.
s3:PutBucketTagging.Title: PUT Bucket tagging

s3:PutBucketVersioning.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the versioning subresource to set the versioning state of an existing bucket. To set the versioning state, you must be the bucket owner.
s3:PutBucketVersioning.Title: PUT Bucket versioning

s3:PutBucketWebsite.Description: Sets the configuration of the website that is specified in the website subresource. To configure a bucket as a website, you can add this subresource on the bucket with website configuration information such as the file name of the index document and any redirect rules. For more information, go to Hosting Websites on Amazon S3 in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.
s3:PutBucketWebsite.Title: PUT Bucket website

s3:PutLifecycleConfiguration.Description: Creates a new lifecycle configuration for the bucket or replaces an existing lifecycle configuration. For information about lifecycle configuration, go to Object Lifecycle Management in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.
s3:PutLifecycleConfiguration.Title: PUT Bucket lifecycle

s3:PutObject.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation adds an object to a bucket. You must have WRITE permissions on a bucket to add an object to it.
s3:PutObject.Title: PUT Object

s3:PutObjectAcl.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the acl subresource to set the access control list (ACL) permissions for an object that already exists in a bucket. You must have WRITE_ACP permission to set the ACL of an object.
s3:PutObjectAcl.Title: PUT Object acl

s3:PutObjectVersionAcl.Description: This implementation of the PUT operation uses the acl subresource to set the access control list (ACL) permissions for an object that already exists in a bucket. You must have WRITE_ACP permission to set the ACL of an object.
s3:PutObjectVersionAcl.Title: PUT Object acl

s3:PutReplicationConfiguration.Description: In a versioning-enabled bucket, this operation creates a new replication configuration (or replaces an existing one, if present). Amazon S3 stores the configuration in the replication subresource associated with the bucket. If the replication subresource does not exist, Amazon S3 creates it. If it does exist, Amazon S3 replaces the configuration stored in the subresource. For information about replication configuration, see Cross-Region Replication in the Amazon Simple Storage Service Developer Guide.
s3:PutReplicationConfiguration.Title: PUT Bucket replication

s3:ReplicateDelete.Description: To set up cross-region replication, you need two buckets—source and destination. These buckets must be versioning-enabled and in different AWS Regions. For a list of AWS Regions where you can create a bucket, see Regions and Endpoints in the AWS General Reference. You can replicate objects from a source bucket to only one destination bucket.
s3:ReplicateDelete.Title: Setting Up Cross-Region Replication

s3:ReplicateObject.Description: To set up cross-region replication, you need two buckets—source and destination. These buckets must be versioning-enabled and in different AWS Regions. For a list of AWS Regions where you can create a bucket, see Regions and Endpoints in the AWS General Reference. You can replicate objects from a source bucket to only one destination bucket.
s3:ReplicateObject.Title: Setting Up Cross-Region Replication

s3:RestoreObject.Description: Restores a temporary copy of an archived object. You can optionally provide version ID to restore specific object version. If version ID is not provided, it will restore the current version.
s3:RestoreObject.Title: POST Object restore

sdb:BatchDeleteAttributes.Description: Performs multiple DeleteAttributes operations in a single call, which reduces round trips and latencies. This enables Amazon SimpleDB to optimize requests, which generally yields better throughput.
sdb:BatchDeleteAttributes.Title: BatchDeleteAttributes

sdb:BatchPutAttributes.Description: With the BatchPutAttributes operation, you can perform multiple PutAttribute operations in a single call. This helps you yield savings in round trips and latencies, and enables Amazon SimpleDB to optimize requests, which generally yields better throughput.
sdb:BatchPutAttributes.Title: BatchPutAttributes

sdb:CreateDomain.Description: The CreateDomain operation creates a new domain. The domain name must be unique among the domains associated with the Access Key ID provided in the request. The CreateDomain operation might take 10 or more seconds to complete.
sdb:CreateDomain.Title: CreateDomain

sdb:DeleteAttributes.Description: Deletes one or more attributes associated with the item. If all attributes of an item are deleted, the item is deleted.
sdb:DeleteAttributes.Title: DeleteAttributes

sdb:DeleteDomain.Description: The DeleteDomain operation deletes a domain. Any items (and their attributes) in the domain are deleted as well. The DeleteDomain operation might take 10 or more seconds to complete.
sdb:DeleteDomain.Title: DeleteDomain

sdb:DomainMetadata.Description: Returns information about the domain, including when the domain was created, the number of items and attributes, and the size of attribute names and values.
sdb:DomainMetadata.Title: DomainMetadata

sdb:GetAttributes.Description: Returns all of the attributes associated with the item. Optionally, the attributes returned can be limited to one or more specified attribute name parameters.
sdb:GetAttributes.Title: GetAttributes

sdb:ListDomains.Description: The ListDomains operation lists all domains associated with the Access Key ID. It returns domain names up to the limit set by MaxNumberOfDomains. A NextToken is returned if there are more than MaxNumberOfDomains domains. Calling ListDomains successive times with the NextToken returns up to MaxNumberOfDomains more domain names each time.
sdb:ListDomains.Title: ListDomains

sdb:PutAttributes.Description: The PutAttributes operation creates or replaces attributes in an item. You specify new attributes using a combination of the Attribute.X.Name and Attribute.X.Value parameters. You specify the first attribute by the parameters Attribute.1.Name and Attribute.1.Value, the second attribute by the parameters Attribute.2.Name and Attribute.2.Value, and so on.
sdb:PutAttributes.Title: PutAttributes

sdb:Select.Description: The Select operation returns a set of Attributes for ItemNames that match the select expression. Select is similar to the standard SQL SELECT statement.
sdb:Select.Title: Select

servicecatalog:AcceptPortfolioShare.Description: Accepts an offer to share the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:AcceptPortfolioShare.Title: AcceptPortfolioShare

servicecatalog:AssociatePrincipalWithPor.Description: Associates the specified principal ARN with the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:AssociatePrincipalWithPor.Title: AssociatePrincipalWithPortfolio

servicecatalog:AssociateProductWithPortf.Description: Associates the specified product with the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:AssociateProductWithPortf.Title: AssociateProductWithPortfolio

servicecatalog:CreatePortfolioShare.Description: Shares the specified portfolio with the specified account.
servicecatalog:CreatePortfolioShare.Title: CreatePortfolioShare

servicecatalog:CreateProvisioningArtifac.Description: Creates a provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.
servicecatalog:CreateProvisioningArtifac.Title: CreateProvisioningArtifact

servicecatalog:DeletePortfolioShare.Description: Stops sharing the specified portfolio with the specified account.
servicecatalog:DeletePortfolioShare.Title: DeletePortfolioShare

servicecatalog:DeleteProvisioningArtifac.Description: Deletes the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.
servicecatalog:DeleteProvisioningArtifac.Title: DeleteProvisioningArtifact

servicecatalog:DescribeConstraint.Description: Gets information about the specified constraint.
servicecatalog:DescribeConstraint.Title: DescribeConstraint

servicecatalog:DescribePortfolio.Description: Gets information about the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:DescribePortfolio.Title: DescribePortfolio

servicecatalog:DescribeProduct.Description: Gets information about the specified product.
servicecatalog:DescribeProduct.Title: DescribeProduct

servicecatalog:DescribeProductAsAdmin.Description: Gets information about the specified product. This operation is run with administrator access.
servicecatalog:DescribeProductAsAdmin.Title: DescribeProductAsAdmin

servicecatalog:DescribeProductView.Description: Gets information about the specified product.
servicecatalog:DescribeProductView.Title: DescribeProductView

servicecatalog:DescribeProvisioningArtif.Description: Gets information about the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.
servicecatalog:DescribeProvisioningArtif.Title: DescribeProvisioningArtifact

servicecatalog:DescribeProvisioningParam.Description: Gets information about the configuration required to provision the specified product using the specified provisioning artifact.
servicecatalog:DescribeProvisioningParam.Title: DescribeProvisioningParameters

servicecatalog:DescribeRecord.Description: Gets information about the specified request operation.
servicecatalog:DescribeRecord.Title: DescribeRecord

servicecatalog:DisassociatePrincipalFrom.Description: Disassociates a previously associated principal ARN from a specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:DisassociatePrincipalFrom.Title: DisassociatePrincipalFromPortfolio

servicecatalog:DisassociateProductFromPo.Description: Disassociates the specified product from the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:DisassociateProductFromPo.Title: DisassociateProductFromPortfolio

servicecatalog:ListAcceptedPortfolioShar.Description: Lists all portfolios for which sharing was accepted by this account.
servicecatalog:ListAcceptedPortfolioShar.Title: ListAcceptedPortfolioShares

servicecatalog:ListConstraintsForPortfol.Description: Lists the constraints for the specified portfolio and product.
servicecatalog:ListConstraintsForPortfol.Title: ListConstraintsForPortfolio

servicecatalog:ListLaunchPaths.Description: Lists the paths to the specified product. A path is how the user has access to a specified product, and is necessary when provisioning a product. A path also determines the constraints put on the product.
servicecatalog:ListLaunchPaths.Title: ListLaunchPaths

servicecatalog:ListPortfolioAccess.Description: Lists the account IDs that have access to the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:ListPortfolioAccess.Title: ListPortfolioAccess

servicecatalog:ListPortfolios.Description: Lists all portfolios in the catalog.
servicecatalog:ListPortfolios.Title: ListPortfolios

servicecatalog:ListPortfoliosForProduct.Description: Lists all portfolios that the specified product is associated with.
servicecatalog:ListPortfoliosForProduct.Title: ListPortfoliosForProduct

servicecatalog:ListPrincipalsForPortfoli.Description: Lists all principal ARNs associated with the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:ListPrincipalsForPortfoli.Title: ListPrincipalsForPortfolio

servicecatalog:ListProvisioningArtifacts.Description: Lists all provisioning artifacts (also known as versions) for the specified product.
servicecatalog:ListProvisioningArtifacts.Title: ListProvisioningArtifacts

servicecatalog:ListRecordHistory.Description: Lists the specified requests or all performed requests.
servicecatalog:ListRecordHistory.Title: ListRecordHistory

servicecatalog:RejectPortfolioShare.Description: Rejects an offer to share the specified portfolio.
servicecatalog:RejectPortfolioShare.Title: RejectPortfolioShare

servicecatalog:ScanProvisionedProducts.Description: Lists the provisioned products that are available (not terminated).
servicecatalog:ScanProvisionedProducts.Title: ScanProvisionedProducts

servicecatalog:SearchProducts.Description: Gets information about the products to which the caller has access.
servicecatalog:SearchProducts.Title: SearchProducts

servicecatalog:SearchProductsAsAdmin.Description: Gets information about the products for the specified portfolio or all products.
servicecatalog:SearchProductsAsAdmin.Title: SearchProductsAsAdmin

servicecatalog:UpdateProvisionedProduct.Description: Requests updates to the configuration of the specified provisioned product.
servicecatalog:UpdateProvisionedProduct.Title: UpdateProvisionedProduct

servicecatalog:UpdateProvisioningArtifac.Description: Updates the specified provisioning artifact (also known as a version) for the specified product.
servicecatalog:UpdateProvisioningArtifac.Title: UpdateProvisioningArtifact

ses:CloneReceiptRuleSet.Description: Creates a receipt rule set by cloning an existing one. All receipt rules and configurations are copied to the new receipt rule set and are completely independent of the source rule set.
ses:CloneReceiptRuleSet.Title: CloneReceiptRuleSet

ses:CreateReceiptFilter.Description: Creates a new IP address filter.
ses:CreateReceiptFilter.Title: CreateReceiptFilter

ses:CreateReceiptRuleSet.Description: Creates an empty receipt rule set.
ses:CreateReceiptRuleSet.Title: CreateReceiptRuleSet

ses:DeleteIdentity.Description: Deletes the specified identity (an email address or a domain) from the list of verified identities.
ses:DeleteIdentity.Title: DeleteIdentity

ses:DeleteIdentityPolicy.Description: Deletes the specified sending authorization policy for the given identity (an email address or a domain). This API returns successfully even if a policy with the specified name does not exist.
ses:DeleteIdentityPolicy.Title: DeleteIdentityPolicy

ses:DeleteReceiptFilter.Description: Deletes the specified IP address filter.
ses:DeleteReceiptFilter.Title: DeleteReceiptFilter

ses:DeleteReceiptRuleSet.Description: Deletes the specified receipt rule set and all of the receipt rules it contains.
ses:DeleteReceiptRuleSet.Title: DeleteReceiptRuleSet

ses:DeleteVerifiedEmailAddress.Description: Deprecated. Use the DeleteIdentity operation to delete email addresses and domains.
ses:DeleteVerifiedEmailAddress.Title: DeleteVerifiedEmailAddress

ses:DescribeActiveReceiptRuleSet.Description: Returns the metadata and receipt rules for the receipt rule set that is currently active.
ses:DescribeActiveReceiptRuleSet.Title: DescribeActiveReceiptRuleSet

ses:DescribeReceiptRule.Description: Returns the details of the specified receipt rule.
ses:DescribeReceiptRule.Title: DescribeReceiptRule

ses:DescribeReceiptRuleSet.Description: Returns the details of the specified receipt rule set.
ses:DescribeReceiptRuleSet.Title: DescribeReceiptRuleSet

ses:FeedbackAddress.Description: You can use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) with Amazon Simple Email Service (Amazon SES) to specify which Amazon SES API actions an IAM user, group, or role can perform. (In this topic we refer to these entities collectively as user.) You can also control which email addresses the user can use for the "From", recipient, and "Return-Path" addresses of emails.
ses:FeedbackAddress.Title: Controlling Access to Amazon SES

ses:FromAddress.Description: You can use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) with Amazon Simple Email Service (Amazon SES) to specify which Amazon SES API actions an IAM user, group, or role can perform. (In this topic we refer to these entities collectively as user.) You can also control which email addresses the user can use for the "From", recipient, and "Return-Path" addresses of emails.
ses:FromAddress.Title: Controlling Access to Amazon SES

ses:FromDisplayName.Description: You can use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) with Amazon Simple Email Service (Amazon SES) to specify which Amazon SES API actions an IAM user, group, or role can perform. (In this topic we refer to these entities collectively as user.) You can also control which email addresses the user can use for the "From", recipient, and "Return-Path" addresses of emails.
ses:FromDisplayName.Title: Controlling Access to Amazon SES

ses:GetIdentityDkimAttributes.Description: Returns the current status of Easy DKIM signing for an entity. For domain name identities, this operation also returns the DKIM tokens that are required for Easy DKIM signing, and whether Amazon SES has successfully verified that these tokens have been published.
ses:GetIdentityDkimAttributes.Title: GetIdentityDkimAttributes

ses:GetIdentityNotificationAttributes.Description: Given a list of verified identities (email addresses and/or domains), returns a structure describing identity notification attributes.
ses:GetIdentityNotificationAttributes.Title: GetIdentityNotificationAttributes

ses:GetIdentityPolicies.Description: Returns the requested sending authorization policies for the given identity (an email address or a domain). The policies are returned as a map of policy names to policy contents. You can retrieve a maximum of 20 policies at a time.
ses:GetIdentityPolicies.Title: GetIdentityPolicies

ses:GetIdentityVerificationAttributes.Description: Given a list of identities (email addresses and/or domains), returns the verification status and (for domain identities) the verification token for each identity.
ses:GetIdentityVerificationAttributes.Title: GetIdentityVerificationAttributes

ses:GetSendQuota.Description: Provides the sending limits for the Amazon SES account.
ses:GetSendQuota.Title: GetSendQuota

ses:GetSendStatistics.Description: Provides sending statistics for the Amazon SES account. The result is a list of data points, representing the last two weeks of sending activity. Each data point in the list contains statistics for a 15-minute period of time.
ses:GetSendStatistics.Title: GetSendStatistics

ses:ListIdentities.Description: Returns a list containing all of the identities (email addresses and domains) for your AWS account, regardless of verification status.
ses:ListIdentities.Title: ListIdentities

ses:ListIdentityPolicies.Description: Returns a list of sending authorization policies that are attached to the given identity (an email address or a domain). This API returns only a list. If you want the actual policy content, you can use GetIdentityPolicies.
ses:ListIdentityPolicies.Title: ListIdentityPolicies

ses:ListReceiptFilters.Description: Lists the IP address filters associated with your AWS account.
ses:ListReceiptFilters.Title: ListReceiptFilters

ses:ListReceiptRuleSets.Description: Lists the receipt rule sets that exist under your AWS account. If there are additional receipt rule sets to be retrieved, you will receive a NextToken that you can provide to the next call to ListReceiptRuleSets to retrieve the additional entries.
ses:ListReceiptRuleSets.Title: ListReceiptRuleSets

ses:ListVerifiedEmailAddresses.Description: Deprecated. Use the ListIdentities operation to list the email addresses and domains associated with your account.
ses:ListVerifiedEmailAddresses.Title: ListVerifiedEmailAddresses

ses:PutIdentityPolicy.Description: Adds or updates a sending authorization policy for the specified identity (an email address or a domain).
ses:PutIdentityPolicy.Title: PutIdentityPolicy

ses:Recipients.Description: You can use AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) with Amazon Simple Email Service (Amazon SES) to specify which Amazon SES API actions an IAM user, group, or role can perform. (In this topic we refer to these entities collectively as user.) You can also control which email addresses the user can use for the "From", recipient, and "Return-Path" addresses of emails.
ses:Recipients.Title: Controlling Access to Amazon SES

ses:ReorderReceiptRuleSet.Description: Reorders the receipt rules within a receipt rule set.
ses:ReorderReceiptRuleSet.Title: ReorderReceiptRuleSet

ses:SendBounce.Description: Generates and sends a bounce message to the sender of an email you received through Amazon SES. You can only use this API on an email up to 24 hours after you receive it.
ses:SendBounce.Title: SendBounce

ses:SendEmail.Description: Composes an email message and immediately queues it for sending. In order to send email using the SendEmail operation, your message must meet the following requirements:
ses:SendEmail.Title: SendEmail

ses:SendRawEmail.Description: Composes an email message and immediately queues it for sending. When calling this operation, you may specify the message headers as well as the content. The SendRawEmail operation is particularly useful for sending multipart MIME emails (such as those that contain both a plain-text and an HTML version).
ses:SendRawEmail.Title: SendRawEmail

ses:SetActiveReceiptRuleSet.Description: Sets the specified receipt rule set as the active receipt rule set.
ses:SetActiveReceiptRuleSet.Title: SetActiveReceiptRuleSet

ses:SetIdentityDkimEnabled.Description: Enables or disables Easy DKIM signing of email sent from an identity:
ses:SetIdentityDkimEnabled.Title: SetIdentityDkimEnabled

ses:SetIdentityFeedbackForwardingEnabled.Description: Given an identity (an email address or a domain), enables or disables whether Amazon SES forwards bounce and complaint notifications as email. Feedback forwarding can only be disabled when Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) topics are specified for both bounces and complaints.
ses:SetIdentityFeedbackForwardingEnabled.Title: SetIdentityFeedbackForwardingEnabled

ses:SetIdentityNotificationTopic.Description: Given an identity (an email address or a domain), sets the Amazon Simple Notification Service (Amazon SNS) topic to which Amazon SES will publish bounce, complaint, and/or delivery notifications for emails sent with that identity as the Source.
ses:SetIdentityNotificationTopic.Title: SetIdentityNotificationTopic

ses:SetReceiptRulePosition.Description: Sets the position of the specified receipt rule in the receipt rule set.
ses:SetReceiptRulePosition.Title: SetReceiptRulePosition

ses:VerifyDomainDkim.Description: Returns a set of DKIM tokens for a domain. DKIM tokens are character strings that represent your domain's identity. Using these tokens, you will need to create DNS CNAME records that point to DKIM public keys hosted by Amazon SES. Amazon Web Services will eventually detect that you have updated your DNS records; this detection process may take up to 72 hours. Upon successful detection, Amazon SES will be able to DKIM-sign email originating from that domain.
ses:VerifyDomainDkim.Title: VerifyDomainDkim

ses:VerifyDomainIdentity.Description: Adds a domain to the list of identities for your Amazon SES account and attempts to verify it. For more information about verifying domains, see Verifying Email Addresses and Domains in the Amazon SES Developer Guide.
ses:VerifyDomainIdentity.Title: VerifyDomainIdentity

ses:VerifyEmailAddress.Description: Deprecated. Use the VerifyEmailIdentity operation to verify a new email address.
ses:VerifyEmailAddress.Title: VerifyEmailAddress

ses:VerifyEmailIdentity.Description: Adds an email address to the list of identities for your Amazon SES account and attempts to verify it. This operation causes a confirmation email message to be sent to the specified address.
ses:VerifyEmailIdentity.Title: VerifyEmailIdentity

shield:CreateProtection.Description: Enables AWS Shield Advanced for a specific AWS resource. The resource can be an Amazon CloudFront distribution, Elastic Load Balancing load balancer, or an Amazon Route 53 hosted zone.
shield:CreateProtection.Title: CreateProtection

shield:CreateSubscription.Description: Activates AWS Shield Advanced for an account.
shield:CreateSubscription.Title: CreateSubscription

shield:DeleteProtection.Description: Deletes an AWS Shield Advanced Protection.
shield:DeleteProtection.Title: DeleteProtection

shield:DeleteSubscription.Description: Removes AWS Shield Advanced from an account. AWS Shield Advanced requires a 1-year subscription commitment. You cannot delete a subscription prior to the completion of that commitment.
shield:DeleteSubscription.Title: DeleteSubscription

shield:DescribeAttack.Description: Describes the details of a DDoS attack.
shield:DescribeAttack.Title: DescribeAttack

shield:DescribeProtection.Description: Lists the details of a Protection object.
shield:DescribeProtection.Title: DescribeProtection

shield:DescribeSubscription.Description: Provides details about the AWS Shield Advanced subscription for an account.
shield:DescribeSubscription.Title: DescribeSubscription

shield:ListAttacks.Description: Returns all ongoing DDoS attacks or all DDoS attacks during a specified time period.
shield:ListAttacks.Title: ListAttacks

shield:ListProtections.Description: Lists all Protection objects for the account.
shield:ListProtections.Title: ListProtections

snowball:CancelCluster.Description: Cancels a cluster job. You can only cancel a cluster job while it's in the AwaitingQuorum status. You'll have at least an hour after creating a cluster job to cancel it.
snowball:CancelCluster.Title: CancelCluster

snowball:CancelJob.Description: Cancels the specified job. You can only cancel a job before its JobState value changes to PreparingAppliance. Requesting the ListJobs or DescribeJob action will return a job's JobState as part of the response element data returned.
snowball:CancelJob.Title: CancelJob

snowball:CreateAddress.Description: Creates an address for a Snowball to be shipped to. Addresses are validated at the time of creation. The address you provide must be located within the serviceable area of your region. If the address is invalid or unsupported, then an exception is thrown.
snowball:CreateAddress.Title: CreateAddress

snowball:CreateCluster.Description: Creates an empty cluster. Each cluster supports five nodes. You use the CreateJob action separately to create the jobs for each of these nodes. The cluster does not ship until these five node jobs have been created.
snowball:CreateCluster.Title: CreateCluster

snowball:CreateJob.Description: Creates a job to import or export data between Amazon S3 and your on-premises data center. Your AWS account must have the right trust policies and permissions in place to create a job for Snowball. If you're creating a job for a node in a cluster, you only need to provide the clusterId value; the other job attributes are inherited from the cluster.
snowball:CreateJob.Title: CreateJob

snowball:DescribeAddress.Description: Takes an AddressId and returns specific details about that address in the form of an Address object.
snowball:DescribeAddress.Title: DescribeAddress

snowball:DescribeAddresses.Description: Returns a specified number of ADDRESS objects. Calling this API in one of the US regions will return addresses from the list of all addresses associated with this account in all US regions.
snowball:DescribeAddresses.Title: DescribeAddresses

snowball:DescribeCluster.Description: Returns information about a specific cluster including shipping information, cluster status, and other important metadata.
snowball:DescribeCluster.Title: DescribeCluster

snowball:DescribeJob.Description: Returns information about a specific job including shipping information, job status, and other important metadata.
snowball:DescribeJob.Title: DescribeJob

snowball:GetJobManifest.Description: Returns a link to an Amazon S3 presigned URL for the manifest file associated with the specified JobId value. You can access the manifest file for up to 60 minutes after this request has been made. To access the manifest file after 60 minutes have passed, you'll have to make another call to the GetJobManifest action.
snowball:GetJobManifest.Title: GetJobManifest

snowball:GetJobUnlockCode.Description: Returns the UnlockCode code value for the specified job. A particular UnlockCode value can be accessed for up to 90 days after the associated job has been created.
snowball:GetJobUnlockCode.Title: GetJobUnlockCode

snowball:GetSnowballUsage.Description: Returns information about the Snowball service limit for your account, and also the number of Snowballs your account has in use.
snowball:GetSnowballUsage.Title: GetSnowballUsage

snowball:ListClusterJobs.Description: Returns an array of JobListEntry objects of the specified length. Each JobListEntry object is for a job in the specified cluster and contains a job's state, a job's ID, and other information.
snowball:ListClusterJobs.Title: ListClusterJobs

snowball:ListClusters.Description: Returns an array of ClusterListEntry objects of the specified length. Each ClusterListEntry object contains a cluster's state, a cluster's ID, and other important status information.
snowball:ListClusters.Title: ListClusters

snowball:ListJobs.Description: Returns an array of JobListEntry objects of the specified length. Each JobListEntry object contains a job's state, a job's ID, and a value that indicates whether the job is a job part, in the case of export jobs. Calling this API action in one of the US regions will return jobs from the list of all jobs associated with this account in all US regions.
snowball:ListJobs.Title: ListJobs

snowball:UpdateCluster.Description: While a cluster's ClusterState value is in the AwaitingQuorum state, you can update some of the information associated with a cluster. Once the cluster changes to a different job state, usually 60 minutes after the cluster being created, this action is no longer available.
snowball:UpdateCluster.Title: UpdateCluster

snowball:UpdateJob.Description: While a job's JobState value is New, you can update some of the information associated with a job. Once the job changes to a different job state, usually within 60 minutes of the job being created, this action is no longer available.
snowball:UpdateJob.Title: UpdateJob

sns:AddPermission.Description: Adds a statement to a topic's access control policy, granting access for the specified AWS accounts to the specified actions.
sns:AddPermission.Title: AddPermission

sns:CheckIfPhoneNumberIsOptedOut.Description: Accepts a phone number and indicates whether the phone holder has opted out of receiving SMS messages from your account. You cannot send SMS messages to a number that is opted out.
sns:CheckIfPhoneNumberIsOptedOut.Title: CheckIfPhoneNumberIsOptedOut

sns:ConfirmSubscription.Description: Verifies an endpoint owner's intent to receive messages by validating the token sent to the endpoint by an earlier Subscribe action. If the token is valid, the action creates a new subscription and returns its Amazon Resource Name (ARN). This call requires an AWS signature only when the AuthenticateOnUnsubscribe flag is set to "true".
sns:ConfirmSubscription.Title: ConfirmSubscription

sns:CreatePlatformApplication.Description: Creates a platform application object for one of the supported push notification services, such as APNS and GCM, to which devices and mobile apps may register. You must specify PlatformPrincipal and PlatformCredential attributes when using the CreatePlatformApplication action. The PlatformPrincipal is received from the notification service. For APNS/APNS_SANDBOX, PlatformPrincipal is "SSL certificate". For GCM, PlatformPrincipal is not applicable. For ADM, PlatformPrincipal is "client id". The PlatformCredential is also received from the notification service. For WNS, PlatformPrincipal is "Package Security Identifier". For MPNS, PlatformPrincipal is "TLS certificate". For Baidu, PlatformPrincipal is "API key".
sns:CreatePlatformApplication.Title: CreatePlatformApplication

sns:CreatePlatformEndpoint.Description: Creates an endpoint for a device and mobile app on one of the supported push notification services, such as GCM and APNS. CreatePlatformEndpoint requires the PlatformApplicationArn that is returned from CreatePlatformApplication. The EndpointArn that is returned when using CreatePlatformEndpoint can then be used by the Publish action to send a message to a mobile app or by the Subscribe action for subscription to a topic. The CreatePlatformEndpoint action is idempotent, so if the requester already owns an endpoint with the same device token and attributes, that endpoint's ARN is returned without creating a new endpoint. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:CreatePlatformEndpoint.Title: CreatePlatformEndpoint

sns:CreateTopic.Description: Creates a topic to which notifications can be published. Users can create at most 100,000 topics. For more information, see http://aws.amazon.com/sns. This action is idempotent, so if the requester already owns a topic with the specified name, that topic's ARN is returned without creating a new topic.
sns:CreateTopic.Title: CreateTopic

sns:DeleteEndpoint.Description: Deletes the endpoint for a device and mobile app from Amazon SNS. This action is idempotent. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:DeleteEndpoint.Title: DeleteEndpoint

sns:DeletePlatformApplication.Description: Deletes a platform application object for one of the supported push notification services, such as APNS and GCM. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:DeletePlatformApplication.Title: DeletePlatformApplication

sns:DeleteTopic.Description: Deletes a topic and all its subscriptions. Deleting a topic might prevent some messages previously sent to the topic from being delivered to subscribers. This action is idempotent, so deleting a topic that does not exist does not result in an error.
sns:DeleteTopic.Title: DeleteTopic

sns:GetEndpointAttributes.Description: Retrieves the endpoint attributes for a device on one of the supported push notification services, such as GCM and APNS. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:GetEndpointAttributes.Title: GetEndpointAttributes

sns:GetPlatformApplicationAttributes.Description: Retrieves the attributes of the platform application object for the supported push notification services, such as APNS and GCM. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:GetPlatformApplicationAttributes.Title: GetPlatformApplicationAttributes

sns:GetSMSAttributes.Description: Returns the settings for sending SMS messages from your account.
sns:GetSMSAttributes.Title: GetSMSAttributes

sns:GetSubscriptionAttributes.Description: Returns all of the properties of a subscription.
sns:GetSubscriptionAttributes.Title: GetSubscriptionAttributes

sns:GetTopicAttributes.Description: Returns all of the properties of a topic. Topic properties returned might differ based on the authorization of the user.
sns:GetTopicAttributes.Title: GetTopicAttributes

sns:ListEndpointsByPlatformApplication.Description: Lists the endpoints and endpoint attributes for devices in a supported push notification service, such as GCM and APNS. The results for ListEndpointsByPlatformApplication are paginated and return a limited list of endpoints, up to 100. If additional records are available after the first page results, then a NextToken string will be returned. To receive the next page, you call ListEndpointsByPlatformApplication again using the NextToken string received from the previous call. When there are no more records to return, NextToken will be null. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:ListEndpointsByPlatformApplication.Title: ListEndpointsByPlatformApplication

sns:ListPhoneNumbersOptedOut.Description: Returns a list of phone numbers that are opted out, meaning you cannot send SMS messages to them.
sns:ListPhoneNumbersOptedOut.Title: ListPhoneNumbersOptedOut

sns:ListPlatformApplications.Description: Lists the platform application objects for the supported push notification services, such as APNS and GCM. The results for ListPlatformApplications are paginated and return a limited list of applications, up to 100. If additional records are available after the first page results, then a NextToken string will be returned. To receive the next page, you call ListPlatformApplications using the NextToken string received from the previous call. When there are no more records to return, NextToken will be null. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:ListPlatformApplications.Title: ListPlatformApplications

sns:ListSubscriptions.Description: Returns a list of the requester's subscriptions. Each call returns a limited list of subscriptions, up to 100. If there are more subscriptions, a NextToken is also returned. Use the NextToken parameter in a new ListSubscriptions call to get further results.
sns:ListSubscriptions.Title: ListSubscriptions

sns:ListSubscriptionsByTopic.Description: Returns a list of the subscriptions to a specific topic. Each call returns a limited list of subscriptions, up to 100. If there are more subscriptions, a NextToken is also returned. Use the NextToken parameter in a new ListSubscriptionsByTopic call to get further results.
sns:ListSubscriptionsByTopic.Title: ListSubscriptionsByTopic

sns:ListTopics.Description: Returns a list of the requester's topics. Each call returns a limited list of topics, up to 100. If there are more topics, a NextToken is also returned. Use the NextToken parameter in a new ListTopics call to get further results.
sns:ListTopics.Title: ListTopics

sns:OptInPhoneNumber.Description: Use this request to opt in a phone number that is opted out, which enables you to resume sending SMS messages to the number.
sns:OptInPhoneNumber.Title: OptInPhoneNumber

sns:Publish.Description: Sends a message to an Amazon SNS topic or sends a text message (SMS message) directly to a phone number.
sns:Publish.Title: Publish

sns:RemovePermission.Description: Removes a statement from a topic's access control policy.
sns:RemovePermission.Title: RemovePermission

sns:SetEndpointAttributes.Description: Sets the attributes for an endpoint for a device on one of the supported push notification services, such as GCM and APNS. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications.
sns:SetEndpointAttributes.Title: SetEndpointAttributes

sns:SetPlatformApplicationAttributes.Description: Sets the attributes of the platform application object for the supported push notification services, such as APNS and GCM. For more information, see Using Amazon SNS Mobile Push Notifications. For information on configuring attributes for message delivery status, see Using Amazon SNS Application Attributes for Message Delivery Status.
sns:SetPlatformApplicationAttributes.Title: SetPlatformApplicationAttributes

sns:SetSMSAttributes.Description: Use this request to set the default settings for sending SMS messages and receiving daily SMS usage reports.
sns:SetSMSAttributes.Title: SetSMSAttributes

sns:SetSubscriptionAttributes.Description: Allows a subscription owner to set an attribute of the topic to a new value.
sns:SetSubscriptionAttributes.Title: SetSubscriptionAttributes

sns:SetTopicAttributes.Description: Allows a topic owner to set an attribute of the topic to a new value.
sns:SetTopicAttributes.Title: SetTopicAttributes

sns:Subscribe.Description: Prepares to subscribe an endpoint by sending the endpoint a confirmation message. To actually create a subscription, the endpoint owner must call the ConfirmSubscription action with the token from the confirmation message. Confirmation tokens are valid for three days.
sns:Subscribe.Title: Subscribe

sns:Unsubscribe.Description: Deletes a subscription. If the subscription requires authentication for deletion, only the owner of the subscription or the topic's owner can unsubscribe, and an AWS signature is required. If the Unsubscribe call does not require authentication and the requester is not the subscription owner, a final cancellation message is delivered to the endpoint, so that the endpoint owner can easily resubscribe to the topic if the Unsubscribe request was unintended.
sns:Unsubscribe.Title: Unsubscribe

sqs:AddPermission.Description: Adds a permission to a queue for a specific principal. This allows sharing access to the queue.
sqs:AddPermission.Title: AddPermission

sqs:ChangeMessageVisibility.Description: Changes the visibility timeout of a specified message in a queue to a new value. The maximum allowed timeout value is 12 hours. For more information, see Visibility Timeout in the Amazon Simple Queue Service Developer Guide.
sqs:ChangeMessageVisibility.Title: ChangeMessageVisibility

sqs:ChangeMessageVisibilityBatch.Description: Changes the visibility timeout of multiple messages. This is a batch version of ChangeMessageVisibility. The result of the action on each message is reported individually in the response. You can send up to 10 ChangeMessageVisibility requests with each ChangeMessageVisibilityBatch action.
sqs:ChangeMessageVisibilityBatch.Title: ChangeMessageVisibilityBatch

sqs:CreateQueue.Description: Creates a new standard or FIFO queue. You can pass one or more attributes in the request. Keep the following caveats in mind:
sqs:CreateQueue.Title: CreateQueue

sqs:DeleteMessage.Description: Deletes the specified message from the specified queue. You specify the message by using the message's receipt handle and not the MessageId you receive when you send the message. Even if the message is locked by another reader due to the visibility timeout setting, it is still deleted from the queue. If you leave a message in the queue for longer than the queue's configured retention period, Amazon SQS automatically deletes the message.
sqs:DeleteMessage.Title: DeleteMessage

sqs:DeleteMessageBatch.Description: Deletes up to ten messages from the specified queue. This is a batch version of DeleteMessage. The result of the action on each message is reported individually in the response.
sqs:DeleteMessageBatch.Title: DeleteMessageBatch

sqs:DeleteQueue.Description: Deletes the queue specified by the QueueUrl, regardless of the queue's contents. If the specified queue doesn't exist, Amazon SQS returns a successful response.
sqs:DeleteQueue.Title: DeleteQueue

sqs:GetQueueAttributes.Description: Gets attributes for the specified queue.
sqs:GetQueueAttributes.Title: GetQueueAttributes

sqs:GetQueueUrl.Description: Returns the URL of an existing queue. This action provides a simple way to retrieve the URL of an Amazon SQS queue.
sqs:GetQueueUrl.Title: GetQueueUrl

sqs:ListDeadLetterSourceQueues.Description: Returns a list of your queues that have the RedrivePolicy queue attribute configured with a dead-letter queue.
sqs:ListDeadLetterSourceQueues.Title: ListDeadLetterSourceQueues

sqs:ListQueues.Description: Returns a list of your queues. The maximum number of queues that can be returned is 1,000. If you specify a value for the optional QueueNamePrefix parameter, only queues with a name that begins with the specified value are returned.
sqs:ListQueues.Title: ListQueues

sqs:PurgeQueue.Description: Deletes the messages in a queue specified by the QueueURL parameter.
sqs:PurgeQueue.Title: PurgeQueue

sqs:ReceiveMessage.Description: Retrieves one or more messages (up to 10), from the specified queue. Using the WaitTimeSeconds parameter enables long-poll support. For more information, see Amazon SQS Long Polling in the Amazon Simple Queue Service Developer Guide.
sqs:ReceiveMessage.Title: ReceiveMessage

sqs:RemovePermission.Description: Revokes any permissions in the queue policy that matches the specified Label parameter.
sqs:RemovePermission.Title: RemovePermission

sqs:SendMessage.Description: Delivers a message to the specified queue.
sqs:SendMessage.Title: SendMessage

sqs:SendMessageBatch.Description: Delivers up to ten messages to the specified queue. This is a batch version of SendMessage. For a FIFO queue, multiple messages within a single batch are enqueued in the order they are sent.
sqs:SendMessageBatch.Title: SendMessageBatch

sqs:SetQueueAttributes.Description: Sets the value of one or more queue attributes. When you change a queue's attributes, the change can take up to 60 seconds for most of the attributes to propagate throughout the Amazon SQS system. Changes made to the MessageRetentionPeriod attribute can take up to 15 minutes.
sqs:SetQueueAttributes.Title: SetQueueAttributes

ssm:AddTagsToResource.Description: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified resource. Tags are metadata that you can assign to your documents, managed instances, Maintenance Windows, Parameter Store parameters, and patch baselines. Tags enable you to categorize your resources in different ways, for example, by purpose, owner, or environment. Each tag consists of a key and an optional value, both of which you define. For example, you could define a set of tags for your account's managed instances that helps you track each instance's owner and stack level. For example: Key=Owner and Value=DbAdmin, SysAdmin, or Dev. Or Key=Stack and Value=Production, Pre-Production, or Test.
ssm:AddTagsToResource.Title: AddTagsToResource

ssm:CancelCommand.Description: Attempts to cancel the command specified by the Command ID. There is no guarantee that the command will be terminated and the underlying process stopped.
ssm:CancelCommand.Title: CancelCommand

ssm:CreateActivation.Description: Registers your on-premises server or virtual machine with Amazon EC2 so that you can manage these resources using Run Command. An on-premises server or virtual machine that has been registered with EC2 is called a managed instance. For more information about activations, see Setting Up Systems Manager in Hybrid Environments.
ssm:CreateActivation.Title: CreateActivation

ssm:CreateAssociation.Description: Associates the specified Systems Manager document with the specified instances or targets.
ssm:CreateAssociation.Title: CreateAssociation

ssm:CreateAssociationBatch.Description: Associates the specified Systems Manager document with the specified instances or targets.
ssm:CreateAssociationBatch.Title: CreateAssociationBatch

ssm:DeleteActivation.Description: Deletes an activation. You are not required to delete an activation. If you delete an activation, you can no longer use it to register additional managed instances. Deleting an activation does not de-register managed instances. You must manually de-register managed instances.
ssm:DeleteActivation.Title: DeleteActivation

ssm:DeleteAssociation.Description: Disassociates the specified Systems Manager document from the specified instance.
ssm:DeleteAssociation.Title: DeleteAssociation

ssm:DeleteDocument.Description: Deletes the Systems Manager document and all instance associations to the document.
ssm:DeleteDocument.Title: DeleteDocument

ssm:DeleteParameter.Description: Delete a parameter from the system.
ssm:DeleteParameter.Title: DeleteParameter

ssm:DeregisterManagedInstance.Description: Removes the server or virtual machine from the list of registered servers. You can reregister the instance again at any time. If you don't plan to use Run Command on the server, we suggest uninstalling the SSM Agent first.
ssm:DeregisterManagedInstance.Title: DeregisterManagedInstance

ssm:DeregisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Description: Removes a patch group from a patch baseline.
ssm:DeregisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Title: DeregisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup

ssm:DeregisterTargetFromMaintenanceWindo.Description: Removes a target from a Maintenance Window.
ssm:DeregisterTargetFromMaintenanceWindo.Title: DeregisterTargetFromMaintenanceWindow

ssm:DeregisterTaskFromMaintenanceWindow.Description: Removes a task from a Maintenance Window.
ssm:DeregisterTaskFromMaintenanceWindow.Title: DeregisterTaskFromMaintenanceWindow

ssm:DescribeActivations.Description: Details about the activation, including: the date and time the activation was created, the expiration date, the IAM role assigned to the instances in the activation, and the number of instances activated by this registration.
ssm:DescribeActivations.Title: DescribeActivations

ssm:DescribeAssociation.Description: Describes the association for the specified target or instance. If you created the association by using the Targets parameter, then you must retrieve the association by using the association ID. If you created the association by specifying an instance ID and a Systems Manager document, then you retrieve the association by specifying the document name and the instance ID.
ssm:DescribeAssociation.Title: DescribeAssociation

ssm:DescribeAutomationExecutions.Description: Provides details about all active and terminated Automation executions.
ssm:DescribeAutomationExecutions.Title: DescribeAutomationExecutions

ssm:DescribeAvailablePatches.Description: Lists all patches that could possibly be included in a patch baseline.
ssm:DescribeAvailablePatches.Title: DescribeAvailablePatches

ssm:DescribeDocument.Description: Describes the specified Systems Manager document.
ssm:DescribeDocument.Title: DescribeDocument

ssm:DescribeDocumentPermission.Description: Describes the permissions for a Systems Manager document. If you created the document, you are the owner. If a document is shared, it can either be shared privately (by specifying a user's AWS account ID) or publicly (All).
ssm:DescribeDocumentPermission.Title: DescribeDocumentPermission

ssm:DescribeEffectivePatchesForPatchBase.Description: Retrieves the current effective patches (the patch and the approval state) for the specified patch baseline. Note that this API applies only to Windows patch baselines.
ssm:DescribeEffectivePatchesForPatchBase.Title: DescribeEffectivePatchesForPatchBaseline

ssm:DescribeInstanceAssociationsStatus.Description: The status of the associations for the instance(s).
ssm:DescribeInstanceAssociationsStatus.Title: DescribeInstanceAssociationsStatus

ssm:DescribeInstanceInformation.Description: Describes one or more of your instances. You can use this to get information about instances like the operating system platform, the SSM Agent version (Linux), status etc. If you specify one or more instance IDs, it returns information for those instances. If you do not specify instance IDs, it returns information for all your instances. If you specify an instance ID that is not valid or an instance that you do not own, you receive an error.
ssm:DescribeInstanceInformation.Title: DescribeInstanceInformation

ssm:DescribeInstancePatchStates.Description: Retrieves the high-level patch state of one or more instances.
ssm:DescribeInstancePatchStates.Title: DescribeInstancePatchStates

ssm:DescribeInstancePatchStatesForPatchG.Description: Retrieves the high-level patch state for the instances in the specified patch group.
ssm:DescribeInstancePatchStatesForPatchG.Title: DescribeInstancePatchStatesForPatchGroup

ssm:DescribeInstancePatches.Description: Retrieves information about the patches on the specified instance and their state relative to the patch baseline being used for the instance.
ssm:DescribeInstancePatches.Title: DescribeInstancePatches

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTa.Description: Retrieves the individual task executions (one per target) for a particular task executed as part of a Maintenance Window execution.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTa.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTaskInvocations

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTa.Description: For a given Maintenance Window execution, lists the tasks that were executed.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTa.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutionTasks

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutions.Description: Lists the executions of a Maintenance Window. This includes information about when the Maintenance Window was scheduled to be active, and information about tasks registered and run with the Maintenance Window.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutions.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindowExecutions

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowTargets.Description: Lists the targets registered with the Maintenance Window.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowTargets.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindowTargets

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowTasks.Description: Lists the tasks in a Maintenance Window.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindowTasks.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindowTasks

ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindows.Description: Retrieves the Maintenance Windows in an AWS account.
ssm:DescribeMaintenanceWindows.Title: DescribeMaintenanceWindows

ssm:DescribePatchBaselines.Description: Lists the patch baselines in your AWS account.
ssm:DescribePatchBaselines.Title: DescribePatchBaselines

ssm:DescribePatchGroupState.Description: Returns high-level aggregated patch compliance state for a patch group.
ssm:DescribePatchGroupState.Title: DescribePatchGroupState

ssm:DescribePatchGroups.Description: Lists all patch groups that have been registered with patch baselines.
ssm:DescribePatchGroups.Title: DescribePatchGroups

ssm:GetAutomationExecution.Description: Get detailed information about a particular Automation execution.
ssm:GetAutomationExecution.Title: GetAutomationExecution

ssm:GetCommandInvocation.Description: Returns detailed information about command execution for an invocation or plugin.
ssm:GetCommandInvocation.Title: GetCommandInvocation

ssm:GetDefaultPatchBaseline.Description: Retrieves the default patch baseline. Note that Systems Manager supports creating multiple default patch baselines. For example, you can create a default patch baseline for each operating system.
ssm:GetDefaultPatchBaseline.Title: GetDefaultPatchBaseline

ssm:GetDeployablePatchSnapshotForInstanc.Description: Retrieves the current snapshot for the patch baseline the instance uses. This API is primarily used by the AWS-RunPatchBaseline Systems Manager document.
ssm:GetDeployablePatchSnapshotForInstanc.Title: GetDeployablePatchSnapshotForInstance

ssm:GetDocument.Description: Gets the contents of the specified Systems Manager document.
ssm:GetDocument.Title: GetDocument

ssm:GetInventorySchema.Description: Return a list of inventory type names for the account, or return a list of attribute names for a specific Inventory item type.
ssm:GetInventorySchema.Title: GetInventorySchema

ssm:GetMaintenanceWindowExecution.Description: Retrieves details about a specific task executed as part of a Maintenance Window execution.
ssm:GetMaintenanceWindowExecution.Title: GetMaintenanceWindowExecution

ssm:GetMaintenanceWindowExecutionTask.Description: Retrieves the details about a specific task executed as part of a Maintenance Window execution.
ssm:GetMaintenanceWindowExecutionTask.Title: GetMaintenanceWindowExecutionTask

ssm:GetParameter.Description: Get information about a parameter by using the parameter name.
ssm:GetParameter.Title: GetParameter

ssm:GetParameterHistory.Description: Query a list of all parameters used by the AWS account.
ssm:GetParameterHistory.Title: GetParameterHistory

ssm:GetParametersByPath.Description: Retrieve parameters in a specific hierarchy. For more information, see Working with Systems Manager Parameters.
ssm:GetParametersByPath.Title: GetParametersByPath

ssm:GetPatchBaseline.Description: Retrieves information about a patch baseline.
ssm:GetPatchBaseline.Title: GetPatchBaseline

ssm:GetPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Description: Retrieves the patch baseline that should be used for the specified patch group.
ssm:GetPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Title: GetPatchBaselineForPatchGroup

ssm:ListAssociationVersions.Description: Retrieves all versions of an association for a specific association ID.
ssm:ListAssociationVersions.Title: ListAssociationVersions

ssm:ListAssociations.Description: Lists the associations for the specified Systems Manager document or instance.
ssm:ListAssociations.Title: ListAssociations

ssm:ListCommandInvocations.Description: An invocation is copy of a command sent to a specific instance. A command can apply to one or more instances. A command invocation applies to one instance. For example, if a user executes SendCommand against three instances, then a command invocation is created for each requested instance ID. ListCommandInvocations provide status about command execution.
ssm:ListCommandInvocations.Title: ListCommandInvocations

ssm:ListCommands.Description: Lists the commands requested by users of the AWS account.
ssm:ListCommands.Title: ListCommands

ssm:ListDocumentVersions.Description: List all versions for a document.
ssm:ListDocumentVersions.Title: ListDocumentVersions

ssm:ListDocuments.Description: Describes one or more of your Systems Manager documents.
ssm:ListDocuments.Title: ListDocuments

ssm:ListInventoryEntries.Description: A list of inventory items returned by the request.
ssm:ListInventoryEntries.Title: ListInventoryEntries

ssm:ListTagsForResource.Description: Returns a list of the tags assigned to the specified resource.
ssm:ListTagsForResource.Title: ListTagsForResource

ssm:ModifyDocumentPermission.Description: Shares a Systems Manager document publicly or privately. If you share a document privately, you must specify the AWS user account IDs for those people who can use the document. If you share a document publicly, you must specify All as the account ID.
ssm:ModifyDocumentPermission.Title: ModifyDocumentPermission

ssm:PutComplianceItems.Description: Registers a compliance type and other compliance details on a designated resource. This action lets you register custom compliance details with a resource. This call overwrites existing compliance information on the resource, so you must provide a full list of compliance items each time that you send the request.
ssm:PutComplianceItems.Title: PutComplianceItems

ssm:PutInventory.Description: Bulk update custom inventory items on one more instance. The request adds an inventory item, if it doesn't already exist, or updates an inventory item, if it does exist.
ssm:PutInventory.Title: PutInventory

ssm:PutParameter.Description: Add one or more parameters to the system.
ssm:PutParameter.Title: PutParameter

ssm:RegisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Description: Registers a patch baseline for a patch group.
ssm:RegisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup.Title: RegisterPatchBaselineForPatchGroup

ssm:RegisterTargetWithMaintenanceWindow.Description: Registers a target with a Maintenance Window.
ssm:RegisterTargetWithMaintenanceWindow.Title: RegisterTargetWithMaintenanceWindow

ssm:RegisterTaskWithMaintenanceWindow.Description: Adds a new task to a Maintenance Window.
ssm:RegisterTaskWithMaintenanceWindow.Title: RegisterTaskWithMaintenanceWindow

ssm:RemoveTagsFromResource.Description: Removes all tags from the specified resource.
ssm:RemoveTagsFromResource.Title: RemoveTagsFromResource

ssm:SendCommand.Description: Executes commands on one or more managed instances.
ssm:SendCommand.Title: SendCommand

ssm:StartAutomationExecution.Description: Initiates execution of an Automation document.
ssm:StartAutomationExecution.Title: StartAutomationExecution

ssm:StopAutomationExecution.Description: Stop an Automation that is currently executing.
ssm:StopAutomationExecution.Title: StopAutomationExecution

ssm:UpdateAssociation.Description: Updates an association. You can update the association name and version, the document version, schedule, parameters, and Amazon S3 output.
ssm:UpdateAssociation.Title: UpdateAssociation

ssm:UpdateAssociationStatus.Description: Updates the status of the Systems Manager document associated with the specified instance.
ssm:UpdateAssociationStatus.Title: UpdateAssociationStatus

ssm:UpdateDocument.Description: The document you want to update.
ssm:UpdateDocument.Title: UpdateDocument

ssm:UpdateDocumentDefaultVersion.Description: Set the default version of a document.
ssm:UpdateDocumentDefaultVersion.Title: UpdateDocumentDefaultVersion

ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindow.Description: Updates an existing Maintenance Window. Only specified parameters are modified.
ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindow.Title: UpdateMaintenanceWindow

ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindowTarget.Description: Modifies the target of an existing Maintenance Window. You can't change the target type, but you can change the following:
ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindowTarget.Title: UpdateMaintenanceWindowTarget

ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindowTask.Description: Modifies a task assigned to a Maintenance Window. You can't change the task type, but you can change the following values:
ssm:UpdateMaintenanceWindowTask.Title: UpdateMaintenanceWindowTask

ssm:UpdateManagedInstanceRole.Description: Assigns or changes an Amazon Identity and Access Management (IAM) role to the managed instance.
ssm:UpdateManagedInstanceRole.Title: UpdateManagedInstanceRole

ssm:UpdatePatchBaseline.Description: Modifies an existing patch baseline. Fields not specified in the request are left unchanged.
ssm:UpdatePatchBaseline.Title: UpdatePatchBaseline

states:CreateActivity.Description: Creates an activity. An activity is a task which you write in any programming language and host on any machine which has access to AWS Step Functions. Activities must poll Step Functions using the GetActivityTask API action and respond using SendTask* API actions. This function lets Step Functions know the existence of your activity and returns an identifier for use in a state machine and when polling from the activity.
states:CreateActivity.Title: CreateActivity

states:CreateStateMachine.Description: Creates a state machine. A state machine consists of a collection of states that can do work (Task states), determine to which states to transition next (Choice states), stop an execution with an error (Fail states), and so on. State machines are specified using a JSON-based, structured language.
states:CreateStateMachine.Title: CreateStateMachine

states:DeleteStateMachine.Description: Deletes a state machine. This is an asynchronous operation: It sets the state machine's status to DELETING and begins the deletion process. Each state machine execution is deleted the next time it makes a state transition.
states:DeleteStateMachine.Title: DeleteStateMachine

states:GetActivityTask.Description: Used by workers to retrieve a task (with the specified activity ARN) which has been scheduled for execution by a running state machine. This initiates a long poll, where the service holds the HTTP connection open and responds as soon as a task becomes available (i.e. an execution of a task of this type is needed.) The maximum time the service holds on to the request before responding is 60 seconds. If no task is available within 60 seconds, the poll returns a taskToken with a null string.
states:GetActivityTask.Title: GetActivityTask

states:GetExecutionHistory.Description: Returns the history of the specified execution as a list of events. By default, the results are returned in ascending order of the timeStamp of the events. Use the reverseOrder parameter to get the latest events first.
states:GetExecutionHistory.Title: GetExecutionHistory

states:ListExecutions.Description: Lists the executions of a state machine that meet the filtering criteria.
states:ListExecutions.Title: ListExecutions

states:SendTaskFailure.Description: Used by workers to report that the task identified by the taskToken failed.
states:SendTaskFailure.Title: SendTaskFailure

states:SendTaskHeartbeat.Description: Used by workers to report to the service that the task represented by the specified taskToken is still making progress. This action resets the Heartbeat clock. The Heartbeat threshold is specified in the state machine's Amazon States Language definition. This action does not in itself create an event in the execution history. However, if the task times out, the execution history contains an ActivityTimedOut event.
states:SendTaskHeartbeat.Title: SendTaskHeartbeat

states:SendTaskSuccess.Description: Used by workers to report that the task identified by the taskToken completed successfully.
states:SendTaskSuccess.Title: SendTaskSuccess

storagegateway:ActivateGateway.Description: Activates the gateway you previously deployed on your host. For more information, see Activate the AWS Storage Gateway. In the activation process, you specify information such as the region you want to use for storing snapshots or tapes, the time zone for scheduled snapshots the gateway snapshot schedule window, an activation key, and a name for your gateway. The activation process also associates your gateway with your account; for more information, see UpdateGatewayInformation.
storagegateway:ActivateGateway.Title: ActivateGateway

storagegateway:AddCache.Description: Configures one or more gateway local disks as cache for a gateway. This operation is only supported in the cached volume, tape and file gateway architectures (see Storage Gateway Concepts).
storagegateway:AddCache.Title: AddCache

storagegateway:AddUploadBuffer.Description: Configures one or more gateway local disks as upload buffer for a specified gateway. This operation is supported for the stored volume, cached volume and tape gateway architectures.
storagegateway:AddUploadBuffer.Title: AddUploadBuffer

storagegateway:AddWorkingStorage.Description: Configures one or more gateway local disks as working storage for a gateway. This operation is only supported in the stored volume gateway architecture. This operation is deprecated in cached volume API version 20120630. Use AddUploadBuffer instead.
storagegateway:AddWorkingStorage.Title: AddWorkingStorage

storagegateway:CancelArchival.Description: Cancels archiving of a virtual tape to the virtual tape shelf (VTS) after the archiving process is initiated. This operation is only supported in the tape gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CancelArchival.Title: CancelArchival

storagegateway:CancelRetrieval.Description: Cancels retrieval of a virtual tape from the virtual tape shelf (VTS) to a gateway after the retrieval process is initiated. The virtual tape is returned to the VTS. This operation is only supported in the tape gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CancelRetrieval.Title: CancelRetrieval

storagegateway:CreateCachediSCSIVolume.Description: Creates a cached volume on a specified cached volume gateway. This operation is only supported in the cached volume gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateCachediSCSIVolume.Title: CreateCachediSCSIVolume

storagegateway:CreateNFSFileShare.Description: Creates a file share on an existing file gateway. In Storage Gateway, a file share is a file system mount point backed by Amazon S3 cloud storage. Storage Gateway exposes file shares using a Network File System (NFS) interface. This operation is only supported in the file gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateNFSFileShare.Title: CreateNFSFileShare

storagegateway:CreateSnapshot.Description: Initiates a snapshot of a volume.
storagegateway:CreateSnapshot.Title: CreateSnapshot

storagegateway:CreateSnapshotFromVolumeR.Description: Initiates a snapshot of a gateway from a volume recovery point. This operation is only supported in the cached volume gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateSnapshotFromVolumeR.Title: CreateSnapshotFromVolumeRecoveryPoint

storagegateway:CreateStorediSCSIVolume.Description: Creates a volume on a specified gateway. This operation is only supported in the stored volume gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateStorediSCSIVolume.Title: CreateStorediSCSIVolume

storagegateway:CreateTapeWithBarcode.Description: Creates a virtual tape by using your own barcode. You write data to the virtual tape and then archive the tape. A barcode is unique and can not be reused if it has already been used on a tape . This applies to barcodes used on deleted tapes. This operation is only supported in the tape gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateTapeWithBarcode.Title: CreateTapeWithBarcode

storagegateway:CreateTapes.Description: Creates one or more virtual tapes. You write data to the virtual tapes and then archive the tapes. This operation is only supported in the tape gateway architecture.
storagegateway:CreateTapes.Title: CreateTapes

storagegateway:DeleteBandwidthRateLimit.Description: Deletes the bandwidth rate limits of a gateway. You can delete either the upload and download bandwidth rate limit, or you can delete both. If you delete only one of the limits, the other limit remains unchanged. To specify which gateway to work with, use the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the gateway in your request.
storagegateway:DeleteBandwidthRateLimit.Title: DeleteBandwidthRateLimit

storagegateway:DeleteChapCredentials.Description: Deletes Challenge-Handshake Authentication Protocol (CHAP) credentials for a specified iSCSI target and initiator pair.
storagegateway:DeleteChapCredentials.Title: DeleteChapCredentials

storagegateway:DeleteFileShare.Description: Deletes a file share from a file gateway. This operation is only supported in the file gateway architecture.
storagegateway:DeleteFileShare.Title: DeleteFileShare

storagegateway:DeleteGateway.Description: Deletes a gateway. To specify which gateway to delete, use the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the gateway in your request. The operation deletes the gateway; however, it does not delete the gateway virtual machine (VM) from your host computer.
